    "questions": [
      {
        "id": "q1",
        "label": "1)",
        "text": "(a) How did Rebbi Meir react to those ruffians who lived in his vicinity and why were a constant thorn in his side?\n(b) B'ruryah however, objected.   Who was B'ruryah?\n(c) How did she refute the suggested source of her husband's actions as the first half of the Pasuk in Tehilim \"Yitamu Chata'im min ha'Aretz\" from ...\n1. ... those very words themselves?\n2. ... the second half of the Pasuk \"u'Resha'im Od Einam!\"?\n(d) How did she therefore interpret the Pasuk?\n(e) What happened in the end?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q2",
        "label": "2)",
        "text": "(a) What Kashya did a certain Tzedoki ask B'ruryah regarding the Pasuk \"Rani Akarah Lo Yaladah (Praise Hash-m, the barren woman who has no children)!\"?\n(b) How did she address the Tzedoki?\n(c) How did she refute this interpretation of the Pasuk, based on the its continuation \"ki Rabim B'nei Shomeimah mi'Benei Be'ulah, Amar Hash-m\"?\n(d) How did she subsequently explain the Pasuk \"Rani Akarah ... \"?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q3",
        "label": "3)",
        "text": "(a) What did another Tzedoki find strange about the position of the two Kapitels \"Mizmor le'David. be'Vorcho Mipnei Avshalom B'no\" (Tehilim 3) and \" ... le'David Michtam be'Vorcho Mipnei Shaul ba'Me'arah\" (Kapitel 57)?\n(b) Rebbi Avahu answered him based on the principle 'S'muchin'.   What does 'S'muchin', which in turn, is based on the Pasuk in Tehilim \"S'muchim la'Ad le'Olam\", mean?\n(c) Which Kapitel does the former above-mentioned Kapitel juxtapose?\n(d) How did Rebbi Avahu therefore answer the Tzedoki's Kashya? What did he prove from Avshalom?\n(e) What prompted the Tzedoki (who was apparently learned) to ask the Kashya in spite of 'Semuchin'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q4",
        "label": "4)",
        "text": "(a) According to the Rebbi Yochanan in the name of Rebbi Shimon bar Yochai, to whom was Shlomoh ha'Melech referring, when he wrote in Mishlei \"Pihah Paschah \"?\n(b) He said \"Borchi Nafshi es Hash-m, ve'Chol K'ravai es Shem Kodsho\" when he was still inside his mother's stomach. Where was he when he said ...\n1. ... \"Barchu Hash-m Mal'achav, Giborei Ko'ach, Osei Devaro, li'Shemo'a be'Kol Devaro!\"?\n2. ... \"Borchi Nafshi es Hash-m, ve'Al Tishk'chu Kol Gemulav!\"\n(c) Why did he see fit to sing Shirah when when suckling his mother's breasts?\n(d) According to Rebbi Avahu, this was to prevent him from looking at the Makom Ervah.   What reason does Rav Masna give?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q5",
        "label": "5)",
        "text": "(a) What was he referring to when he said ...\n1. ... \"Yitamu Chata'im min ha'Aretz u'Resha'im; Borchi Nafshi es Hash-m ... \"?\n2. ... \"Borchi Nafshi es Hash-m, Hash-m Elokai Gadalta Me'od Hod ve'Hadar Lavashta\"?\n(b) In what connection does Rabah bar Shiloh cite the Pasuk there \"Tastir Panecha Yibaleihun, Tosef Rucham Yigva'un\"?\n(c) Rav Shimi bar Ukva (or Rav Ukva) would often visit Rebbi Shimon ben Pazi.   What did he tend to do in front of Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q6",
        "label": "6)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rebbi Shimon ben Pazi answer him, when he asked him about the meaning of the Pasuk \"Borchi Nafshi es Hash-m, ve'Chol K'ravai es Shem Kodsho\"?\n(b) What is the connection between the current Pasuk and the words \"Ein Tzur k'Elokeinu\" (in the Pasuk in Shmuel said by Chanah \"Ein Kadosh ka'Hashem ki Ein Bitecha, ve'Ein Tzur k'Elokeinu\").\n(c) And how did Rebbi Yehudah bar Menasyah amend the words there \"ki Ein Bitecha\"?\n(d) What is the Pasuk then coming to teach us?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q7",
        "label": "7)",
        "text": "(a) Rebbi Shimi bar Ukva pointed out that Rebbi Shimon ben Pazi had misunderstood his question.   What had he really meant to ask him concerning the five 'Borchi Nafshi\"?\n(b) To which the latter answered that it refers to two things; One of them is Hakadosh-Baruch-Hu.   What is the other?\n(c) What are the first three things, one connected with ...\n1. ... space, one with ...\n2. ... sight and one with ...\n3. ... sustaining)?\n(d) The fourth is that the Neshamah, like Hakadosh-Baruch-Hu, is pure.   What is the fifth comparison (to do with location)?\n(e) What is the punch-line of the current comparison?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q8",
        "label": "8)",
        "text": "(a) How did Rav Hamnuna explain the Pasuk in Koheles \"Mi ke'ha'Chacham, u'Mi Yode'a Pesher Davar?\" Who is the Chacham referred to here?\n(b) What problem did Chizkiyahu ha'Melech and Yeshayahu ha'Navi have (concerning Sancheriv, Melech Ashur's imminent attack of Yerushalayim)?\n(c) What made ...\n1. ... Chizkiyahu think that Yeshayah should come and visit him?\n2. ... Yeshayahu think that Chizkayih should come to him?\n(d) What compromise did Hash-m arrange?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q9",
        "label": "9)",
        "text": "(a) What did the Navi tell Chizkiyah when he arrived?\n(b) What had the latter done to deserve the death-sentence?\n(c) Why did the Navi use the double Lashon \"ki Meis Atah ve'Lo Sichyeh\"?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q10",
        "label": "10)",
        "text": "(a) How did Chizkiyah defend himself? Why did he indeed not get married?\n(b) On what grounds did Yeshayah refute his argument?\n(c) What did Chizkiyah therefore suggest?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q11",
        "label": "11)",
        "text": "(a) What did Chizkiyah retort when Yeshayah claimed that it was too late, since Hash-m had already decreed that he had to die?\n(b) What does the Pasuk in Iyov \"Hein Yikteleini, Lo Ayacheil!\" mean?\n(c) What did Rebbi Yochanan and Rebbi Elazar both say about that?\n(d) Based on a Pasuk in Koheles, what does Rebbi Chanan say about someone whom the angel in charge of dreams informs that he is going to die?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q12",
        "label": "12)",
        "text": "(a) What did Chizkiyah do immediately following his response to Yeshayah?\n(b) Based on the Pasuk in Yirmiyah \"Me'aiMe'ai Ochilah mi'Kiros Libi\", how does Resh Lakish explain the words \"to the wall\"?\n(c) According to Rebbi Levi, he was referring to an incident concerning a wall (in connection with the Shunamis and Eliyahu ha'Navi).  Which incident?\n(d) What Kal ve'Chomer did he Darshen from there?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q13",
        "label": "13)",
        "text": "(a) Which good deed of his was Chizkiyah referring to when, after 'reminding' Hash-m how he always went in His ways, he added \"ve'ha'Tov be'Einecha Asisi\"?\n(b) Why was that considered a good deed?\n(c) Hiding the Book of Cures is one of the six things that Chizkiyahu did listed in the Beraisa.   With how many of them did the Chachamim agree?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q14",
        "label": "14)",
        "text": "(a) Besides hiding the Book of Cures and cutting-up the Copper Snake, what else does the Tana include in this list?\n(b) Why was it considered a good thing  ...\n1. ... to cut-up the copper snake?\n2. ... to drag his father's bones around Yerushalayim?\n(c) One of the three things with which the Chachamim disagreed was that he closed up the waters of the Gichon Spring.  Why did he do that?"
