  {
    "daf": 14,
    "questions": [
      {
        "id": "q1",
        "label": "1)",
        "text": "(a) We cite a Beraisa in support of the amendment to our Mishnah. In a case where someone is reading the Sh'ma meets his Rebbe or someone who is greater than him, Rebbi Meir says 'bi'Perakim Sho'el Mipnei ha'Kavod ... ', u'be'Emtza Sho'el Mipneiha'Yir'ah ... '.   How does he conclude each statement?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q2",
        "label": "2)",
        "text": "(a) Achai Tana de'bei Rebbi Chiya asked Rebbi Chiya whether the concession to interrupt extends to Hallel and Megilah.   On what grounds might it be ...\n1. ... permitted like Keri'as Sh'ma?\n2. ... forbidden?\n(b) What did Rebbi Chiya reply?\n(c) Rabah agrees that between chapters, one may interrupt.   What distinction does he draw with regard to interrupting in the middle of a chapter? When may one interrupt and when may one not?\n(d) How do we reconcile this with Ravina, who did not interrupt Hallel for Rav bar Sh'va, on a day when they did not say whole-Hallel?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q3",
        "label": "3)",
        "text": "(a) Ashi'an Tana de'bei Rebbi Ami asked Rebbi Ami whether someone who undertakes to fast is permitted to taste food (See Tos. DH 'To'em').  What is one tasting it for?\n(b) Why might it be ...\n1. ... permitted?\n2. ... forbidden?\n(c) What did Rebbi Ami reply?\n(d) We cite a Beraisa which exempts a woman who tastes food from reciting a B'rachah.   What does the Tana say about a person who is fasting tasting food?\n(e) We ask up to how much a person is permitted to taste.   How much did Rebbi Ami and Rebbi Asi actually taste?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q4",
        "label": "4)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rav say about someone who gives Shalom (greets) his fellowman before greeting Hash-m?\n(b) How does he learn it from the Pasuk in Yeshayah \"Chidlu lachem min ha'Adam asher Neshamah b'Apo ki ba'Meh Nechshav hu\"?\n(c) How does Shmuel interpret the Pasuk without amending the word \"ba'Meh\"?\n(d) What problem does Rav Sheishes have with this prohibition from our Mishnah?\n(e) How does Rebbi Aba qualify the prohibition in order to resolve the problem?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q5",
        "label": "5)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rav Idi bar Avin Amar Rebbi Yitzchak bar Ashi'an say about someone who sees to his own affairs before Davening?\n(b) How does he learn it from the Pasuk in Tehilim \"Tzedek Lefanav Yehalech Veyasem le'Derech Panav\"?\n(c) What is the Pasuk therefore mean?\n(d) And what does he say about somebody who Davens first before setting off on a journey?\n(e) From which Pasuk there does he learn it?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q6",
        "label": "6)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rebbi Yonah Amar Rebbi Zeira (or Rebbi Ze'ira) say about someone who goes seven days without dreaming?\n(b) How does he learn this from the Pasuk in Mishlei \" ... ve'Save'a Yalin Bal Yipaked Ra\"? Which word does he amend to arrive at this explanation?\n(c) How does Rav Acha b'rei de'Rebbi Chiya citing ... Rebbi Yochanan, who disagrees with the previous explanation, interpret the Pasuk as it stands?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q7",
        "label": "7)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rebbi Avahu Amar Rebbi Yochanan say in connection with Rebbi Yehudah's ruling 'Bein Elokeichem le'Emes Veyatziv Lo Yafsik'?\n(b) On which Pasuk in Yirmiyah is Rebbi Yehudah's ruling based?\n(c) What She'eilah do we ask about someone who waits after concluding \"Hash-m Elokeichem Emes\"? What was he waiting for?\n(d) Rebbi Avahu Amar Rebbi Yochanan rules that he does repeat 'Emes'.   What does Rabah say?\n(e) What did Rabah comment when he heard a Chazen repeat the word 'Emes'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q8",
        "label": "8)",
        "text": "(a) When Rav Shmuel bar Yehudah arrived in Bavel from Eretz Yisrael, what did he say about the text \"Daber el B'nei Yisrael ve'Amarta aleihem Ani Hash-m Elokeichem Emes\"?\n(b) What did Rav Yosef exclaim about Rav Shmuel bar Yehudah Yehudah's testimony?\n(c) Abaye queried him from a statement by Rav Kahana Amar Rav.   What did he say about reciting the Parshah of \"Vayomer\" at nighttime?\n(d) We cannot answer that \"Ve'amarta aleihem\" is not considered as having begun, due to a statement by Rav Shmuel bar Yitzchak Amar Rav.  What, according to him, is not considered a Haschalah and what is?\n(e) How did Rav Papa answer the Kashya, bearing in mind that Rav Shmuel bar Yehudah's original statement was made in the name of the Yerushalmim?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q9",
        "label": "9)",
        "text": "(a) On what grounds does Abaye therefore rule that ...\n1. ... one begins Parshas 'Vayomer'?\n2. ... since he has, he is obligated to complete the entire Parshah?\n(b) What does Rav Chiya bar Rav mean when he says that once someone says \"Ani Hash-m Elokeichem\", he needs to say \"Emes\"?\n(c) What problem do we have with the continuation of his statement (that if he didn't, he need not to add \"Emes\")?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q10",
        "label": "10)",
        "text": "(a) How do we solve the current problem?\n(b) What is the gist of the replacement B'rachah?\n(c) The Chazan concludes it with 've'Sharnu Lach'.   How does he  continue?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q11",
        "label": "11)",
        "text": "(a) According to Rebbi Shimon in a Beraisa, why is it only right for ...\n1. ... 'Sh'ma' to precede \"Vehayah Im Shamo'a\"?\n2. ... \"Vehayah Im Shamo'a\" to precede \"Vayomer\"?\n(b) What problem do we have with connecting learning Torah to the Sh'ma ...\n1. ... but not teaching it?\n2. ... but not performing Mitzvos?\n(c) And what similar problem do we have with connecting teaching Torah with \"Vehayah Im Shamo'a\" but not performing Mitzvos?\n(d) How do we therefore amend the Beraisa?\n(e) Why are the reasons given by Rebbi Yehoshua ben Korchah (first Malchus Shamayim ... ) not good enough?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q12",
        "label": "12)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rav once do after washing his hands, reading the Sh'ma and putting on his Tefilin?\n(b) We query him from a Beraisa, which discusses somebody who is digging a Kuch for a Meis.   What is a 'Kuch'?\n(c) What does the Tana there say regarding his obligation to recite the Sh'ma, Daven the Amidah, don Tefilin and perform all other Mitzvos?\n(d) On which principle is this ruling based?\n(e) How do we reconcile this with the continuation of the Beraisa, which obligates him proceed with the very same Mitzvos from which the Tana just exempted him?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q13",
        "label": "13)",
        "text": "(a) Where does the Seifa of the current Beraisa list the obligation to put onTefilin (creating a Kashya on Rav)?\n(b) How do we initially attempt to answer the Kashya by establishing Rav like Rebbi Yehoshua ben Korchah (in our Mishnah)?\n(c) Based on what logic do we refute that answer?\n(d) Moreover, we cite Rav Chiya bar Ashi's testimony which does not concur with our answer.   According to Rav Chiya bar Ashi, which two things did Rav used to do after washing his hands, reciting Birchas ha'Torah and teaching his Talmidim?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q14",
        "label": "14)",
        "text": "(a) How do we try to reconcile Rav Chiya bar Ashi's testimony with the previous ruling of Rav?\n(b) And how do we reject the suggestion that in that case, Rav Chiya bar Ashi's testimony would be meaningless.  What else might he be coming to teach us?\n(c) The question remains however that Rebbi Yehoshua ben Korchah's ruling is confined to Keriyah.   How do we finally explain Rav's first ruling? Why did he put on his Tefilin only after reciting the Sh'ma?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q15",
        "label": "15)",
        "text": "(a) What does Ula mean when he refers to someone who recites the Sh'ma without Tefilin as if he was giving false testimony about himself ?\n(b) Rebbi Chiya bar Aba compares it to bringing an Olah without a Minchah or a Shelamim without Nesachim.  What else might he have said?\n(c) Then why did he use the two examples that he did? On which Pasuk in Emor did he base it?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q16",
        "label": "16)",
        "text": "(a) Three of the five things that Rebbi Yochanan lists that a person needs to do in order to take upon himself Ol Malchus Shamayim in an ideal manner are washing his hands, putting on Tefilin and reciting the Sh'ma.   What must he also do ...\n1. ... before washing his hands?\n2. ... after reciting the Sh'ma?"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "daf": 15,
    "questions": [
      {
        "id": "q1",
        "label": "1)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rebbi Chiya bar Aba in the name of Rebbi Yochanan, based on the Pasuk in Tehilim \"Erchatz be'Nikayon Kapai, va'Asov'vah es Mizbach'cha, Hash-m\", consider someone who washes his hands, puts on Tefilin, recites the Shema and says the Amidah, as having achieved?\n(b) What did Rava ask Rebbi Chiya bar Aba, due to the 'extra' word \"be'Nikayon\", when it would have sufficed to write \"Architz Kapai\"?\n(c) What did Ravina tell Rava about a Talmid-Chacham who came from Eretz Yisrael concerning someone has no water to wash his hands before Davening?\n(d) What did he allow one to use besides loose earth or a clod of earth?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q2",
        "label": "2)",
        "text": "(a) How did Rava justify Ravina's ruling, based on the same Pasuk that we just cited? What does the Pasuk omit that supports it?\n(b) And he proved it further from a ruling of Rav Chisda.  What did Rav Chisda say about someone who searches for water when the time Davening falls due?\n(c) How do we qualify that? For which part of Davening is one obligated to search for water?\n(d) Why the difference?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q3",
        "label": "3)",
        "text": "(a) How far is one obligated to search for water for washing one's hands before Tefilah?\n(b) We confine that to searching in the direction that one is traveling.  What do we say about searching in other directions?\n(c) And what do we extrapolate from the statement that one does not need to search 'even a Mil'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q4",
        "label": "4)",
        "text": "(a) According to the Tana Kama, someone who recites the Sh'ma silently, without hearing what he is saying, is Yotzei.  What does Rebbi Yossi say?\n(b) According to Rebbi Yossi, someone who recites the Sh'ma and does read the words carefully is Yotzei.  What does Rebbi Yehudah say?\n(c) What does the Mishnah say about someone who reads the (Pesukim of the) Sh'ma backwards?\n(d) What does the Mishnah instruct a person who made a mistake in the Sh'ma and subsequently continued until the end?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q5",
        "label": "5)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rebbi Yossi learn from the word \"Sh'ma\"?\n(b) What does the Tana Kama Darshen from the same word?\n(c) From where does Rebbi Yossi then learn that one may recite the Sh'ma in any language that one understands?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q6",
        "label": "6)",
        "text": "(a) On what grounds does the Mishnah in T'rumos forbids a Cheresh who can speak to separate T'rumah?\n(b) What makes Rav Chisda initially think that the author there is Rebbi Yossi, who renders invalid the Sh'ma of someone who did not hear what he said?\n(c) On what grounds do we counter that it could just as well be Rebbi Yehudah?\n(d) How do we extrapolate this from the word 'ha'Korei' in ourMishnah (assuming that the Tana Kama is Rebbi Yehudah?\n(e) We refute this proof however, suggesting that really Rebbi Yehudah holds that one is not Yotzei even Bedieved.   Then why does he say 'ha'Korei'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q7",
        "label": "7)",
        "text": "(a) Establishing the Mishnah in T'rumos like Rebbi Yossi presents a problem with a Beraisa concerning Birchas ha'Mazon.  What does the Tana there say about someone who recites Birchas ha'Mazon quietly?\n(b) What is the problem?\n(c) On the other hand, establishing Rebbi Yehudah in our Mishnah by Bedi'eved creates a problem with a statement of Rebbi Yehudah b'rei de'Shimon ben Pazi.   What does Rebbi Yehudah b'rei de'Shimon ben Pazi say about a Cheresh who can speak but who cannot hear reciting the Sh'ma?\n(d) What is now the problem?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q8",
        "label": "8)",
        "text": "(a) After finally establishing that Rebbi Yehudah does indeed permit a Cheresh to read the Sh'ma, how do we reconcile this with the Beraisa which permits him to recite Birchas ha'Mazon only Bedieved?\n(b) The source for this is yet another Beraisa citing Rebbi Yehudah. What does Rebbi Yehudah citing Rebbi Elazar ben Azaryah say about someone recites the Sh'ma?\n(c) What is the Torah source for this ruling?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q9",
        "label": "9)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rebbi Meir retort, based on the Pasuk \"Ve'ahavta ... be'Chol Levavcha\"?\n(b) How does this last statement affect our interpretation of Rebbi Yehudah?\n(c) Based on the current Sugya, like whom does Rav Masna establish as the Tana Kama of the Mishnah in Megilah 'ha'Kol Kesheirim Lik'ros es ha'Megilah Chutz me'Chashu'?\n(d) What does 'Chutz mi'Chashu' then mean?\n(e) What does Rebbi Yehudah say there?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q10",
        "label": "10)",
        "text": "(a) On what grounds do we try to reject the suggestion that the Tana Kama is Rebbi Yehudah, and 'Chutz me'Chashu' means Lechatchilah, but Bedi'eved, a Cheresh is Kasher?\n(b) How do we refute that Kashya?\n(c) What other problem do we have with establishing Rebbi Yehudah as the Tana Kama of the Mishnah in Megilah?\n(d) We answer by establishing the entire Mishnah like Rebbi Yehudah, and presenting two kinds of Katan.   What are the two kinds?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q11",
        "label": "11)",
        "text": "(a) We add a section to the Mishnah ('Bameh Devarim Amurim ... ').  Which kind of Katan is Rebbi Yehudah referring too when he says ...\n1. ... in the Reisha 'Chutz me'Chashu'?\n2. ... in the Seifa that a Katan is Kasher?\n(b) In conclusion, the Sugya on Amud 'Alef' is repeated in its entirety.  With which Tana does the statement of Rebbi Yehudah b'rei de Rebbi Shimon ben Pazi (permitting Birchas ha'Mazon to be recited quietly Lechatchilah) conform?\n(c) Who is finally the author of the Beraisa, which renders Yotzei Bedi'eved someone who reads the Sh'ma quietly?\n(d) Which Tana argues with him?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q12",
        "label": "12)",
        "text": "(a) Like which two Tana'im does Rav Chisda Amar Rav Shilo rule?\n(b) Seeing as he rules like Rebbi Yehudah ...\n1. ... why does he find it necessary to rule like Rebbi Yehudah citing Rebbi Elazar ben Azaryah?\n2. ... citing Rebbi Elazar ben Azaryah, why does he then see fit to rule like Rebbi Yehudah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q13",
        "label": "13)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rav Yosef learn from the Pasuk in Ki Savo \"Haskeis u'Sh'ma Yisrael\" (in connection with what we just learned)?\n(b) We query him however, from a Beraisa which begins \"Lo Yevarech Adam Birchas ha'Mazon be'Libo\".   How does the Tana conclude?\n(c) How do we therefore amend Rav Yosef's statement? Why do some say that K'ri'as Sh'ma must be verbalized?\n(d) What does he conclude about Birchas ha'Mazon and other Mitzvos?\n(e) How does he then explain \"Haskeis u'Sh'ma Yisrael\"?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q14",
        "label": "14)",
        "text": "(a) Our Mishnah cited two Machlokos between Rebbi Yehudah Rebbi Yossi (regarding 'Kara ve'Lo Hishmi'a le'Aznav' and 'Kara ve'Lo Dikdek be'Osiyosehah').   What single ruling does Rav Tavi Amar Rebbi Yashiyah issue that covers both Machlokos?\n(b) Rav Tavi Amar Rebbi Yashiyah also quotes a Pasuk in Mishlei.  What does the Pasuk say about the grave, the womb and the land? What do they have in common.\n(c) How does he explain the comparison between the grave and the womb? What major issue does he learn from the womb?\n(d) And what Kal va'Chomer does he learn from there, based on the fact that the entry into the womb is does quietly?\n(e) What is Rav Tavi's final word on the matter?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q15",
        "label": "15)",
        "text": "(a) A Beraisa cited by Rav Oshaya in front of Rava states that 'Everything must be written, even the commands'.   What topic is he referring to?\n(b) Which 'commands' is he talking about?\n(c) How does he Darshen this from the word 'u'Chesavtam\"?\n(d) We suggest that the author of the Beraisa is Rebbi Yehudah.   What does Rebbi Yehudah say about including the commands of Parshas Sotah on the parchment?\n(e) How do we prove our point, assuming that Rebbi Yehudah's ruling there is based on the word \"ve'Chasav\" (in the Pasuk \"ve'Chasav es ha'Alos ha'Eileh\")?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q16",
        "label": "16)",
        "text": "(a) We query the previous suggestion however, inasmuch as Rebbi Yehudah's ruling there is not based on \"ve'Chasav\".   On which Pasuk is it actually based?\n(b) How does this imply that the author of the Beraisa is not Rebbi Yehudah? Why would we initially think that, according to Rebbi Yehudah, one would have to write everything even without \"u'Chesavtam\"?\n(c) How do we nevertheless reconcile the Beraisa with Rebbi Yehudah? Why is \"u'Chesavtam\" necessary after all?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q17",
        "label": "17)",
        "text": "(a) The Beraisa cited by Rav Ovadya Darshens the acronym of the word \"ve'Limadtem\" (in the second Parshah of the Sh'ma) - 'she'Tehei Limudcha Tam'.   What are the ramifications of this Limud?\n(b) What are some of the examples that Rava presents to illustrate this?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q18",
        "label": "18)",
        "text": "(a) Based on the Pasuk in Tehilim \"bi'Feros Shakai Melachim (with reference to Malchus Shamayim) bah Tashleg be'Tzalmon\", what does Rebbi Chama b'Rebbi Chanina say about whoever reads all the letters of the Sh'ma meticulously?\n(b) How does he therefore amend the word ...\n1. ... \"bi'Feros\"?\n2. ... be'Tzalmon\"?\n(c) What does he also learn from the juxtaposition of the word \"ka'Ahalim (in the Pasuk in Balak \"ka'Ahalim Nata Hash-m [See Tosfos DH Ohalimli li'Nechalim') next to the word \"ki'Nechalim\" (in the Pasuk there \"ki'Nechalim Nitayu\")?"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "daf": 16,
    "questions": [
      {
        "id": "q1",
        "label": "1)",
        "text": "(a) What were Rebbi Ami and Rebbi Asi doing for Rebbi Elazar when the latter decided to go to the Beis-ha'Medrash to see what he could pick up?\n(b) What topic did he find a Beraisa expert discussing?\n(c) What does the Tana say about someone who ...\n1. ... cannot remember where he is holding?\n2. ... knows he is in the middle of a specific Parshah, but cannot remember whereabouts?\n3. ... knows that he holds bein ha'Perakim, but does not know which bein ha'Perakim?\n4. ... cannot remember whether he is up to the first \"u'Chesavtam\" or the second one?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q2",
        "label": "2)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rebbi Yochanan comment on the last ruling?\n(b) Why is that?\n(c) What did Rebbi Ami and Rebbi Asi comment when Rebbi Elazar came and told them what he had heard?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q3",
        "label": "3)",
        "text": "(a) The Mishnah discusses laborers who are working on top of a tree or a Nidbach when the time arrives to recite the Sh'ma.   What is a 'Nidbach'?\n(b) What does the Mishnah say?\n(c) Does the same apply to the Amidah?\n(d) Why the difference?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q4",
        "label": "4)",
        "text": "(a) If a Chasan is Patur from the Sh'ma on the night of his marriage, on what condition does he remain Patur until Motza'ei Shabbos?\n(b) What did Raban Gamliel do on the night of his marriage?\n(c) What did he reply when his Talmidim reminded him that he had taught them that a Chasan is Patur?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q5",
        "label": "5)",
        "text": "(a) The Beraisa reiterates the Din of the Mishnah regarding laborers reciting the Sh'ma or the Amidah whilst working on a tree or on a building.   What does the Tana permit doing on an olive and a fig tree which is forbidden on any other tree?\n(b) Why is that?\n(c) What does he say about the employer doing the same thing?\n(d) Why is that?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q6",
        "label": "6)",
        "text": "(a) Rav Mari the son of Shmuel's daughter queries our Mishnah.   What was her name?\n(b) Why is he not called after his father (Isar Giyora)?\n(c) What does Rav Mari extrapolate from the Mishnah, which permits laborers to recite the Sh'ma on top of a tree or a building even whilst they are working?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q7",
        "label": "7)",
        "text": "(a) What problem does Rav Mari have with that, based on a Beraisa? What does the Tana there say?\n(b) The Tana actually learns this from a Gezeirah-Shavah (\"Sh'ma Yisrael\" \"Sh'ma Yisrael\") from a Pasuk in Ki Savo.   Which Pasuk?\n(c) What was Rava's response to Rav Mari's Kashya?\n(d) What did Rav Mari himself ...\n1. ... quoting Rav Sheishes answer?\n2. ... answer when they cited a Beraisa, where Beis-Hillel permits the workers to recite the Sh'ma even whilst they are working?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q8",
        "label": "8)",
        "text": "(a) What does the Beraisa say about employees during work-hours, reciting...\n1. ... the B'rachos of the Sh'ma?\n2. ... the B'rachos before and after eating?\n3. ... the Amidah?\n(b) What, besides Duchening if they are Kohanim, are they not permitted to do?\n(c) Why is that?\n(d) We query this Beraisa from another Beraisa, which obligates employees to recite an abridged version of the Amidah.   What does this abridged version comprise? What is it called?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q9",
        "label": "9)",
        "text": "(a) Rav Sheishes answers that this is in fact, a Machlokes between Raban Gamliel and Rebbi Yehoshua.  What does Rebbi Yehoshua say?\n(b) What problem do we have with this answer?\n(c) So we establish both Beraisos like Raban Gamliel.   On what condition does Raban Gamliel ...\n1. ... permit a worker to recite 'Havineinu'?\n2. ... obligate a worker to recite the full Amidah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q10",
        "label": "10)",
        "text": "(a) And we cite a Beraisa in support of this answer.   What does the Tana conclude with regard to workers who work merely for their meals (or where their boss has eaten with them) regarding Birchas ha'Mazon after the meal?\n(b) In the Reisha(which speaks where they paid full wages), the Tana requires them to recite a B'rachah before eating (See Hagahos ha'Bach).   How many B'rachos does he require them to recite after eating?\n(c) If the first Brachah consists of of Birchas ha'Zan (as we say it), what does the second B'rachah comprise?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q11",
        "label": "11)",
        "text": "(a) If, from \"be'Shivt'cha be'Veisecha\", the Beraisa learns that somebody who is performing a Mitzvah is Patur from reciting the Sh'ma, what does the Tana learn from \"u've'Lecht'cha ba'Derech\"?\n(b) What practical Halachah does he learn from there?\n(c) What about someone who marries an Almanah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q12",
        "label": "12)",
        "text": "(a) On what grounds do we query Rav Papa, who attributes the former ruling to the Torah's use of the word \"Derech\", which he initially assumes implies a personal journey?\n(b) How does he therefore amend his explanation (See Gemara 11a)?\n(c) Regarding the latter ruling, on what grounds do we initially differentiate between somebody who marries a Besulah and somebody who  marries an Almanah?\n(d) What problem do we have presenting the criterion as worry?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q13",
        "label": "13)",
        "text": "(a) The current problem is based on a statement of Rebbi Aba bar Zavda Amar Rav.   What does he say about an Aveil (despite the fact that he too is worried)?\n(b) What is the only Mitzvah from which he is exempt?\n(c) On which Pasuk in Yechezkel is this based?\n(d) To answer the Kashya, what distinction do we finally draw between marrying a Besulah on the one hand, and an Aveil and someone whose ship is sinking in the sea on the other?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q14",
        "label": "14)",
        "text": "(a) What did Raban Gamliel do ...\n1. ... the night after his wife's death?\n2. ... when Tavi his slave died?\n(b) How did he explain ...\n1. ... the former to his Talmidim when they reminded him that he had taught them that this was prohibited?\n2. ... the latter when his Talmidim reminded him that he had taught them that one does accept comfort for a slave that died?\n(c) What did Raban Shimon ben Gamliel comment when the Tana Kama declared that a Chasan is permitted to recite the Sh'ma on the first night of his wedding?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q15",
        "label": "15)",
        "text": "(a) On what basis did Raban Gamliel in our Mishnah allow himself to 'transgress' the prohibition of Aninus with regard to washing?\n(b) Besides prohibiting making a Shurah (two rows that one makes for an Aveil), which two other things does he negate following the burial of an Eved?\n(c) Where did Rebbi Eliezer go when his Talmidim came to comfort him after his Shifchah died?\n(d) He then entered an Anpilun.   What is an'Alpinun'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q16",
        "label": "16)",
        "text": "(a) Finally, Rebbi Eliezer went into the main room.   What did he mean when he commented that...\n1. ... he thought at first that they would be scalded with warm water?\n2. ... he now saw that even boiling water did not scald them?\n(b) After repeating the previous Beraisa, to what did he compare the 'comfort' of a deceased Eved or Shifchah?\n(c) So what should one actually say?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q17",
        "label": "17)",
        "text": "(a) In another Beraisa, the Tana Kama corroborates Rebbi Eliezer's opinion.   According to Rebbi Yossi, if he was faithful, one mentions that he was a good man and a faithful slave.   What does he allow one to add to that?\n(b) On what grounds did the Tana Kama object?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q18",
        "label": "18)",
        "text": "(a) What does the Beraisa say about the Avos and the Imahos?\n(b) On what grounds do we reject the suggestion that we stop there because we do not know from which tribe we descend?\n(c) Then why do we stop there?\n(d) What does yet another Beraisa say about giving Avadim or Sh'fachos a title (such as 'Aba [Mr.] P'loni' or 'Ima [Mrs.] P'lonis')?\n(e) Then why did they do that with regard to Raban Gamliel's Avadim?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q19",
        "label": "19)",
        "text": "(a) Rebbi Elazar explains the Pasuk in Tehilim \"Kein Avarech'cha be'Chayai, be'Shimcha Esa Kapi\".   If the first half of the Pasuk refers to K'ri'as Sh'ma, what does the second half refer to?\n(b) And what does he subsequently learn from the following Pasuk \"ve'Sifsei Renanos Yehalel Pi\"?\n(c) How does he learn this from there?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q20",
        "label": "20)",
        "text": "(a) What do Rebbi Elazar, Rebbi Yochanan, Rebbi Zeira, Rebbi Chiya, Rav, Rebbi and Rav Safra (all listed on this Amud) have in common? What did they all do after completing the Amidah?\n(b) The two best-known of these Tefilos are those of Rav (the 'Y'hi Ratzon' that precedes Rosh Chodesh Benching, and that of Rebbi, which we still say every day after Birchos ha'Shachar.   Which Tefilah is that?\n(c) What do we mean when, regarding the latter, we conclude 've'Af-al-Gav de'Kaymi Ketzutzei aleih de'Rebbi'?\n(d) Rav Safra prayed that Hash-m should make peace among the Angels of the nations and among the nations themselves.   What did he pray for regarding those who study Torah she'Lo li'Shemah?"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "daf": 17,
    "questions": [
      {
        "id": "q1",
        "label": "1)",
        "text": "(a) Rebbi Alexandri, Rav Hamnuna, Rava and Marb'reih de'Ravina too, would add their own daily Tefilah at the end of the Amidah.  According to the second version, what did Rebbi Alexandri say about wanting to perform the will of Hash-m? Which two obstructions did he pray that we overcome?\n(b) Rava would first declare that he was as worthless after birth as before.   What did he say about being dust even in his lifetime?\n(c) He concluded with a prayer that Hash-m should stop him from sinning again and that He should cleanse his sins.   What were his final words?\n(d) When did Rav Hamnuna say it?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q2",
        "label": "2)",
        "text": "(a) Of all the private Tefilos, the best-known is that of Mar b'rei de'Ravina.   Which famous prayer is that?\n(b) What did he ...\n1. ... insert in that Tefilah that we do not say?\n2. ... not say that we do?\n(c) What is the gist of the Tefilah that Rav Sheshes would add on a Ta'anis?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q3",
        "label": "3)",
        "text": "(a) When Rebbi Yochanan finished the Book of Iyov, he recited a Tefilah which began 'Man is destined to die, and animals to be Shechted;in any event they are all going to die, one way or another'.   How did his Tefilah end?\n(b) What did Sh'lomoh ha'Melech say about this in Seifer Koheles?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q4",
        "label": "4)",
        "text": "(a) The Rabbanan of Yavneh would often refer to the difference between 'myself' and my 'friend'.   To whom were they referring?\n(b) They would declare how both were 'creations of Hashem' and how the one worked in the field, whilst the other worked in town, neither taking upon themselves the work of the other.   Why might one justify the Am-ha'Aretz not taking up the work of the Talmid-Chacham?\n(c) Why does this argument not hold water?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q5",
        "label": "5)",
        "text": "(a) Abaye would say that a person should act  with cunning to attain the fear of Hash-m, and would quote the Pasuk in Mishlei \"Ma'aheh Rach Meishiv Cheimah\".   What does his mean?\n(b) With whom did he advise one to increase peace, besides with his brothers?\n(c) What does one achieve by doing so?\n(d) And he concluded that one should be accepted by all people.   What did they say about Raban Yochanan ben Zakei with reference to greeting people?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q6",
        "label": "6)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rava used to say is the main objective of Chochmah?\n(b) What was he otherwise worried about?\n(c) And he learns this from the Pasuk in Mishlei \"Reishis Chochmah Yir'as Hash-m, Seichel Tov le'Chol Oseihem\".   What did he extrapolate from the word \"Oseihem\"?\n(d) What did he say about anyone who performs she'Lo li'Shemah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q7",
        "label": "7)",
        "text": "(a) Rav would cite four mundane things and three character-traits that are done in this world but not in the Olam ha'Ba. Two of the ...\n1. ... former are eating and drinking.   What are the other two?\n2. ... latter are jealousy and hatred.   What is the third?\n(b) What will one find there instead?\n(c) We learn this from the Pasuk in Mishpatim \"Va'yechzu es ha'Elokim Va'yochlu Va'yishtu\".   About whom was that said?\n(d) What does the Pasuk mean?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q8",
        "label": "8)",
        "text": "(a) What do we learn from the Pasuk in Yeshayah \"Nashim Sha'ananos Komnah, Shema'anah Koli, B'nos Botchos ... \", both expressions that he did not mention in connection with men."
      },
      {
        "id": "q9",
        "label": "9)",
        "text": "(a) One of the things that women (who are not commanded to study Torah) must do to earn for themselves reward in Olam ha'Ba is taking their children to study Torah.   Why do Chazal refer to the Torah that the children learn as 'bei K'nishta'?\n(b) What are the other two things?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q10",
        "label": "10)",
        "text": "(a) What did the Rabbanan mean when, upon leaving the Beis-ha'Medrash of Rebbi Ami (or Rebbi Chanina), they made a long declaration which began 'Olamcha Tir'eh be'Chayecha'?\n(b) How did they continue?\n(c) To whom did they say this?\n(d) What was the significance of the declaration?\n(e) And what was the gist of the B'rachos that followed?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q11",
        "label": "11)",
        "text": "(a) Likewise, when the Rabbanan would leave the Beis-ha'Medrah of Rav Chisda (or Rebbi Shmuel bar Nachmeni) they would quote the Pasuk in Tehilim \"Alufeinu Mesubalim\".   What is the simple translation of the Pasuk? (Our Rebbes are laden).\n(b) Rav and Shmuel (and some say Rebbi Yochanan and Rebbi Elazar) explained the Pasuk; one of them said 'Alufeinu in Torah and Mesubalim with Mitzvos'.   What did the other one say?\n(c) How did they interpret the continuation of the Pasuk ...\n1. ... \"Ein Peretz\" (there should not be a breach [See Tosfos])\"?\n2. ... \"ve'Ein Yotzeis\" (See Tosfos)?\n3. ... \"ve'Ein Tzevachah\" (cries [See Tosfos])?\n(d) And how did they explain the final word in the Pasuk \"bi\"Rechovoseinu\"?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q12",
        "label": "12)",
        "text": "(a) Rav and Shmuel (or Rebbi Yochanan and Rebbi Elazar) argue over the Pasuk in Yeshayah \"Shim'u na Abirei Leiv ha'Rechokim mi'Tzedakah\". To whom does the Pasuk refer, according to them?\n(b) What does one of them mean when he explains that even though everybody else is sustained through Tzedakah, they are sustained 'by force'? What does he mean by 'by force'?\n(c) How does the other one explain the Pasuk?\n(d) What does he mean when he says tat Tzadikim are not?\n(e) The latter explanation conforms with a statement of Rav Yehudah Amar Rav.   What did Rav Yehudah Amar Rav say about a Bas-Kol and Rebbi Chanina ben Dosa?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q13",
        "label": "13)",
        "text": "(a) Rav Yehudah disagrees with the above explanations.  To which category of people does \"Abirei Leiv\" refer, according to him?\n(b) More explicitly, he mentions 'Guvai Tipshai'.   What does this mean?\n(c) To whom does it pertain according to the Gemara in Kidushin?\n(d) How does Rav Yosef prove that they were Tipshai?\n(e) What similar comment did Rav Ashi make regarding the Nochrim of Masa Mechsaya?."
      },
      {
        "id": "q14",
        "label": "14)",
        "text": "(a) According to the Tana Kama of the Mishnah in Pesachim, working on Tish'ah be'Av (afternoon) is a matter of Minhag.   What does he say about Talmidei-Chachamim?\n(b) What does Raban Shimon ben Gamliel say about that?\n(c) What dual problem does this create with our Mishnah?\n(d) How does Rebbi Yochanan solve the problem in two words?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q15",
        "label": "15)",
        "text": "(a) Rav Shisha b'rei de'Rav Idi leaves the Beraisa intact.  According to him, why do the Rabbanan permit taking on the mantle of a Talmid-Chacham regarding a Chasan reciting the Sh'ma, but not regarding not working on Tish'ah be'Av?\n(b) And why does Raban Shimon ben Gamliel forbid a Chasan to recite the Sh'ma, but permit an ordinary person to refrain from working on Tish'ah-be'Av?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q16",
        "label": "16)",
        "text": "(a) The Mishnah now discusses someone whose deceased relative is 'lying before him'.   What is he better known as?\n(b) Why is he Patur from K'ri'as-Shma (from Tefilah) and from Tefilin?\n(c) From what else is he Patur?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q17",
        "label": "17)",
        "text": "(a) Why do they change the pall-bearers as the stretcher is being transported to its burial-site?\n(b) What distinction does the Tana draw between those in front of the stretcher and those behind it?\n(c) Why is that?\n(d) Why are both groups Patur from Tefilah?\n(e) What is wrong with saying that it is because there is still time to Daven?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q18",
        "label": "18)",
        "text": "(a) Following the burial, on what condition does one begin to recite the Sh'ma?\n(b) Once they reach the Shurah (the row where they would comfort the Aveilim), who is Chayav to recite the Sh'ma and who is Patur?\n(c) We query the Lashon 'Mutal Lefanav' in the Mishnah from a Beraisa.   What does 'Mutal Lefanav' actually mean?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q19",
        "label": "19)",
        "text": "(a) What does the Beraisa say about somebody whose deceased is lying before him who wants to eat?\n(b) What if he has no other room in which to eat?\n(c) And what if there is ...\n1. ... no neighbor by whom he is able to eat?\n2. ... nothing with which to form a partition?\n(d) What is an Onein not permitted to eat and drink?\n(e) And what does the Tana mean when he says 've'Eino Meisav'?"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "daf": 18,
    "questions": [
      {
        "id": "q1",
        "label": "1)",
        "text": "(a) What B'rachos does the Onein recite before and after eating?\n(b) What does the Tana then mean when he adds ...\n1. ... 'Ein Mevorchin alav'?\n2. ... 've'Ein Mezamnin alav'?\n(c) In fact, he is Patur from all Mitzvos (Asei).   Which three Mitzvos does the Beraisa specifically mention?\n(d) What does the Tana Kama say about Shabbos?\n(e) How does Rebbi Yochanan explain Raban Shimon ben Gamliel's statement 'Since he Chayav these (Mitzvos [on Shabbos]), he is Chayav all the Mitzvos'? Which Mitzvah is he coming to obligate an Onein (even though the Tana Kama exempts him)?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q2",
        "label": "2)",
        "text": "(a) What problem does the Beraisa now create with 'Mutal Lefanav' in our Mishnah?\n(b) How does Rav Papa establish 'Patur ... ' in the Beraisa, to answer the Kashya?\n(c) How does Rav Ashi interpret 'Mutal Lefanav' to answer it?\n(d) How does he support this from the Pesukim in Chayei Sarah \"Vayakam Avraham me'al-P'nei Meiso\" and \"ve'Ekb'ra Meisi mi'Lefanai\"?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q3",
        "label": "3)",
        "text": "(a) What do we now extrapolate from the word 'Meiso' in our Mishnah ('Mi she'Meiso Mutal Lefanav')?\n(b) We query this from a Beraisa 'ha'Meshamer es ha'Meis ... Patur ... mi'Kol Mitzvos ha'Amuros ba'Torah'.   What is the contradiction to the Mishnah\t?\n(c) Why does a Meis need guarding?\n(d) How do we solve the problem? Which two independent P'turim are the Tena'im presenting?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q4",
        "label": "4)",
        "text": "(a) What is the problem with the Mishnah and the Beraisa, which confine the prohibition either to someone whose deceased relative the Meis is or to the person who is guarding it? Who else is Patur from Tefilin and from learning Torah\n(b) On which Pasuk in Mishlei is this prohibition cased?\n(c) What do we answer? What is the basic difference between the first two prohibitions and this one?\n(d) This answer is based on a statement of Mar.   What did Mar say that confines the latter Isur to within four Amos?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q5",
        "label": "5)",
        "text": "(a) What does ...\n1. ... the Tana Kama of the above Beraisa say about two Shomrim who are guarding a Meis?\n2. ... ben Azai say about two Shomrim who are transporting a Meis on a boat?\n(b) What reason does Ravina give to explain his opinion?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q6",
        "label": "6)",
        "text": "(a) What does another Beraisa say that someone who is transporting the bones of a Meis in a leather sack should not do?\n(b) Why is that?\n(c) On what condition does he permit it?\n(d) What is he referring to when he adds 've'Chein be'Seifer-Torah'?\n(e) Why can he not be referring to the prohibition in the Reisha?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q7",
        "label": "7)",
        "text": "(a) Based on what we learned a short while back, what did Rachba Amar Rav Yehudah say about somebody who sees a Meis passing and who does not accompany him? What has he transgressed?\n(b) Rav Asi informs us that, in the event that he does accompany him, his reward lies in the Pasuk in Mishlei \"Malveh Hash-m Chonein Dal\".    What does that have to do with the Mitzvah of Halvayas ha'Meis?\n(c) What does Rav Asi now learn from the Pasuk?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q8",
        "label": "8)",
        "text": "(a) What bothered Rebbi Chiyta when he and Rebbi Yonasan were once walking in a graveyard?\n(b) What did he answer when Rebbi Yonasan asked why he needed to lift his Tzitzis and conceal them?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q9",
        "label": "9)",
        "text": "(a) Why was Rebbi Yonasan surprised by Rebbi Chiya's reply?\n(b) Which Pasuk in Koheles did he quote in support of his theory?\n(c) And what did Rebbi Chiya mean when he retorted 'Im Karisa Lo Shanisa' Im Shanisa Lo Shilashta'?\n(d) How did he continue?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q10",
        "label": "10)",
        "text": "(a) Rebbi Chiya then proceeded to explain the Pasuk in Koheles to Rebbi Yonasan.   How did he explain the phrase ...\n1. ... \"Ki ha'Chayim Yod'im she'Yamusu\"?\n2. ... \"ve'ha'Meisim Einam Yod'im Me'umah\"?\n(b) The first source for the latter explanation is the Pasuk in Yechezkel \"ve'Atah Chalal Rasha, N'si Yisrael\".   To whom was the Navi speaking?\n(c) The second source is the Pasuk in Shoftim \"Al-pi Shenayim Eidim O Sheloshah Eidim Yumas ha'Meis\".   How does he learn it from there?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q11",
        "label": "11)",
        "text": "(a) He learns the former explanation from a Pasuk in Sh'muel.   To whom does the Navi refer as \"ben Ish Chai\"?\n(b) What does Rebbi Chiya extrapolate from there?\n(c) How does he explain ...\n1. ... \"Rav Pe'alim mi'Kabtze'el\"?\n2. ... \"ve'Hu Hikah es Sh'nei Ariel Mo'av?\n(d) The first of two interpretations of the continuation of the Pasuk \"ve'Hu Yarad ve'Hikah es ha'Ari be'Toch ha'Bor be'Yom ha'Shaleg\" is that he broke the ice in order to Tovel.   What is the second?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q12",
        "label": "12)",
        "text": "(a) What happened to the sons of Rebbi Chiya when they once went to tend to their property?\n(b) What did one of them say that caused the other one to cite the Pasuk in Iyov \"Yechabdu Banav ve'Lo Yada\"?\n(c) The first brother  countered by citing Rebbi Yitzchak in connection with the very next Pasuk \"Ach Besaro alav Yich'av, ve'Nafsho alav Te'abel\".   What did Rebbi Yitzchak extrapolate from there?\n(d) How did his brother refute the proof from there?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q13",
        "label": "13)",
        "text": "(a) So the first brother cited a Beraisa in connection with a certain Chasid, who once gave a Dinar to a poor man on Erev Rosh ha'Shanah.  What caused him to run away and spend the night in a graveyard?\n(b) What did he hear one spirit suggest to the other?\n(c) What did her friend reply? Why was she unable to accompany her?\n(d) What did the Chasid do when the spirit returned and informed her friend that the crops of whoever sows after the early rain will be destroyed by hail?\n(e) What subsequently happened?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q14",
        "label": "14)",
        "text": "(a) What happened the following year?\n(b) What did the same spirit discover 'from behind the curtain'?\n(c) What did the Chasid do and what ultimately happened?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q15",
        "label": "15)",
        "text": "(a) How did the Chasid's wife discover what had happened?\n(b) Why, on the following Rosh ha'Shanah night, did the spirit turn down her friend's suggestion that 'they' go out once again to discover what punishment awaits the world?\n(c) How happened that caused her to say that?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q16",
        "label": "16)",
        "text": "(a) What did one of the sons of Rebbi Chiya try to prove from there?\n(b) How did his brother refute the proof?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q17",
        "label": "17)",
        "text": "(a) What did Ze'iri discover when, after depositing money with the inn-keeper by whom he was staying, he returned from the Yeshivah?\n(b) What did he do?\n(c) Where did the innkeeper's spirit inform him that he would find the money?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q18",
        "label": "18)",
        "text": "(a) Which two items did the spirit ask Ze'iri to obtain from her mother?\n(b) How was he supposed to get it to her?\n(c) What use did she have for these things?\n(d) What did the one son of Rebbi Chiya try to prove from that episode?\n(e) How did his brother refute the proof?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q19",
        "label": "19)",
        "text": "(a) The same brother supports his argument from another episode cited in a Beraisa, this time in connection with the father of Shmuel (Rav's Chaver), with whom they had deposited money belonging to Yesomim.   Which problem arose after he died?\n(b) What did people begin to call Shmuel?\n(c) Who was 'Aba'?\n(d) What did 'they' reply when Shmuel followed his deceased father to the Beis-ha'Kevaros and asked for Aba?\n(e) What did they reply when he asked to see Aba ...\n1. ... bar Aba?\n2. ... bar Aba the father of Shmuel?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q20",
        "label": "20)",
        "text": "(a) What did Levi (Shmuel's deceased Chaver) reply when Shmuel asked him why he was sitting outside the Beis-ha'Medrash (in connection with Rebbi Efes)?\n(b) What was unusual about Shmuel's father when he eventually came out of the Beis-ha'Medrash?\n(c) Why was he ...\n1. ... crying?\n2. ... laughing?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q21",
        "label": "21)",
        "text": "(a) How did Shmuel's react when he heard the latter?\n(b) What happened on account of his request?\n(c) What did Shmuel's father then tell him he would find in ...\n1. ... the top and lower section of the mill?\n2. ... the middle section of the mill?\n(d) Why did he do that?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q22",
        "label": "22)",
        "text": "(a) What did the one brother try to prove from this episode?\n(b) From which part of the story did he try to prove it?\n(c) How did the other brother refute the proof?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q23",
        "label": "23)",
        "text": "(a) Based on a statement of Rebbi Shmuel bar Nachmeni in his name, Rebbi Yonasan retracted from his original stance.   What did Rebbi Yonasan initially say?\n(b) In his current statement, what does he learn from the word \"Leimor\" (in the Pasuk in ve'Zos ha'Berachah [where Hash-m said to Moshe] \"Zos ha'Aretz asher Nishba'ti le'Avraham ... Leimor ... \")?\n(c) What does he prove from there?\n(d) What problem do we have with that?\n(e) How do we solve it?"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "daf": 19,
    "questions": [
      {
        "id": "q1",
        "label": "1)",
        "text": "(a) 'Whoever speaks evil about a deceased person, may as well speak about a stone'. This might mean that the dead do not know what one says about them.   What else might it mean?\n(b) In that case, how can we explain the incident, cited by Rav Papa, in which someone spoke evil about Shmuel after his death, and a cane fell from the roof and pierced his brain?\n(c) What does Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi say happens to a person who speaks badly of a Talmid-Chacham after his death?\n(d) In the Pasuk on which he bases his statement (which follows the words \"Heitivah Hash-m la'Tovim\"), how does Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi explain ...\n1. ...  \"ve'ha Matim Akalkelosam\"?\n2. ... \"Yolichei Hash-m es Po'alei ha'Aven\"?\n3. ... \"Shalom al Yisrael\"?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q2",
        "label": "2)",
        "text": "(a) What does Tana de'Bei Rebbi Yishmael say one should think about a Talmid-Chacham whom one saw sin at night?\n(b) On what grounds do we reject the initial statement 'Shema Asah Teshuvah'?\n(c) So what did Tana de'bei Rebbi Yishmael really say?\n(d) If this is confined to where the Talmid-Chacham sinned bodily, what about where he sinned in money-related issues?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q3",
        "label": "3)",
        "text": "(a) In how many places did Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi tell Rebbi Elazar they placed a Niduy on someone on account of Kavod ha'Rav? in the Mishnah\n(b) How many of them are recorded in the Mishnah?\n(c) What did the former reply when the latter asked him whereabouts they are to be found?\n(d) What is then the significance of the following three cases: 'Someone who denigrates Netilas Yadayim, who speaks ill of a Talmid-Chacham after his death or who speaks to Hash-m in an arrogant manner?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q4",
        "label": "4)",
        "text": "(a) Regarding the second of the three cases, we cite a Mishnah in Iduyos, which describes how, in order to prove that a Giyores and a Meshuchreres are subject to the Din of Sotah, the Chachamim cited Sh'mayah and Avtalyon who gave 'Kurk'mis' Mei-Sotah to drink.   Who was Kurk'mis?\n(b) What did Akavya ben Mahalalel then comment?\n(c) What happened to Akavya ben Mahalalel after ...\n1. ... they placed a Niduy on him?\n2. ... he died?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q5",
        "label": "5)",
        "text": "(a) On what grounds did Rebbi Yehudah (there) reject the above version? Why could Akavya ben Mahalalel not have been guilty of the sin of which the Tana Kama accused him of?\n(b) According to him, who was the person on whom they placed a Niduy and why?\n(c) What did they do after his death?\n(d) Why"
      },
      {
        "id": "q6",
        "label": "6)",
        "text": "(a) The third case that Rebbi Elazar found was that of a man who troubled Hash-m a number of times to send rain the way he wanted it.   What was his name?\n(b) What message did Shimon ben Shetach send him? What would he have done to him had he not been Choni?\n(c) Then why didn't he?\n(d) What is the significance of the Pasuk in Mishlei that Shimon ben Shetach sent him \"Yismach Avicha ve'Imecha ve'Sagel Yolad'techa\"?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q7",
        "label": "7)",
        "text": "(a) We ask why Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi omitted the Beraisa in connection with Todos Ish Romi.   What did Todos Ish Romi initiate in Rome in connection with eating kid-goats on Seider-night?\n(b) Why were they called 'Mekulasin'?\n(c) Why did Shimon ben Shetach then place a Niduy on him?\n(d) Why indeed, did Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi omit that case?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q8",
        "label": "8)",
        "text": "(a) Similarly, we ask why he omitted the Mishnah involving Rebbi Eliezer.   What did Rebbi Eliezer say about an oven that they cut into segments between which they placed sand?\n(b) What did the Chachamim say?\n(c) What does Rav Yehudah Amar Rav say to explain why they referred to that oven as 'Tanur shel Achnai'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q9",
        "label": "9)",
        "text": "(a) What does the Beraisa say they did before placing a Niduy on Rebbi Eliezer?\n(b) So why did Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi omit that case?\n(c) If Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi had a list of twenty-four Mishnahs where the Chachamim placed a Niduy ... , how come that Rebbi Elazar found only three?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q10",
        "label": "10)",
        "text": "(a) The Beraisa forbids taking out a Meis for burial close to the time of Keri'as Sh'ma.   What if one did begin carrying him out?\n(b) How do we reconcile this with the fact they took Rav Yosef out to be buried close to the time of Keri'as Sh'ma?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q11",
        "label": "11)",
        "text": "(a) What does another Beraisa say about those who are 'dealing with the Hesped', if the Meis is lying in front of them?\n(b) What if it is not?\n(c) What does the Aveil do whilst they are ...\n1. ... reciting the Sh'ma?\n2. ... saying the Amidah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q12",
        "label": "12)",
        "text": "(a) In the previous case, the Aveil begins 'Master of the World, I have sinned much before you!'   How does he continue, according to the Beraisa?\n(b) And he concludes 'May it be Your will to repair our breaches and the breaches of all the world with mercy!'   On what grounds did Abaye object to the opening wording of the Aveil's Tefilah?\n(c) His objection is based on a statement of Resh Lakish (and of a Beraisa in the name of Rebbi Yossi).   What principle did Resh Lakish teach us, based on a Pasuk in Yeshayah?\n(d) The people there said \"Kim'at ki'Sedom Hayinu\".   What did the Navi answer them?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q13",
        "label": "13)",
        "text": "(a) We learned in our Mishnah that if, after burying the Meis, one is able to begin and finish the Sh'ma before reaching the Shurah, one should do so, but if not, not.   What does the Beraisa say that poses a Kashya on the Mishnah?\n(b) How do we explain the Mishnah to solve the problem?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q14",
        "label": "14)",
        "text": "(a) In the time of the Mishnah, when forming the Shurah, the Aveil would sit and the rows of people would file past him.   According to the Tana Kama, which rows were Patur from the Sh'ma and which rows were Chayav?\n(b) What was the criterion according to Rebbi Yehudah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q15",
        "label": "15)",
        "text": "(a) Based on the Pasuk in Mishlei \"Ein Chochmah, ve'Ein Tevunah ve'Ein Eitzah Neged Hash-m Hash-m\", what does Rav Yehudah Amar Shmuel say about someone who discovers he is wearing Sha'atnez whilst walking through the main street?\n(b) What reason does he present for his ruling?\n(c) We query this from a Beraisa which talks about accompanying an Aveil who is a Kohen from the Beis ha'Kevaros and where there are two possible paths along which to walk, one Tahor and one Tamei.    What does the Tana say one should do if the Aveil opts to walk along the one that is Tamei?\n(d) Why is this permitted (See Shitah Mekubetzes)?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q16",
        "label": "16)",
        "text": "(a) Based on another statement of Rav Yehudah Amar Shmuel, how did Rebbi Aba explain 'Tamei' in this context, so as not to pose a Kashya on Rav Yehudah Amar Shmuel?\n(b) What is a Beis-ha'Peras?\n(c) What were Chazal afraid might happen?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q17",
        "label": "17)",
        "text": "(a) Rav Yehudah gave a special concession regarding a Beis-ha'Peras to a person on his way to perform a specific Mitzvah.   Which Mitzvah?\n(b) What did he allow him to do?\n(c) What did Rav Yehudah bar Ashi Amar Rav say about a Beis-ha'Peras that has become trampled?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q18",
        "label": "18)",
        "text": "(a) We query Rav Yehudah Amar Shmuel again from another Beraisa, where Rebbi Elazar b'Rebbi Tzadok describes how they used to jump over graves to greet kings.   What was Rebbi Elazar b'Rebbi Tzadok's status?\n(b) What sort of kings was he referring to?\n(c) Why did they permit this even for Nochri kings?\n(d) How does this pose a Kashya on Rav Yehudah Amar Shmuel?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q19",
        "label": "19)",
        "text": "(a) To answer the Kashya, we cite Rava.   What distinction did Rava draw between an Ohel where there is a gap of a Tefach and one which there is not?\n(b) On which principle is the latter ruling based?\n(c) What did he say about the majority of coffins?\n(d) What did the Rabbanan decree?\n(e) ow does this answer the Kashya on Rav Yehudah Amar Shmuel?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q20",
        "label": "20)",
        "text": "(a) Once again, we query Rav Yehudah Amar Shmuel from a Beraisa.   What does  the Beraisa mean when it says 'Gadol Kavod ha'Beri'os'?\n(b) Why did they laugh at Rav bar Sh'va when in front of Rav Kahana he established the Beraisa by the La'av of \"Lo Sasur\"?\n(c) What did Rav Kahana comment about their reaction?\n(d) What did Rav bar Sh'va really mean to say?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q21",
        "label": "21)",
        "text": "(a) We now query Rav Yehudah Amar Shmuel from a Beraisa in connection with the Mitzvah of Hashavas Aveidah.   What does the Tana extrapolate from the words \"Vehis'alamta Meihem\" (in the Pasuk in Ki Seitzei Lo Sir'eh ... Vehis'alamta Meihem\")?\n(b) The Beraisa lists three examples: 1. If the finder is a Kohen and the article is lying in a Beis ha'Kevaros; 2. If he is a Zakein, and picking up the article and carrying it through the streets would be below his dignity.   What is the third example?\n(c) How do we initially answer the Kashya from there on Rav Yehudah Amar Shmuel?\n(d) Why can we not then apply it to Sha'atnez and all other cases of Kavod?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q22",
        "label": "22)",
        "text": "(a) Finally, we query Rav Yehudah Amar Shmuel from a Beraisa in connection with the Pasuk in Naso \"le'Aviv u'le'Imo, le'Achiv u'le'Achoso Lo Yitama\".   About whom is the Pasuk speaking?\n(b) After Darshening \"le'Aviv u'le'Imo\", what does the Beraisa learn from \"u'le'Achoso\" (in connection with someone who is on his way to Shecht his Korban Pesach or to circumcise his son)?\n(c) What is now the Kashya on Rav Yehudah Amar Shmuel from there?\n(d) What do we answer?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q23",
        "label": "23)",
        "text": "(a) On what basis is Sha'atnez that one is wearing in the street considered a 'Kum va'Asei'?\n(b) Why do we not learn from the fact that a Kohen and a Nazir render themselves Tamei for a Meis Mitzvah, that Kavod ha'Beri'os overrides even a La'av min ha'Torah, even be'Kum va'Asei?"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "daf": 20,
    "questions": [
      {
        "id": "q1",
        "label": "1)",
        "text": "(a) Rav Papa asked why it was that earlier generations were accustomed to witnessing more miracles than his own.   What prompted him to ask this question?\n(b) Why could the reason not have been due to the fact that the earlier generations were more learned than they were?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q2",
        "label": "2)",
        "text": "(a) They also had problems with the Mishnah in Uktzin, which discusses a woman who pickles vegetables in a pot' (or 'Olives that are pickled) together with their leaves'.   What does the Mishnah rule there?\n(b) Why do the leaves (which generally serve as a handle for the vegetables) not transmit Tum'ah to the vegetables?\n(c) What did Rav Yehudah comment when he arrived at that Mishnah?\n(d) What did Rav Papa say about the Yeshivos of his generation?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q3",
        "label": "3)",
        "text": "(a) What did Abaye answer Rav Papa? Why was Rav Yehudah's generation more worthy of miracles than theirs?\n(b) What example did Abaye give citing an incident that occurred with Rav Ada bar Ahavah?\n(c) What was his mistake?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q4",
        "label": "4)",
        "text": "(a) How much did Beis-Din penalize him?\n(b) Who was 'Masun'?\n(c) Who said 'Masun Masun'?\n(d) What was the significance of those words?\n(e) What is the connection between this episode and the previous Sugya?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q5",
        "label": "5)",
        "text": "(a) What was Rav Gidal doing sitting by the gates leading to the location where the women used to Tovel?\n(b) What did he reply when the Rabbanan asked him whether he was not afraid of the Yeitzer-ha'Ra?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q6",
        "label": "6)",
        "text": "(a) Why did Rebbi Yochanan do the same thing?\n(b) What did he answer when they asked him whether he was not afraid of 'Ayin ha'Ra'?\n(c) One of the sources for this lies in the Pasuk in Vayechi (in connection with Ya'akov's B'rachah to Yosef) \"Ben Poras Yosef, Ben Poras Alei Ayin\".  What did Rebbi Avahu Darshen from there?\n(d) How did Rebbi Yossi b'Rebbi Chanina learn it from the Pasuk there (in connection with Ya'akov's B'rachah to Yosef's sons) \" Veyidgu la'Rov be'Kerev ha'Aretz\"?\n(e) What logical reason do yet others give to explain why Yosef's descendents are not subject to Ayin ha'Ra?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q7",
        "label": "7)",
        "text": "(a) What does the Mishnah say about Nashim, Avadim and Ketanim, regarding ...\n1. ... Keri'as Sh'ma and Tefilin?\n2. ... Tefilah and Mezuzah?\n(b) Which other Mitzvah does the Mishnah add to the latter list?\n(c) Why are Ketanim Patur from Tefilin (even mi'de'Rabbanan)?\n(d) Seeing as Tefilah is a time-related Mitzvah, why are women Chayav?\n(e) The Gemara will discuss women vis-a-vis Birchas ha'Mazon shortly.   Why are they Chayav Mezuzah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q8",
        "label": "8)",
        "text": "(a) Why might we have otherwise thought that women are ...\n1. ... Patur from Tefilah?\n2. ... are Patur from Mezuzah?\n(b) Based on the Pasuk in Beshalach (in connection with the Manna) \"be'Seis Hash-m lachem ba'Erev Basar Le'echol ve'lechem ba'Boker Li'sbo'a\", why  might we have thought that women are Patur from Birchas ha'Mazon?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q9",
        "label": "9)",
        "text": "(a) What problem do we have with Rav Ada bar Ahavah, who says that women are Chayav to make Kidush on Shabbos min ha'Torah?\n(b) Besides the fact that if Rav Ada bar Ahavah had meant 'mi'de'Rabbanan, why did he say min ha'Torah, what other objection does Rava raise to Abaye's answer that Rav Ada bar Ahavah really meant that they are Chayav mi'de'Rabbanan?\n(c) How does Rava therefore answer the question by citing the Hekesh of \"Zachor\" to \"Shamor\"?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q10",
        "label": "10)",
        "text": "(a) What She'eilah did Ravina ask Rava concerning women and Birchas ha'Mazon?\n(b) What are the ramifications of the She'eilah?\n(c) Bearing in mind that Benching is not a time-bound Mitzvah, why might women nevertheless be Patur min ha'Torah?\n(d) How do we resolve this with the fact that the daughters of Tz'lofchad did receive a portion in Eretz Yisrael?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q11",
        "label": "11)",
        "text": "(a) Rava tried to resolve the She'eilah from a Beraisa which discusses various people being Motzi others Birchas ha'Mazon.   What does the Tana say about ...\n1. ... a small son being Motzi his father?\n2. ... an Eved being Motzi his master?\n3. ... a woman  being Motzi her husband?\n(b) What does the Tana say about a man who needs his wife and children to be Motzi him with Birchas ha'Mazon?\n(c) On what grounds does Ravina refute Rava's proof from the last case, that a woman must be Chayav min ha'Torah; otherwise how could she be Motzi her husband?\n(d) How must all three cases therefore be speaking?\n(e) What is the Shi'ur mi'de'Rabbanan according to ...\n1. ... Rebbi Meir?\n2. ... Rebbi Yehudah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q12",
        "label": "12)",
        "text": "(a) Rav Avira sometimes in the name of Rebbi Ami, sometimes in the name of Rebbi Asi, cited the angels.   What problem did the angels have with the Pasuk in Eikev \"asher Lo Yisa Panim ve'Lo Yikach Shochad\"?\n(b) How did Hash-m reconcile the two Pesukim?\n(c) If Hash-m wrote in the Torah \"Ve'achalta Ve'sava'ta u'Verachta\", what did Yisrael undertake to do?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q13",
        "label": "13)",
        "text": "(a) Why is a Ba'al Keri obligated to think the Sh'ma in his heart and not say it out loud?\n(b) How about the B'rachos before and after the Sh'ma?\n(c) Why is he not obligated to think them too?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q14",
        "label": "14)",
        "text": "(a) What does the Mishnah say about reciting the B'rachos over one's food?\n(b) Why the difference?\n(c) What does Rebbi Yehudah say?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q15",
        "label": "15)",
        "text": "(a) What does Ravina extrapolate from the fact that one is Yotzei the Sh'ma with Hirhur alone?\n(b) In that case, what is the point of not reciting it loud (See Tosfos DH 'ke'de'Ashk'chan ... ')?\n(c) What does Rav Chisda extrapolate from the fact that one does not recite the Sh'ma loud?\n(d) How does Rebbi Elazar then explain the need to think it?\n(e) How does Rav Ada bar Ahavah explain why it will not suffice simply to study another topic (See Hagahos ha'Bach)?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q16",
        "label": "16)",
        "text": "(a) We query this from the next Mishnah, which discusses someone who remembers that he is a Ba'al Keri in the middle of the Amidah.   What should he do?\n(b) What do we extrapolate from the fact that the Mishnah speaks specifically about a person who has already begun the Amidah?\n(c) How do we initially answer the Kashya? Why were the Chachamim more stringent by the Sh'ma than by the Amidah?\n(d) How do we query this answer from Birchas ha'Mazon in our Mishnah?\n(e) What do we finally answer to explain the difference between the Sh'ma and Birchas ha'Mazon on the one hand and the Amidah on the other?"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "daf": 21,
    "questions": [
      {
        "id": "q1",
        "label": "1)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rav Yehudah learn from the Pasuk in ...\n1. ... Eikev \"ve'Achalta ve'Sava'ta u'Verachta ... \"?\n2. ... Ha'azinu \"Ki Shem Hash-m Ekra, Havu Godel l'Elokeinu\"?\n(b) How did Rebbi Yochanan try to learn the B'rachah ...\n1. ... after Torah from Birchas ha'Mazon?\n2. ... before eating from Birchas ha'Torah?\n(c) How do we refute these Limudim? Why can one not learn ...\n1. ... Birchas Torah from Birchas ha'Mazon?\n2. ... the B'rachah over food from Birchas ha'Torah?\n(d) We also query Rebbi Yochanan from a Beraisa.   What distinction does the Tana draw between the B'rachah after eating and the B'rachah before eating?\n(e) What do we answer?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q2",
        "label": "2)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rav Yehudah say about someone who is unsure as to whether he ...\n1. ... recited the Sh'ma or not?\n2. ... said 'Emes ve'Yatziv' or not?\n(b) What reason did he give for this ruling?\n(c) What makes 'Emes ve'Yatziv' d'Oraysa?\n(d) Rav Yosef queried Rav Yehudah from the Pasuk \"u've'Shochb'cha u've'Kumecha\" (implying that reciting the Sh'ma twice a day is a Mitzvah min ha'Torah.   What did Abaye answer?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q3",
        "label": "3)",
        "text": "(a) What problem do we now have with this from our Mishnah, which obligates a Ba'al Keri to think the Sh'ma but not the B'rachos before and after it?\n(b) What do we answer?\n(c) Why is it preferable to think the Sh'ma than 'Emes ve'Yatziv'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q4",
        "label": "4)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rebbi Elazar say about someone who is uncertain as to whether he has ...\n1. ... recited the Sh'ma or not?\n2. ... Davened the Amidah or not?\n(b) What does Rebbi Yochanan comment about the latter?\n(c) On what condition does the B'hag Pasken like Rebbi Yochanan?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q5",
        "label": "5)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rav Yehudah Amar Shmuel say about someone who remembers in the middle of the Amidah that he has already Davened?\n(b) We query this from a She'eilah that Rav Nachman asked Rabah bar Avuhah concerning Talmidim who forget that it is Shabbos and begin the middle B'rachos of the Amidah with the weekday B'rachah.    What did Rabah bar Avuhah reply?\n(c) How do we refute the Kashya? Why are the cases not comparable?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q6",
        "label": "6)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rav Yehudah Amar Shmuel say about someone who has already Davened who enters Shul and finds the Tzibur Davening the Amidah? On what condition may he join them?\n(b) What if he is unable to add anything?\n(c) Following Rav Yehudah's ...\n1. ... first ruling concerning a Yachid at home, why did he see fit to add the latter ruling?\n2. ... latter ruling, why did he see fit to issue his first ruling?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q7",
        "label": "7)",
        "text": "(a) According to Rav Huna, someone who has not yet Davened who enters Shul and finds the Tzibur Davening, may begin the Amidah on condition he is able to finish it before the Shatz reaches 'Modim'.   What does Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi say?\n(b) Why is Rav Huna not concerned that the Yachid misses Kedushah be'Tzibur?\n(c) Bearing in mind that the Yachid says 'Modim' anyway, why is he then concerned about missing 'Modim' be'Tzibur?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q8",
        "label": "8)",
        "text": "(a) Rav Ada bar Ahavah concurs with Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi, who maintains that a Yachid does not say Kedushah on his own, even when Davening with the Tzibur.   From which Pasuk in Emor does he learn it?\n(b) And he learns that \"be'Soch\" refers to a Tzibur - \"Toch\" \"Toch\" from a Gezeirah Shavah cited by Ravna'i, the brother of Rebbi Chiya bar Aba.   Which Pasuk in Sh'lach L'cha (in connection with the ten bad spies) does he learn it?\n(c) How do he know that the Pasuk is speaking about ten people?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q9",
        "label": "9)",
        "text": "(a) What She'eilah did they ask regarding 'Yehei Sh'mo ha'Gadol Mevorach ... '?\n(b) What did Rav Dimi quote Rebbi Yehudah and Resh Lakish the Talmidim of Rebbi Yochanan as saying regarding this She'eilah?\n(c) What did they add regarding interrupting Ma'aseh Merkavah to answer it?\n(d) What is the Halachah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q10",
        "label": "10)",
        "text": "(a) What do we learn from the juxtaposition of the Pasuk in Va'esachanan \"Vehoda'tam le'Venecha ... \" (in connection with learning Torah) and that of \"Yom asher Amadta lifnei Hash-m Elokecha be'Chorev\"?\n(b) What Kashya does this pose on Rebbi Yehudah in our Mishnah?\n(c) On what grounds does Rav Yosef refute the suggestion that Rebbi Yehudah does not hold of 'Semuchin'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q11",
        "label": "11)",
        "text": "(a) What does ben Azai in a Beraisa, Darshen from the juxtaposition of the Pasuk in Mishpatim \"Mechasheifah Lo Sechayeh\" to that of \"Kol Shochev im Beheimah Mos Yumas\"?\n(b) What does Rebbi Yehudah counter that?\n(c) How does Rebbi Yehudah therefore learn the same ruling from 'Ov ve'Yid'oni'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q12",
        "label": "12)",
        "text": "(a) Rebbi Eliezer, in another Beraisa, permits a man to marry the woman that his father raped or seduced.   What does he say marrying the woman that his son raped or seduced?\n(b) With which of these rulings does Rebbi Yehudah disagree?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q13",
        "label": "13)",
        "text": "(a) Rav Gidal Amar Rav cites Rebbi Yehudah's source as the Pasuk in Ki Seitzei \"Lo Yikach Ish es Eishes Aviv ve'Lo Yegaleh K'naf Aviv\".   How does he interpret the latter half of the Pasuk?\n(b) How does he extrapolates this from the Pasuk that follows \"ve'Nasan ha'Ish ha'Shochev imah la'Avi ha'Na'arah\"?\n(c) What has Rav Yosef now proved?\n(d) We conclude that Rebbi Yehudah does indeed learn Semuchim in Devarim, and that he Darshens the Semuchim in question (\"Vehoda'tam le'Venecha ... \" and \"Yom asher Amadta lifnei Hash-m Elokecha be'Chorev\") like Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi.   How did Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi explain the Semuchim?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q14",
        "label": "14)",
        "text": "(a) We query Rebbi Yehudah (who permits a Ba'al Keri to learn Torah) from the Mishnah later, where the Tana Kama requires 'Zav she'Ra'ah Keri, ve'Nidah she'Paltah Shichvas Zera' and 'ha'Meshameshes ve'Ra'asah Dam to Tovel.   What does Rebbi Yehudah say?\n(b) What do we initially extrapolate from Rebbi Yehudah? What would he say with regard to an ordinary Ba'al Keri?\n(c) Why the difference?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q15",
        "label": "15)",
        "text": "(a) What do we mean when we counter that perhaps Rebbi Yehudah exempts a Ba'al Keri from Tevilah, and the Mishnah later presents the three cases on account of the Tana Kama?\n(b) We query this answer however, from the latter case 'ha'Meshameshes ve'Ra'asah Dam'.   What is the problem with establishing it according to the Tana Kama?\n(c) We are therefore forced to establish it like Rebbi Yedhudah.   What is the problem with that?\n(d) To solve the problem, how do we therefore amend 'Mevarech Lefanav u'le'Acharav' in our Mishnah?"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "daf": 22,
    "questions": [
      {
        "id": "q1",
        "label": "1)",
        "text": "(a) We query the current amendment of Rebbi Yehudah in our Mishnah from a Beraisa where Rebbi Meir permits a Ba'al Keri who has no water to recite the Sh'ma without any of the accompanying B'rachos.   What does he say about reciting a B'rachah before and after eating?\n(b) What does he say about thinking it?\n(c) What does Rebbi Yehudah say?\n(d) What does Rav Nachman bar Yitzchak answer? If at the end of the day, Rebbi Yehudah forbids learning Torah without Tevilah, on what grounds does he permit the recital of the B'rachos?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q2",
        "label": "2)",
        "text": "(a) And he cites a Beraisa as his source.   What distinction does the Tana draw between Zavin, Metzora'im and Ba'in al Nidos on the one hand and Ba'alei Keri on the other?\n(b) What two things does the Tana forbid the former to learn, besides T'nach, Mishnah and Gemara?\n(c) What is his source for the prohibition?\n(d) What does the Tana say based on the Pasuk in Yisro \"Va'yar ha'Am va'Yanu'u ... \"?\n(e) On what grounds do they then preclude Zavin, Metzora'im and Ba'in al Nidos in the prohibition?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q3",
        "label": "3)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rebbi Yossi permit a Ba'al Keri to do when it comes to Regiliyos? What are 'Regiliyos'?\n(b) What does he not permit?\n(c) Rebbi Yonasan ben Yosef even allows him to learn Mishnayos but not the relevant Medrashim.   Why is that?\n(d) What does Rebbi Nasan ben Avishalom say?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q4",
        "label": "4)",
        "text": "(a) Rebbi Yochanan ha'Sandlar is more stringent than the previous two opinions.   What did he say in the name of his Rebbe? What was the name of his Rebbe?\n(b) In the first Lashon, he permits a Ba'al Keri to enter the Beis-ha'Medrash and to remain silent.   What does he say in the second Lashon?\n(c) The last opinion is that of Rebbi Yehudah.   What does he allow a Ba'al Keri to learn?\n(d) What did he tell his Talmidim when they asked him why, when he was once a Ba'al Keri, and they were once walking beside a river, he made a point of Toveling before teaching them a Perek in Hilchos Derech Eretz?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q5",
        "label": "5)",
        "text": "(a) The most lenient opinion of all is that of Rebbi Yehudah ben Beseira.   What does he say?\n(b) What did he once say to a Talmid who was a Ba'al Keri and who was hurriedly mumbling Divrei Torah in his presence?\n(c) How did he learn this from the Pasuk in Yirmiyah \"ha'Lo Koh Devari ka'Eish, Ne'um Hash-m\"?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q6",
        "label": "6)",
        "text": "(a) We cite Rebbi Yonasan ben Yosef In the above Beraisa, who allows a Ba'al Keri to learn Mishnayos but not the relevant Medrashim in support of Rebbi Ila'i.   What did Rebbi Ila'i Amar Rav Acha bar Ya'akov in the name of Rabeinu say? To whom does 'Rabeinu' refer?\n(b) In another Beraisa, this is also the opinion of Rebbi Meir. According to one opinion, Rebbi Yehudah ben Gamliel, quoting his brother Rebbi Chanina forbids both Mishnayos and the relevant Medrashim.   What does the second opinion hold?\n(c) We equate the former opinion with Rebbi Yochanan ha'Sandlar (in the earlier Beraisa).   With whom do we equate the latter opinion?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q7",
        "label": "7)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rav Nachman bar Yitzchak say about 'those three elders' (Rebbi Ila'a, Rebbi Yashiyah and Rebbi Yehudah ben Beseira)?\n(b) What did Rebbi ...\n1. ... Ila'i say about the Mitzvah of Reishis ga'Gez?\n2. ... Yashiyah say about the Isur of Kil'ayim?\n(c) What did Rebbi Yehudah ben Beseira say?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q8",
        "label": "8)",
        "text": "(a) There are two versions of what Ze'iri said when he came from Eretz Yisrael. According to the Lashon, he said 'Batluhah li'Tevilusa'.   With which Tana does this conform?\n(b) According to the second Lashon, he said 'Batluhah li'Netilusa'.   What did he mean by this?\n(c) What did Rav Chisda say about that?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q9",
        "label": "9)",
        "text": "(a) What did Nachum Ish Bamzu whisper to Rebbi Akiva, and Rebbi Akiva to ben Azai in connection with a Ba'al Keri?\n(b) What did ben Azai then do?\n(c) Rebbi Yossi bar Avin and Rebbi Yossi bar Z'vida argue over the current episode.   Where did they live?\n(d) One of them cited it as it stands.   What did the other one say to amend it?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q10",
        "label": "10)",
        "text": "(a) The latter opinion learned 'Shan'ah' for two reasons.   One of them is Bitul Beis-ha'Medrash.   What is the other one?\n(b) What is the reason behind the other version?\n(c) Rebbi Yanai heard that some people are lenient about Tevilas Ba'alei Keryan and others are strict.   What did he comment about the latter?\n(d) Seeing as Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi forbids a Ba'al Keri to study Torah, how do we explain the fact that he queried the need for his having to Tovel?\n(e) Rebbi Chanina maintains that the Tevilah of Ba'alei Keryan is a great achievement, and he cites a Beraisa to support his statement.   What happened once when a man accosted a woman that proves the wisdom of the Takanah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q11",
        "label": "11)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rav Huna suggest to the Rabbanan to do if their laxness in Tevilas Keri was due to the cold?\n(b) When Rav Chisda queried the leniency of Toveling in hot water, Rav Huna quoted Rav Ada bar Ahavah.   What did Rav Ada bar Ahavah say?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q12",
        "label": "12)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rebbi Zeira instruct his servant to do when he was once sitting in a bathtub?\n(b) What did he respond when Rebbi Chiya bar Aba asked him why this was necessary, since he was already sitting in nine Kabin of water?\n(c) What did Rav Nachman establish to facilitate the Takanah of nine Kabin?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q13",
        "label": "13)",
        "text": "(a) When Rav Dimi arrived from Eretz Yisrael, how did he strictly limit the Din of nine Kabin quoting Rebbi Akiva and Rebbi Yehudah G'lutera?\n(b) What did he say about a Choleh ha'Margil (What does 'ha'Margil' mean)?\n(c) What did this prompt Rav Yosef to say about Rav Nachman's barrel?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q14",
        "label": "14)",
        "text": "(a) When Ravin arrived from Eretz Yisrael, he cited an incident that took place in Usha.   In which area of Rav Oshaya's house did they ask Rav Asi about Tish'ah Kabin (Note, is seems that it ought to be Rebbi Oshaya and Rebbi Asi)?\n(b) What did he say about a Choleh le'Onso?\n(c) To what did he then confine the Takanah of Tish'ah Kabin?\n(d) What did this prompt Rav Yosef to comment about Rav Nachman's barrel?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q15",
        "label": "15)",
        "text": "(a) Who initiated the Tevilah of a Ba'al Keri?\n(b) What problem do we therefore have with the Machlokes between Rav Dimi and Ravin?\n(c) To explain the Machlokes, we initially explain that Ezra instituted two Takanos by a Bari (a healthy person).   Which two Takanos?\n(d) And Rav Dimi and Ravin argue over what he said by a Choleh.   What does ...\n1. ... Rav Dimi say?\n2. ... Ravin say?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q16",
        "label": "16)",
        "text": "(a) Rava queries this answer however, based on a statement by Mar.   What did Mar say about Takanas Ezra that refutes the previous explanation?\n(b) How does Rava therefore amend the answer? What did Ezra actually institute?\n(c) Who instituted the Nesinah of nine Kabin?\n(d) What is then the Machlokes between Rav Dimi and Ravin?\n(e) Rava finally rules that Bari ha'Margil requires forty Sa'ah.   What does he say about ...\n1. ... Bari le'Onso and Choleh ha'Margil?\n2. ... Choleh le'Onso?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q17",
        "label": "17)",
        "text": "(a) What distinction does the Tana Kama in a Beraisa draw between learning Torah and teaching Torah regarding Tish'ah Kabin?\n(b) What does Rebbi Yehudah say?\n(c) What is the significance of the two pairs of Talmidei-Chachamim, Rebbi Yochanan and Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi and Rebbi Elazar and Rebbi Yossi b'Rebbi Chanina?\n(d) One of the former comments that the Tana Kama only requires forty Sa'ah for teaching by a Choleh ha'Margil, but by a Choleh le'Onso, nine Kabin will suffice.   What does the other one say?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q18",
        "label": "18)",
        "text": "(a) What does one of the latter comment with regard to Rebbi Yehudah's statement? What does he mean when he restricts Tevilah in forty Sa'ah to 'be'Karka'?\n(b) What does the other one say?\n(c) According to the first of the latter opinions, what does Rebbi Yehudah then come to include when he adds 'mi'Kol Makom'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q19",
        "label": "19)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rav Papa, Rav Huna b'rei de'Rav Yehoshua and Rava bar Shmuel once do together?\n(b) Why did Rav Papa think that he ought to Bench Mezuman?\n(c) On what grounds did Rava bar Shmuel object?\n(d) Why did he therefore claim the right to Bench Mezuman?\n(e) Rav Huna b'rei de'Rav Yehoshua won the day.  What did he say?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q20",
        "label": "20)",
        "text": "(a) Why did Rav Chama used to Tovel in forty Sa'ah on Erev Pesach?\n(b) What are the two possible reasons that the Halachah is not like him?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q21",
        "label": "21)",
        "text": "(a) What does the Mishnah say one should do if, in the middle of the Amidah, a person remembers that he is a Ba'al Keri?\n(b) In a case where he is on his way down to Tovel just before Haneitz ha'Chamah, on what condition should he Tovel ad complete the process before reciting the Sh'ma?\n(c) What if he is unable to do that?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q22",
        "label": "22)",
        "text": "(a) What does the Tana forbid him to cover himself with besides 'Mei ha'Mishreh? What is 'Mei ha'Mishreh'?\n(b) On what condition does he appear to permit covering oneself with them?\n(c) How far must one distance oneself from them (assuming one did not add water)?\n(d) What else does the Mishnah incorporate in this ruling?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q23",
        "label": "23)",
        "text": "(a) The Beraisa reiterates the Mishnah's ruling concerning a Ba'al Keri who remembers that he is Tamei whilst Davening the Amidah. What does the Tana Kama say if a Ba'al Keri remembers ... whilst he is Leining in the Torah?\n(b) Rebbi Meir disagrees. What does he say?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q24",
        "label": "24)",
        "text": "(a) What does another Beraisa say about a case where, in the middle of the Amidah, someone notices Tzo'ah in front of him?\n(b) How do we reconcile this with yet another Beraisa, which rules that it will suffice if he moves to the side?\n(c) What is an example of 'Lo Efshar'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q25",
        "label": "25)",
        "text": "(a) What objection did Rava raise when Rabah ruled that someone who Davens the Amidah and discovers Tzo'ah in its place (on his body) is Yotzei?\n(b) Which Pasuk in Mishlei did he quote as his source?\n(c) What did he therefore rule?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q26",
        "label": "26)",
        "text": "(a) What does the Beraisa say one should do if, whilst Davening the Amidah, urine begins to drip down one's legs?\n(b) Rav Chisda and Rav Hamnuna argue over what he does when he resumes Davening.   One says that he repeat the Tefilah from the beginning.   What dos the other one say?\n(c) Based on the assumption that he waited the amount of time it takes to recite the entire Amidah, how do we initially interpret their Machlokes?\n(d) On what grounds does Rav Ashi refute this explanation? What ought the Tana to have then said?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q27",
        "label": "27)",
        "text": "(a) What must both opinions therefore hold in a case where the person waited the amount of time it takes to recite the entire Amidah?\n(b) Since they therefore argue over where he did not wait so long, how does Rav Ashi then explain the basis of their Machlokes?"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "daf": 23,
    "questions": [
      {
        "id": "q1",
        "label": "1)",
        "text": "(a) What does the Beraisa say about someone who Davens when he needs to relieve himself (for Gedolim)?\n(b) According to Rav Z'vid (or Rav Yehudah), on what condition does this not apply?\n(c) How does Rav Sheishes explain this? For how long must one be able to restrain oneself?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q2",
        "label": "2)",
        "text": "(a) In what form do others cite Rav Z'vid's condition?\n(b) What did Rav Z'vid subsequently say?\n(c) What does Rebbi Shmuel bar Nachmeni Amar Rebbi Yonasan learn from the Pasuk in Amos \"Hikon Lik'ras Elokecha Yisrael\"?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q3",
        "label": "3)",
        "text": "(a) How does Rebbi Shmuel bar Nachmeni Amar Rebbi Yonasan explain the Pasuk in Koheles \"Sh'mor Ragl'cha ka'asher Teilech el Beis ha'Elokim\"? Against what should one guard oneself?\n(b) Why should one then need to go the House of Hash-m?\n(c) How does Rava explain the continuation of the Pasuk \"ve'Karov Lish'mo'a? To whom should one listen?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q4",
        "label": "4)",
        "text": "(a) How do we initially explain the continuation of the Pasuk \"mi'Teis ha'Kesilim Zevach\"?\n(b) What problem do we have with that, based on the conclusion \"ki Einam Yod'im La'asos Ra\"?\n(c) How do we therefore reinterpret the previous phrase? What is wrong with the Korbanos brought by the fools?\n(d) So what does Hash-m say about them?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q5",
        "label": "5)",
        "text": "(a) How does Rav Papa (or his son, Rav Chanina) explain the above Pasuk \"Sh'mor Ragl'cha ka'asher Teilech el Beis ha'Elokim\" in connection with someone who is Davening the Amidah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q6",
        "label": "6)",
        "text": "(a) What does the Beraisa say about someone who is wearing Tefilin who enters a bathroom (in the fields)?\n(b) Rav Acha bar Rav Huna citing Rav Sheishes establishes this by a Beis ha'Kisei Kavu'a.   What is a Beis ha'Kisei Kavu'a'?\n(c) What does he do with them after having taken them off?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q7",
        "label": "7)",
        "text": "(a) What if it is a Beis ha'Kisei Arai (that is being used for the first time)?\n(b) What must he do upon leaving the bathroom?\n(c) Why is this necessary even if it is a Beis ha'Kisei Arai?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q8",
        "label": "8)",
        "text": "(a) What She'eilah do we now ask with regard to entering a Beis ha'Kisei in  order to urinate?\n(b) Ravina permits it.   What does Rav Ada bar Masna say?\n(c) With whom did Rava concur when they asked him for his opinion?\n(d) Some say that it is because he may need to make Gedolim.   What reason do others give for the prohibition?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q9",
        "label": "9)",
        "text": "(a) In another Beraisa which discusses the same case as the previous one, Beis Shamai requires the person entering the Beis ha'Kisei to place his Tefilin on the windowsill of the Beis ha'Kisei.   What do Beis Hillel say?\n(b) What objection do we raise to Rebbi Akiva, who maintains that one should enter the Beis ha'Kisei holding the Tefilin in one's garment?\n(c) How do we therefore amend his statement?\n(d) According to him, once inside the Beis ha'Kisei, he places his Tefilin on one of the holes on the inside of the wall.   Why not on the window sill on the outside?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q10",
        "label": "10)",
        "text": "(a) The previous ruling of Rebbi Akiva followed an incident that took place at that time, when a Talmid-placed his Tefilin on the window-sill.   Who subsequently took them?\n(b) What did she then do?\n(c) How did the Talmid react?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q11",
        "label": "11)",
        "text": "(a) Another Beraisa informs us that initially they would place their Tefilin in the holes of the walls behind which they relieved themselves.   Why did they switch over to placing them in the windows of walls next to the roads, before proceeding into the field?\n(b) What did they finally do, when people in the street began taking them?\n(c) What did Rebbi Meyasha the grandson of Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi say one should do with one's Tefilin whilst relieving oneself?\n(d) What does Rav Yosef bar Minyumi Amar Rav Nachman add about the strap?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q12",
        "label": "12)",
        "text": "(a) According to Ya'akov bar Acha Amar Rebbi Zeira, all this applies only if there is time to don the Tefilin before nightfall.   What does he do if there is not?\n(b) Why must the bag be at least the size of a Tefach?\n(c) Rabah bar bar Chanah Amar Rebbi Yochanan makes a similar statement.   What does he say someone should do with his Tefilin if he is relieving himself ...\n1. ... in the day in the field?\n2. ... in the night in his house?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q13",
        "label": "13)",
        "text": "(a) Abaye qualifies the Tefach bag of Rebbi Ya'akov bar Acha to a Tefilin-bag.   What does he say about a bag that was not initially made to hold Tefilin?\n(b) Why is that?\n(c) How does Mar Zutra (or Rav Ashi) prove this from the Din of little sealed  earthenware vessels that are in the same room as a Meis?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q14",
        "label": "14)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rabah bar bar Chanah testify about Rebbi Yochanan.   What distinction did he draw between Sifrei Agadta and Tefilin when he would go to the Beis ha'Kisei?\n(b) Why did he do that?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q15",
        "label": "15)",
        "text": "(a) What does the Beraisa say about holding Tefilin in one's hands or a Seifer-Torah in one's arms whilst one is ...\n1. ... Davening?\n2. ... urinating?\n3. ... sleeping?\n(b) What about a short nap?\n(c) What is the reason for the latter?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q16",
        "label": "16)",
        "text": "(a) With regard to which of the above does Shmuel add a knife, money and a dish?\n(b) Which fourth item does he include in the list?\n(c) What is the reason for prohibition?\n(d) What is the problem with the above ruling with regard to urinating?\n(e) Like whom does Rava Amar Rav Sheishes therefore establish the Beraisa?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q17",
        "label": "17)",
        "text": "(a) We query Rava however from the Beraisa itself, which continues 'The things that I permitted you here I forbade you there', which we assume, is still talking about Tefilin.   How do we interpret 'here' and 'there'?\n(b) On what grounds do we think that this must go according to Beis Hillel and not Beis Shamai?\n(c) We answer that it refers (not to Tefilin, but) to Tefach Tefachayim.   What does this mean?\n(d) To explain 'here' and 'there', we now cite two B'raisos, both of which permit revealing one Tefach at the back.  What do the two respective opinions say about the front?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q18",
        "label": "18)",
        "text": "(a) What is the problem with establishing the Beraisa which permits two Tefachim in front by Ketanim, and the Beraisa which forbids it by Gedolim?\n(b) So we conclude that both Beraisos are speaking by Gedolim.   How do we then reconcile them? To whom is the Beraisa which ...\n1. ... permits two Tefachim at the front referring? Why is that?\n2. ... forbids anything in the front?\n(c) How do we now explain the Beraisa 'The things that I permitted you here I forbade you there'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q19",
        "label": "19)",
        "text": "(a) We refute this answer too however, by citing the conclusion of the Beraisa 'This is a Kal va'Chomer which has no answer!'.   What does this mean?\n(b) How does it pose a Kashya on the current explanation?\n(c) So what is the conclusion regarding ...\n1. ... the Beraisa's context? What is the Beraisa talking about?\n2. ... Rava Amar Rav Sheishes's interpretation of the Beraisa (that distinguishes between men and women regarding Gedolim)?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q20",
        "label": "20)",
        "text": "(a) The question remains however, if one is permitted to enter a Beis ha'Kisei Kavu'a (for Gedolim) with Tefilin, how much more so, a Beis ha'Kisei Arai (for Ketanim)? How do we answer the Kashya?\n(b) How does that explain the prohibition of urinating with Tefilin in one's hand?\n(c) Then what does the Tana mean when it says 'Zehu Kal va'Chomer she'Ein alav Teshuvah'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q21",
        "label": "21)",
        "text": "(a) The Beraisa instructs a person who is about to a eat a fixed meal to first walk ten times four Amos.   Why is that?\n(b) What alternative instructions does the Tana issue?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q22",
        "label": "22)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rebbi Yitzchak require a person who is about to a eat a full meal to do with his Tefilin?\n(b) Rebbi Chiya disagrees.   What does he say one should do with one's Tefilin when eating a fixed meal?\n(c) What does he mean when he concludes that this is the right thing to do ('ve'Chein Hadur lo')?\n(d) We ask up to when should he remain without Tefilin, according to Rebbi Chiya.   What does Rav Nachman bar Yitzchak answer?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q23",
        "label": "23)",
        "text": "(a) One Beraisa permits wrapping one's Tefilin together with one's money be'Afr'kuseih.   What does 'be'Afr'kuseih' mean?\n(b) How do we reconcile this with another Beraisa, which forbids it?\n(c) This answer is based on a ruling of Rav Chisda.   What did Rav Chisda say about someone who ...\n1. ... designated a Tefilin-bag for Tefilin and subsequently placed them inside it?\n2. ... designated a Tefilin-bag for Tefilin but did not yet place them inside it?\n3. ... placed Tefilin inside it without actually designating it for Tefilin?\n(d) What is the source for the latter ruling?\n(e) With which of the above cases does Abaye, who holds 'Hazmanah Milsa hi' disagree?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q24",
        "label": "24)",
        "text": "(a) What She'eilah did Rav Yosef b'rei de'Rav Nechunyah ask Rav Yehudah about placing one's Tefilin when going to bed?\n(b) Why did he not ask about placing them under his feet?\n(c) What did Rav Yehudah citing Shmuel reply?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q25",
        "label": "25)",
        "text": "(a) We query Shmuel from a Beraisa, which forbids placing one's Tefilin underneath one's feet.   On what condition does the Tana permit placing them underneath one's cushion?\n(b) On what condition does he permit placing them close to one's cushion?\n(c) What did Rav Yehudah say about the Kashya from the Beraisa?\n(d) What ruling does Rava issue, despite the Tiyuvta on Shmuel?\n(e) Why is that?"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "daf": 24,
    "questions": [
      {
        "id": "q1",
        "label": "1)",
        "text": "(a) According to Rebbi Yirmiyah, who comments on Rava's previous ruling, where exactly does one put one's Tefilin when going to bed with his wife?\n(b) How do we reconcile this with the Beraisa cited by Rebbi Chiya that one puts them inside a Kova underneath one's cushion? What is a 'Kova'?\n(c) With what did bar Kapara wrap them before making sure that part of the Tefilin protruded from the cushion?\n(d) Rav Shisha b'rei de'Rav Idi would place the Tefilin on a bench before going to bed with his wife.   What did he cover them with?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q2",
        "label": "2)",
        "text": "(a) When Rava once asked Rav Hamnuna b'rei de'Rav Yosef to fetch his Tefilin, where did he find them?\n(b) What did the latter infer from that?\n(c) Why did Rava ask him to fetch his Tefilin in the first place?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q3",
        "label": "3)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rav Yosef b'rei de'Rav Nechunya ask Rev Yehudah about regard to two people who are sleeping in the same bed with regard to reciting the Sh'ma?\n(b) Why did he confine his She'eilah to where they turn round back to back?\n(c) Rav Yehudah answered with a statement of Shmuel.   What did Shmuel say?\n(d) Rav Yosef queried the word 'even'.   What is the problem with it?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q4",
        "label": "4)",
        "text": "(a) We query Shmuel from two Beraisos which refer to the She'eilah under discussion, one of which Beraisa permits two people in the same bed to recite the Sh'ma provided they turn round.   What does the other Beraisa say about a man who is lying together with his children and family in the same bed?\n(b) What if they are Ketanim?\n(c) What is now the Kashya on Shmuel?\n(d) Why is there no problem according to Rav Yosef?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q5",
        "label": "5)",
        "text": "(a) What will Shmuel retort, (based on the fact that 'family' includes one's wife?\n(b) How do we therefore resolve the contradiction ...\n1. ... according to Rav Yosef?\n2. ... according to Shmuel?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q6",
        "label": "6)",
        "text": "(a) We cited the Beraisa which permits reciting the Sh'ma provided one turns round.  Why is the fact that their buttocks are touching not a problem?\n(b) What did Rav Huna say about that?\n(c) What does the Mishnah in Chalah say about an unclad woman separating Chalah?\n(d) What does the Mishnah say about an unclad man?\n(e) Bearing in mind that her buttocks are exposed, how does Rav Nachman bar Yitzchak refute the proof from there for Rav Nachman (that buttocks are not subject to Ervah)?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q7",
        "label": "7)",
        "text": "(a) ) We seated earlier the Beraisa which permits a man to recite the Sh'ma in bed without a dividing garment as long as his children are small.    If, according to the first Lashon, Rav Chisda defines a Ketanah (Tinokes) as one who is three years old.   How does he define a Katan?\n(b) In the second Lashon, he defines the former as one who is eleven.   How does he define the latter?\n(c) What is the significance of these ages?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q8",
        "label": "8)",
        "text": "(a) In the previous Sugya we Paskened like Shmuel (regarding Tefilin) in spite of the Tiyuvta on him.   What did Rav Kahana ask Rav Ashi in connection with Shmuel's ruling permitting turning round and reciting the Sh'ma when his wife is with him?\n(b) What did Rav Ashi reply?\n(c) What did Rav Mari ask Rav Papa about a bit of pubic hair that is showing through a hole in one's clothes?\n(d) What did Rav Papa mean when he replied 'Sa'ar Sa'ar!'"
      },
      {
        "id": "q9",
        "label": "9)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rebbi Yitzchak say about 'Tefach be'Ishah'?\n(b) We refute the suggestion that this refers to the area of a woman that one is forbidden to look at from a statement of Rav Sheishes, with reference to the inner ornaments that the soldiers brought back as booty together with the outer ornaments, following the war against Midyan.   Why did they donate them to Hekdesh?\n(c) What are ...\n1. ... the inner ornaments?\n2. ... the outer ornaments?\n(d) According to Rav Sheishes, why does the Torah mention the former together with the latter?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q10",
        "label": "10)",
        "text": "(a) What did we prove from Rav Sheishes' statement?\n(b) In what connection did Rebbi Yitzchak then state 'Tefach be'Ishah Ervah'?\n(c) Based on Pesukim in Yeshayah, what does Rav Chisda say about the calf of a woman?\n(d) And based on the Pasuk in Shir ha'Shirim ...\n1. ... \"Ki Kolech Areiv u'Mar'ech Navah\", what does Shmuel say about a woman's hair?\n2. ... \"Sa'arech ke'Eider ha'Recheilim\", what does Rav Chisda say about her hair?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q11",
        "label": "11)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rebbi Chanina see Rebbi do with his Tefilin?\n(b) We query that from a Beraisa however.  What does the Tana say about someone who hangs up his Tefilin?\n(c) How do the Dorshei Chamuros or Reshumos) say about the Pasuk \"Vehayu Chayecha Teluyin l'cha mi'Neged\"?\n(d) What does 'Dorshei Chamuros' mean?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q12",
        "label": "12)",
        "text": "(a) What is the Gemara's first answer regarding the Kashya on Rebbi (that differentiates between the Tefilin and the strap)?\n(b) According to the second answer, both of the above are forbidden.   Then how do we explain what Rebbi did?\n(c) Then why did Rebbi Chanina see fit to mention it? What would we otherwise have thought?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q13",
        "label": "13)",
        "text": "(a) Rebbi Chanina saw Rebbi burp, yawn, sneeze (Nis'atesh), spit 'u'Memashmesh be'Vigdo' whilst Davening the Amidah.   What does 'Memashmesh be'Vigdo' mean?\n(b) What would he do whenever he yawned?\n(c) What would he not do during the Amidah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q14",
        "label": "14)",
        "text": "(a) We query Rebbi on a number of points from a Beraisa.   How does the Tana describe someone who Davens the Amidah ...\n1. ... loudly enough for others to hear him?\n2. ... in a loud voice?\n(b) What is the source for the latter statement?\n(c) How does the Beraisa describe someone who during the Amidah ...\n1. ... burps or yawns?\n2. ... sneezes (Mis'atesh)?\n3. ... spits?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q15",
        "label": "15)",
        "text": "(a) How do we reconcile Rebbi's ...\n1. ... burping and yawning during the Amidah, with the Beraisa, which describes someone who does this as conceited?\n2. ... sneezing (Nis'atesh) during the Amidah with the Beraisa which describes someone who does that as disgusting?\n(b) What did Rebbi Zeira learn from bei Rav Hamnuna?\n(c) How is it a Siman that it is 'a good sign'?\n(d) What did he add to that, regarding the importance of this piece of information?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q16",
        "label": "16)",
        "text": "(a) The one remaining Kashya on Rebbi is the Beraisa's statement regarding spitting, which we reconcile Rebbi, who spat during the Amidah, with the Beraisa, which forbids it, by citing Rav Yehudah.   What did Rav Yehudah say one should do if spittle gathers in his mouth?\n(b) What if he is wearing a nice Talis?\n(c) What did Rav Ashi do when he had excess spittle in his mouth?\n(d) What did he reply when Ravina asked him why he did not follow the advice of Rav Yehudah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q17",
        "label": "17)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rav Huna say about someone who cannot concentrate when he Davens quietly?\n(b) On what condition is this not permitted?\n(c) Why is that?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q18",
        "label": "18)",
        "text": "(a) Why did Rebbi Aba avoid Rav Yehudah after having decided to leave Bavel for Eretz Yisrael?\n(b) What did Rav Yehudah say, based on the Pasuk Yirmiyahu \"Bavelah Yavo'u ve'Sham Yih'yu ad Yom Pakdi osam ... \"?\n(c) What did Rebbi Aba nevertheless decide to do before leaving?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q19",
        "label": "19)",
        "text": "(a) What does the Beraisa cited by the Beraisa-expert in front of Rav Yehudah say about someone who ...\n1. ... makes a smell whilst Davening the Amidah, according to the first Lashon?\n2. ... needs to make a smell, according to the second Lashon?\n(b) What is the gist of the comment that Rav Yehudah introduced after hearing the Beraisa?\n(c) When does one say it?\n(d) Why is it not considered a Hefsek in the middle of the Amidah?\n(e) What did Rebbi Aba comment when he heard that?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q20",
        "label": "20)",
        "text": "(a) The Beraisa discusses someone is lying in bed naked on a cold night who wants to say the Sh'ma but it is too cold to stick his head out of the covers.   What must he do to avoid reciting the Sh'ma in the same domain as his Ervah?\n(b) Why is the Tana not concerned about the prohibition of 'Libo Ro'eh es ha'Ervah'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q21",
        "label": "21)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rav Huna quoting Rebbi Yochanan permit someone who is walking in unclean alleyways to do should he want to recite the Sh'ma?\n(b) What did Rav Chisda say about that?\n(c) According to others, It was Rabah bar bar Chana who issued the statement.   Whom did he quote?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q22",
        "label": "22)",
        "text": "(a) We query Rav Huna (in the first Lashon) from another statement of his, where he forbids a Talmid-Chacham to stand in an unclean place.   Why is that?\n(b) How do we reconcile the two statements of Rav Huna?\n(c) We now query Rebbi Yochanan himself from a statement that Rabah bar bar Chanah made in his name.   In which kind of location exclusively did he forbid a person to even think of Divrei Torah?\n(d) What is now the problem?\n(e) What do we initially suggest to reconcile the two statements?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q23",
        "label": "23)",
        "text": "(a) We try to refute the previous suggestion however, based on an episode that occurred when Rebbi Avahu was walking behind Rebbi Yochanan reciting the Sh'ma.   What did he do when they arrived at an unclean alleyway?\n(b) What did Rebbi Yochanan reply, when Rebbi Avahu asked him from where he should resume the Sh'ma after they left the that area?\n(c) What is now the Kashya on Rebbi Yochanan?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q24",
        "label": "24)",
        "text": "(a) How do we answer the Kashya? What does Rebbi Yochanan really hold?\n(b) What did he then tell Rebbi Avahu?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q25",
        "label": "25)",
        "text": "(a) Whose opinion is supported by the Beraisa which ...\n1. ... permits placing one's hand over one's mouth and reciting the Sh'ma whilst walking through unclean alleyways?\n2. ... forbids it?\n(b) What does the latter Beraisa add with regard to someone who enters an unclean alleyway reciting the Sh'ma?\n(c) In what connection does Rebbi Meyashe the grandson of Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi quote the Pasuk in Yechezkel \"ve'Gam Ani Nasati lahem Chukim Lo Tovim u'Mishpatim Lo Yichyu bahem'?\n(d) Rebbi Asi quotes a Pasuk in Mishlei regarding the same issue.   Which Pasuk in Sh'lach l'cha does Rav Ada bar Ahavah quote?\n(e) Based on a Pasuk in Vayeilech quoted by Rebbi Avahu, what reward will someone receive if he does stop reciting the Sh'ma when entering an unclean alleyway?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q26",
        "label": "26)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rav Huna say about someone who is only covered from the waist down reciting the Sh'ma?\n(b) What does the Beraisa that supports his opinion say about someone who is wearing a garment of cloth, leather or sackcloth on his loins?\n(c) When does the Tana say one must cover one's heart too, before proceeding?"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "daf": 25,
    "questions": [
      {
        "id": "q1",
        "label": "1)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rav Huna say about someone who inadvertently enters a bathroom still wearing his Tefilin?\n(b) What problem do we have with that?\n(c) How does Rav Nachman bar Yitzchak therefore amend Rav Huna's initial statement?\n(d) How do we query that ruling too?\n(e) And we answer with a Beraisa quoting Raban Shimon ben Gamliel.   What does Raban Shimon ben Gamliel say about ...\n1. ... an 'Amud' that one draws back into the body?\n2. ... urine that one draws back into the body?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q2",
        "label": "2)",
        "text": "(a) Rav Huna and Rav Chisda argue over whether someone is permitted the Sh'ma in two cases. One of them, if there is excrement on his body.  What is the other?\n(b) How does Rav Huna derive his opinion from the Pasuk in Tehilim \"Kol ha'Neshamah Tehalel Kah ... \"?\n(c) From which Pasuk there does Rav Chisda derive his opinion?\n(d) How does he learn it from there?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q3",
        "label": "3)",
        "text": "(a) According to Rav Huna, one needs to distance oneself four Amos from the smell of a substance before reciting the Sh'ma.   On what condition is it then permitted?\n(b) What does Rav Chisda say?\n(c) What does the Beraisa say about reciting the Sh'ma in front of the excrement of humans, dogs, pigs or chickens?\n(d) The Tana also forbids reciting the Sh'ma in front of a trash-heap.   What is the difference between the latter and the former?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q4",
        "label": "4)",
        "text": "(a) On what condition is one permitted to recite the Sh'ma even whilst sitting beside them?\n(b) What does the Beraisa conclude one must do, if there is no such Mechitzah?\n(c) And what does the Tana say about the Amidah?\n(d) What does he conclude regarding a smell with a substance that supports Rav Chisda?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q5",
        "label": "5)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rava say about the first rulings of the previous Beraisa?\n(b) How can he simply reject the rulings of a Beraisa?\n(c) What does the Tana in the second Beraisa say about reciting the Sh'ma whilst facing the excrement of pigs and dogs (some erase 'pigs' from the Beraisa)? On what condition is it forbidden?\n(d) Why does this distinction not pertain to the excrement of humans, which the Tana mentioned before that of pigs and dogs?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q6",
        "label": "6)",
        "text": "(a) They asked Rav Sheishes about a smell without a substance.   What is a 'smell without a substance'?\n(b) In answer to the She'eilah, he pointed to the Tzipi de'bei Rav. What are 'Tzipi de'bei Rav'?\n(c) What did he prove from there?\n(d) What is one not permitted to do in the presence of such a smell?\n(e) On what condition may one not even learn Torah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q7",
        "label": "7)",
        "text": "(a) Abaye permits reciting the Sh'ma in front of passing Tzo'ah (someone who is carrying a potty).   What does Rava say?\n(b) Abaye bases his opinion in a Mishnah in Nega'im.   What does the Mishnah there say about a case where ...\n1. ... a Metzora is standing under a tree when a Tahor person walks past?\n2. ... the Tahor person is standing under the tree and the Metzora walks past?\n(c) Why can these rulings not possibly be referring to a Tamei Meis?\n(d) What does the Tana say there about a stone from a house that has been stricken with Tzara'as?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q8",
        "label": "8)",
        "text": "(a) Rava rejects Abaye's proof from Metzora.   What does he learn from the Pasuk in Metzora \"Badad Yeishev, mi'Chutz la'Machaneh Moshavo\"?\n(b) Based on the Pasuk in Ki Seitzei \"Vahayah Machanecha Kadosh\", what is the criteria by Keri'as Sh'ma'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q9",
        "label": "9)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rav Papa say about the mouth of a Chazir?\n(b) Why do we ask 'P'shita'?\n(c) What do we answer?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q10",
        "label": "10)",
        "text": "(a) According to the first Lashon, what distinction does Rav Yehudah draw between reciting the Sh'ma where there is Safek Tzo'ah and where there is Safek Mei Raglayim?\n(b) According to the second Lashon, what distinction does he draw between Safek Tzo'ah in the house and safek Tzo'ah in an Ashpah?\n(c) What does he say there about Safek Mei Raglayim?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q11",
        "label": "11)",
        "text": "(a) Rav Yehudah's lenient ruling by Safek Mei Raglayim is based on rulings by Rav Hamnuna and Rebbi Yonasan.   What did Rav Hamnuna say about Mei Raglayim? When is it Asur min ha'Torah to recite the Sh'ma in front of it?\n(b) What problem did Rebbi Yonasan have with the two consecutive Pesukim in Ki Seitzei, both of which deal with leaving the camp to relieve oneself?\n(c) How does he reconcile them?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q12",
        "label": "12)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rav Yehudah now extrapolate from the fact that, on the one hand, one needs to leave the camp for Mei Raglayim, whilst on the other, one is not obligated to cover it?\n(b) How does that explain his distinction between Safek Tzo'ah and Safek Mei Raglayim?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q13",
        "label": "13)",
        "text": "(a) In reply to the Gemara's She'ielah how long after the urine reaches the ground is one still forbidden to recite the Sh'ma when facing it, Rav Yehudah Amar Shmuel replied 'Kol Z'man she'Matfichin'.   What did he mean by that?\n(b) What did Rabah bar bar Chanah and Ula say about it?\n(c) G'niva Amar Rav was more stringent.   What does he say?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q14",
        "label": "14)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rav Yosef comment when he heard G'niva's ruling?\n(b) He based his statement on a statement of Rav Yehudah.   What did Rav Yehudah Amar Rav say about reciting the Sh'ma when facing Tzo'ah?\n(c) However, Abaye refuted Rav Yosef's Kal va'Chomer from Tzo'ah in that G'niva may well hold like Rabah bar Rav Huna.   What did Rabah bar Rav Huna Amar Rav give with regard to reciting the Sh'ma facing Tzo'ah.\n(d) Rabah bar bar Chanah defines that as Tzo'ah that does not break up when one throws it. Others are even more stringent. What do they say?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q15",
        "label": "15)",
        "text": "(a) Ravina related how, when Rav Yehudah mi'Difti once spotted Tzo'ah, he asked him to ascertain whether its surface had crusted (like Rav Yehudah Amar Rav).   How do others quote Rav Yehudah mi'Difti?\n(b) In conclusion, some forbid Tzo'ah that is as hard as clay; Ravina permits it.   How does Rava finally rule with regard to ...\n1. ... Tzo'ah?\n2. ... Mei Raglayim?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q16",
        "label": "16)",
        "text": "(a) We query Rava from a Beraisa which initially substantiates Rava's statement, but which adds that Mei Raglayim is permitted if it has become absorbed or has dried.   Based on 'dried', how do we interpret 'absorbed' that poses a Kashya on Rava?\n(b) How do we counter this interpretation, based on the Reisha of the Beraisa?\n(c) What do therefore conclude?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q17",
        "label": "17)",
        "text": "(a) We suggest that Rava's ruling is a Machlokes Tana'im in a Beraisa.   What does the Tana there say about reciting the Sh'ma facing a potty whose contents of Mei Raglayim have been emptied?\n(b) The Tana Kama goes on to permit reciting the Sh'ma facing the Mei Raglayim itself, provided it has been absorbed.   What does Rebbi Yossi say?\n(c) On what grounds do we reject the suggestion that 'absorbed' means that it does not wet whoever touches it ('Kol Z'man she'Matfichin')?\n(d) How do we therefore try to interpret it?\n(e) Like whom will Rava then hold?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q18",
        "label": "18)",
        "text": "(a) We refute this suggestion too, however, by establishing that even the Tana Kama forbids 'Kol Z'man she'Matfichin' and permits 'Rishuman Nikar' (like Rava).   What is then the basis of the Machlokes between the Tana and Rebbi Yossi?\n(b) Which Tana holds which opinon?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q19",
        "label": "19)",
        "text": "(a) We suggest that the author of our Mishnah that requires someone who is able to Tovel, cover himself and read the Sh'ma before sunrise to do so holds like Rebbi Eliezer.   What does Rebbi Eliezer say?\n(b) What are the ramifications of the suggestion?\n(c) We counter that the Mishnah might well go like Rebbi Yehoshua.   What does he say?\n(d) Then why does the Mishnah give the time period as Hanetz ha'Chamah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q20",
        "label": "20)",
        "text": "(a) What problem does reciting the Sh'ma whilst standing in a river present?\n(b) From which Pasuk in in Ki Seitzei do we learn the prohibition of 'Libo Ro'eh es ha'Ervah' with regard to learning Torah?\n(c) How does Rebbi Elazar (or Rebbi Acha bar Aba Acha in the name of Rav) solve the problem?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q21",
        "label": "21)",
        "text": "(a) The Tana Kama in a Beraisa requires a person who is standing in clear water to sit up to his neck and recite the Sh'ma.   What do Yesh Omrim say?\n(b) What does the Tana Kama do about ...\n1. ... 'Libo Ro'eh es ha'Ervah'?\n2. ... 'Akeivo Ro'eh es ha'Ervah'?\n(c) What is the basis of the Makshan's second question? What does he learn from the Pasuk - \"ve'Lo Yir'eh b'cha Ervas Davar\"?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q22",
        "label": "22)",
        "text": "(a) Abaye holds that if one's heel is touching one's Ervah, one may not recite the Sh'ma.   What does Rava say?\n(b) According to Rav Z'vid, both Abaye and Rava agree that it is forbidden.   Aver what are they then arguing?\n(c) What reason does Rava give for permitting it?\n(d) What does the Gemara finally rule regarding the heel?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q23",
        "label": "23)",
        "text": "(a) What distinction do we draw between Tzo'ah and Ervah that are visible through glass ?\n(b) What is the reason for the distinction? Why is ...\n1. ... the former permitted?\n2. ... the latter forbidden?\n(c) How does ...\n1. ... Abaye suggest nullifying a Kolshehu of Tzo'ah?\n2. ... Rava qualify Abaye's ruling?\n(d) What does Rava suggest one does to allow reading the Sh'ma in the presence of Tzo'ah in a small pit?\n(e) Mar b'reih de'Ravina asked whether one may recite the Sh'ma if there is Yzo'ah on the sole of one's shoe.   What is the outcome of the She'eilah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q24",
        "label": "24)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rav Yehudah say about reciting the Sh'ma in front of a naked Nochri?\n(b) What problem do we have with that?\n(c) We answer by citing the Pasuk in Yechezkel (in connection with Nochrim) \" ... asher Basar Chamorim Besaram\".   Why might we have therefore thought that a Nochri is different?\n(d) From which Pasuk in No'ach do we learn that the Ervah of a Nochri is in fact, considered Ervah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q25",
        "label": "25)",
        "text": "(a) What problem do we have with our Mishnah, which states that one may not recite the Sh'ma in foul water or in Mei Mishrah (water in which flax has been soaked) until one adds water?\n(b) After we amend the Mishnah, what is the Din regarding foul water and Mei Mishrah?\n(c) Then what is the Tana referring to when he requires water to be added?\n(d) According to the Tana Kama in the Beraisa, one needs to add no more than a Kolsh'hu.   What does Rebbi Zakai say?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q26",
        "label": "26)",
        "text": "(a) Rav Nachman establishes the Machlokes by 'the end'.   What does he mean by the end?\n(b) What will both Tana'im then hold at the beginning?\n(c) What does Rav Yosef say? How does he explain the Machlokes?\n(d) Accord to which Tana did he instruct his servant to bring a Revi'is of water before urinating?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q27",
        "label": "27)",
        "text": "(a) The Beraisa discusses an Avit and a G'raf.    What is the difference between them?\n(b) What are they both made of?\n(c) What does the Tana say about reciting the Sh'ma facing either of them when they are empty?\n(d) Why is that?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q28",
        "label": "28)",
        "text": "(a) And what does the Tana say about reciting the Sh'ma facing urine that is in a different receptacle according to ...\n1. ... the Tana Kama?\n2. ... Rebbi Zakai?\n(b) The Tana Kama forbids reciting the Sh'ma in front of urine irrespective of whether it is in front of the bed or behind it.   What does Raban Shimon ben Gamliel say?\n(c) How does he qualify his statement? What must he do before reciting the Sh'ma?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q29",
        "label": "29)",
        "text": "(a) Rebbi Shimon ben Elazar is the most stringent of all.   What does he say about reciting the Sh'ma in front of a receptacle containing urine?\n(b) What option does he have other than removing it from the room?\n(c) When Raban Shimon ben Gamliel talked about keeping a distance of four Amos, he may have been referring to where the urine is in front of the bed.    What will the Din then be if it is behind the bed?\n(d) What else might he have meant?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q30",
        "label": "30)",
        "text": "(a) Based on a similar Beraisa, we resolve the She'eilah from the statement of Rebbi Shimon ben Elazar, who says that if the urine is behind the bed, one may recite the Sh'ma right up to the bed.   What does he say about where it is in front of the bed?\n(b) What problem do we have with the Beraisa?\n(c) How do we resolve it?\n(d) We switch the opinions of Raban Shimon ben Gamliel and Rebbi Shimon ben Elazar in the second Beraisa rather than in the first because of a statement of Rebbi Shimon ben Elazar.   What did he say about a house (i.e. a room) that concurs with his opinion in the first Beraisa?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q31",
        "label": "31)",
        "text": "(a) In connection with the ruling of Raban Shimon ben Gamliel (who gave an option of placing the urine under the bed), Rav Yosef asked Rav Huna a She'eilah with regard to the height of the bed. What did he say about where its height is less than three Tefachim or ten Tefachim or more?\n(b) He himself attributed the former to the principle of 'L'vud' (as if the bed extended to the ground), in which case the urine is considered covered.   To which principle did Abaye attribute the latter ruling?\n(c) Why was it obvious?\n(d) What then was Rav Yosef's She'eilah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q32",
        "label": "32)",
        "text": "(a) What was Rav Huna's response?\n(b) What did Rava subsequently rule?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q33",
        "label": "33)",
        "text": "(a) Rav Paskens like Rebbi Shimon ben Elazar.   What does Rava say?\n(b) With which opinion does Ba'li Amar Rav Ya'akov the son of (Rachel) bas Shmuel (See Mesores ha'Shas) concur?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q34",
        "label": "34)",
        "text": "(a) What happened when Rav Acha'i married off his son to the daughter of Rav Yitzchak bar Shmuel bar Marsa?\n(b) What did he discover when he went to investigate the matter?\n(c) What did he subsequently tell his Mechutan?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q35",
        "label": "35)",
        "text": "(a) Rav Acha'i based his accusation on the Beraisa which discusses performing Tashmish ha'Mitah in the same room as a Seifer Torah.   On what condition is it permitted?\n(b) What if he places it inside ten covers that are made for a Seifer-Torah?\n(c) To what else, besides a Seifer-Torah, does this Din apply?\n(d) What does Rava say about a coat on an Akimt'ra? What is an 'Akimt'ra'?"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "daf": 26,
    "questions": [
      {
        "id": "q1",
        "label": "1)",
        "text": "(a) According to Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi, a Seifer-Torah that is not adequately covered during Tashmish requires a partition.   How high must the partition be?\n(b) What objection did Mar Zutra raise when he saw a partition of ten Tefachim in Mar bar Rav Ashi's bedroom?\n(c) What did Rav Ashi reply when Mar Zutra put it to him?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q2",
        "label": "2)",
        "text": "(a) How did Rava Amar Rav S'chorah qualify our Mishnah, which requires a person who is reciting the Sh'ma to move four Amos away from foul-smelling water and from Tzo'ah?\n(b) What does he add with regard to Tefilah?\n(c) We query Rava however, from a statement of Rafram bar Papa Amar Rav Chisda.   What did Rafram say about Davening in front of a bathroom?\n(d) We refute the suggestion that Rafram is referring to a bathroom that does not contain Tzo'ah from a statement of Rav Yosef (or Rebbi Yossi) bar Chanina.   What did he say about a bathroom that does not contain Tzo'ah or a bathhouse with nobody inside?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q3",
        "label": "3)",
        "text": "(a) And we query the answer that Rava is speaking about a new bathroom from Ravina's She'eilah.   What did Ravina ask about designating a bathroom before it has been used?\n(b) And we answer that Ravina's She'eilah did not concern Davening in front of it (which is definitely permitted).   Then what did it concern?\n(c) What did Rava say about Persian bathrooms?\n(d) Why is that?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q4",
        "label": "4)",
        "text": "(a) What do a Zav who has an emission, a Nidah who exudes Shichvas-Zera and a woman who, after being intimate with her husband, becomes a Nidah have in common?\n(b) The Tana Kama requires them to Tovel (for the emission of Keri) before reciting the Sh'ma.   Why would we have thought otherwise?\n(c) What does Rebbi Yehudah say?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q5",
        "label": "5)",
        "text": "(a) What She'eilah do we ask concerning a Ba'al Keri who became a Zav, according to Rebbi Yehudah?\n(b) What is the Safek? Why might he be worse than a Zav who became a Ba'al-Keri?\n(c) How do we resolve the She'eilah from the Mishnah itself?\n(d) Rebbi Chiya resolves it from a Beraisa that is even more specific than the Mishnah.   What does the Beraisa say about a Ba'al-Keri who became a Zav?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q6",
        "label": "6)",
        "text": "(a) The Tana Kama of our Mishnah rules that one may Daven ...\n1. ... Shachris until midday.   What does Rebbi Yehudah say?\n2. ... Minchah until night.   What does Rebbi Yehudah say?\n(b) What does the Mishnah say about ...\n1. ... Tefilas Arvis?\n2. ... Musaf?\n(c) According to our text, what does Rebbi Yehudah say about Musaf?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q7",
        "label": "7)",
        "text": "(a) We query our Mishnah (which gives the final time for Shachris as Chatzos or four hours) from a Beraisa.   What reason does the Tana there give for reciting the Sh'ma with Hanetz?\n(b) This is based on a statement of Rebbi Yochanan.   What did Rebbi Yochanan say about the Vasikin?\n(c) We query the Shi'ur of Chatzos from another statement of Rebbi Yochanan.   What did Rav Mari b'rei de'Rav Huna ... Amar Rebbi Yochanan say about someone who erred and forgot to Daven ...\n1. ... Ma'ariv?\n2. ... Shachris?\n(d) How do we now reconcile the latter statement of Rebbi Yochanan with our Mishnah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q8",
        "label": "8)",
        "text": "(a) We ask what the Din will be regarding someone forgot to Daven Minchah.  Why might the Din that pertains to someone who forgot Ma'ariv not apply to him?\n(b) From where do we learn that the Shachris after is considered the same day as the Ma'ariv that one missed?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q9",
        "label": "9)",
        "text": "(a) Why, based on the fact that Tefilah is in the place of Korban, might one not be permitted to make up for the missed Minchah?\n(b) On the other hand, why might one nevertheless be permitted to do so?\n(c) We resolve the She'eilah from another statement of Rebbi Yochanan.   What did Rav Huna bar Yehudah ... Amar Rebbi Yochanan specifically say about the She'eilah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q10",
        "label": "10)",
        "text": "(a) We query the latter ruling of Rebbi Yochanan from a Beraisa which discusses the Pasuk in Koheles \"Me'uvas Lo Yuchal Lis'kon ... \".   What does the Tana learn from ...\n1. ... there regarding someone who misses K'ri'as Sh'ma or Tefilah at night or in the morning?\n2. ... the continuation of the Pasuk \"ve'Chesaron Lo Yuchal Lehimanos\"?\n(b) How does Rebbi Yitzchak quoting Rebbi Yochanan himself establish the Pasuk to reconcile it with his ruling?\n(c) And how does Rav Ashi support Rebbi Yochanan's explanation from the wording of the Beraisa 'Zeh she'Biteil Keri'as Sh'ma ... '?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q11",
        "label": "11)",
        "text": "(a) What does the Beraisa say one should do in the event that one forgot to Daven Minchah ...\n1. ... on Friday afternoon?\n2. ... on Shabbos afternoon?\n(b) In which Amidah does he insert Havdalah?\n(c) Why is that?\n(d) What does the Tana say should he inserted Havdalah in the second Amidah? What is he therefore obligated to do?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q12",
        "label": "12)",
        "text": "(a) We query this from another Beraisa which obligates someone who omits Gevuros Geshamim ('Mashiv ha'Ru'ach') in Techi'as ha'Meisim or She'eilah ('Tal u'Matar li'Verachah') in Birchas ha'Shanim to 'go back'.   What does the Tana say about someone who omitted Havdalah in 'Chonen ha'Da'as'?\n(b) How do we reconcile this Beraisa with the previous one (which suggests that Havdalah in the Amidah is crucial)?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q13",
        "label": "13)",
        "text": "(a) According to Rebbi Yossi b'Rebbi Chanina, it was the three Avos who instituted the three Amidos.   What does Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi say?\n(b) Whose opinion do we support with a Beraisa?\n(c) In the first Beraisa, how does the Tana prove that Avraham instituted Shachris from the Pasuk in Vayeira (following the destruction of S'dom), \"Vayashkem Avraham ba'Boker el ha'Makom asher Amad Sham\" (based on the Pasuk in Tehilim \"Vaya'amod Pinchas Vayefalel)\"?\n(d) And what does he learn from the Pasuk in ...\n1. ... Chayei Sarah (just before he met Eliezer and Rivkah) \"Vayeitzei Yitzchak Lasu'ach ba\"Sadeh\" (based on the Pasuk in Tehilim \"Tefilah le'Ani ki Ya'atof, ve'Lifnei Hash-m Yishpoch Sicho\")?\n2. ... Vayeitzei (in connection with Ya'akov's flight to Charan) \"Vayifga ba'Makom\" (based on the Pasuk in Yirmiyahu \"ve'Atah Al Tispalel be'ad ha'Am ha'Zeh ... ve'Al Tifga bi\")?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q14",
        "label": "14)",
        "text": "(a) In the second Beraisa (that supports Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi), with regard to the final time to Daven Shachris, how do the Tana Kama And Rebbi Yehudah learn their respective opinions from the Korban Tamid regarding the final time to Daven ...\n1. ,,, Shachris (until midday & until four hours)?\n2. ... Minchah (until night & until P'lag ha'Minchah)?\n(b) By the same token, from where does the Beraisa learn that 'Tefilas ha'Erev Ein lah K'va'?\n(c) And from where do the Tana Kama and Rebbi Yehudah derive their respective opinions regarding the final time to Daven Musaf (all day & until seven hours)?\n(d) How does the Beraisa finally define ...\n1. ... Minchah Gedolah?\n2. ... Minchah Ketanah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q15",
        "label": "15)",
        "text": "(a) In the Beraisa that we just discussed, Rebbi Yehudah maintains that the final time for Tefilas Minchah is until P'lag ha'Minchah.   Which dilemma does this create?\n(b) How do we resolve it based on another Beraisa?\n(c) How long before night is P'lag ha'Minchah Ketanah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q16",
        "label": "16)",
        "text": "(a) How do we query Rebbi Yossi b'Rebbi Chanina from the latter two Beraisos?\n(b) How do we reconcile them with his opinion?\n(c) How do we prove this answer from Tefilas Musaf?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q17",
        "label": "17)",
        "text": "(a) What dilemma are we faced with regarding Rebbi Yehudah, who says in our Mishnah that the final time for Shachris is 'until four hours'?\n(b) What does 'ad' mean according to the Rabanan?\n(c) How do we try to resolve the She'eilah from Rebbi Yehudah's ruling that the final time for Minchah is P'lag ha'Minchah?"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "daf": 27,
    "questions": [
      {
        "id": "q1",
        "label": "1)",
        "text": "(a) We just proved that Rebbi Yehudah holds 'Ad ve'Lo ad bi'Chelal' from his ruling by Tefilas Minchah. And we now proceed to refute that from his ruling by Musaf ('ad Sheva Sha'os'), based on another Beraisa.   On what grounds does the ...\n1. ... Tana Kama there rule that if someone has not yet Davened Musaf and Minchah, he should Daven Minchah first?\n2. ... Rebbi Yehudah give Musaf precedence?\n(b) What is now the problem with Rebbi Yehudah's ruling, if he holds 'Ad ve'Lo ad bi'Chelal'?\n(c) This forces us to conclude that he holds 'Ad ve'ad bi'Chelal'.   How do we then explain the difference between Rebbi Yehudah and the Tana Kama regarding Minchah? What must Rebbi Yehudah then mean when he says 'ad P'lag ha'Minchah?\n(d) But did the Beraisa, citing Rebbi Yehudah, not say 'P'lag ha'Minchah Achronah Amru, ve'Hi Achas-Esrei Sha'os Chaser Revi'a'? What did the Tana really mean to say?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q2",
        "label": "2)",
        "text": "(a) Rav Nachman supports this conclusion from a Mishnah, which discusses the five testimonies of Rebbi Yehudah ben Bava, the first of which is 'she'Mema'anin es ha'Ketanah'.    What does the statement mean literally?\n(b) Which case was Rebbi Yehudah ben Bava referring to?\n(c) What did he then testify?\n(d) The second testimony is that a woman may remarry on the basis of one witness who testifies that her husband died, and the third that they stoned a rooster in Yerushalayim.   Why did they stone it?\n(e) What was the gist of Rebbi Yochanan's testimony?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q3",
        "label": "3)",
        "text": "(a) The fourth thing that he testified concerned wine that is only forty days old.   What did he say about it?\n(b) And what did he finally say about the Tamid shel Shachar?\n(c) How do we prove from there that Rebbi Yehudah holds 'Ad ve'ad bi'Chelal'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q4",
        "label": "4)",
        "text": "(a) In which Masechta is this Mishnah located?\n(b) Why does the Gemara refer to it as 'Bechirta'?\n(c) What does Rav Kahana therefore prove from there?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q5",
        "label": "5)",
        "text": "(a) According to the Beraisa, what time of day is the Torah referring to when it writes in Beshalach (in connection with Manna) \"ve'Cham ha'Shemesh Venamas\"?\n(b) How do we know that it does not mean six hours? What does the Torah write in connection with Avraham and the angels which precludes this suggestion?\n(c) What is the difference between ...\n1. ... \"ve'Cham ha'Shemesh Venamas\" and \"ke'Chom ha'Yom\"?\n2. ... \"ve'Cham ha'Shemesh Venamas\" and the period before four hours?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q6",
        "label": "6)",
        "text": "(a) What problem do we now have with the Beraisa? Why can the author of the Beraisa therefore not be ...\n1. ... Rebbi Yehudah?\n2. ... the Rabbanan\"?\n(b) Bearing in mind that with regard to collecting the Manna, the Torah writes (not \"ba'Boker\", but) \"ba'Boker ba'Boker\", how do we establish the Beraisa like ...\n1. ... the Rabbanan?\n2. ... Rebbi Yehudah?\n(c) It is unanimously agreed upon that \"ve'Cham ha'Shemesh ve'Namas\" refers to the fourth hour.   How does Rav Acha bar Ya'akov learn it from the phrase itself?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q7",
        "label": "7)",
        "text": "(a) We cited Rav Kahana earlier, who rules like Rebbi Yehudah regarding the final time to Daven Shachris ('since the Mishnah in Iduyos [Bechirta]  conforms with him').   What did Rav Yitzchak answer when Rav Chisda asked him like whom we rule regarding Minchah?\n(b) What did Rav Chisda himself try to prove from the fact that Rav would Daven Kabalas Shabbos before nightfall?\n(c) We counter this however, by citing Rav Huna and the Rabbanan.   What did they used to do (or not used to do)?\n(d) What do we therefore conclude?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q8",
        "label": "8)",
        "text": "(a) When Rav went to the house of Geniva and Davened Kabalas Shabbos before nightfall, where did Rebbi Yirmiyah bar Aba stand?\n(b) Who was Rebbi Yirmiyah bar Aba?\n(c) What did Rav not do when he finished Davening before Rebbi Yirmiyah bar Aba?\n(d) Besides the fact that one is permitted to Daven Kabalas Shabbos on Erev Shabbos and that one is forbidden to enter the space of a person who is Davening the Amidah, what third Halachah do we learn from the current incident?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q9",
        "label": "9)",
        "text": "(a) The above incident with Rav supports Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi.   What did Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi say about entering the space of someone who is Davening the Amidah?\n(b) We query this ruling from Rebbi Ami and Rebbi Asi who walked in front of someone who was Davening he Amidah.  How do we reconcile Rebbi Ami and Rebbi Asi with Rav and Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi?\n(c) We also query Rebbi Yirmiyah bar Aba from a statement of Rav Yehudah.   What did Rav Yehudah Amar Rav prohibit besides Davening next to one's Rebbe?\n(d) Why does he forbid it?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q10",
        "label": "10)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rebbi Eliezer also say in a Beraisa about someone who Davens behind his Rebbe?\n(b) He incorporated in this statement four other items.   The first of them is someone who greets his Rebbe, what is the second?\n(c) What is the exact prohibition?\n(d) The third of the prohibitions is someone who opens his own Beis-ha'Medrash without his Rebbe's consent ('Cholek al Yeshivaso shel Rebbe').   What is the fourth?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q11",
        "label": "11)",
        "text": "(a) How do we now reconcile Rebbi Yirmiyah bar Aba (who Davened behind Rav) with Rav Yehudah Amar Rav and Rebbi Eliezer in the Beraisa?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q12",
        "label": "12)",
        "text": "(a) We prove that Rebbi Yirmiyah bar Aba was a Talmid-Chaver of Rav from the fact that, on that same occasion, he asked Rav 'Mi Badalta?'   What does 'Mi Badalta' mean?\n(b) What ought he to have said had he been merely a Talmid?\n(c) What did Rav reply to the question?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q13",
        "label": "13)",
        "text": "(a) We query Rav's reply however, from a statement of Rebbi Avin, who related an incident where Rav Davened Kabalas Shabbos on Erev Shabbos.   What did Rav do before learning with his Talmidim, all before nightfall?\n(b) What is now the Kashya on Rav?\n(c) How did Rava answer the Kashya? What did Rav actually do, and why does the Kashya fall away?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q14",
        "label": "14)",
        "text": "(a) We ask from Abaye, who permitted Rav Dimi bar Liva'i to smoke baskets after having Davened Kabalas Shabbos on Erev Shabbos.   What did he smoke them with?\n(b) How do we answer that? In what way was that case different?\n(c) What was their mistake?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q15",
        "label": "15)",
        "text": "(a) This answer too, we query from a statement of Avidan.   What did they once do when the sky was overcast and everybody thought that Shabbos had already entered?\n(b) What did Rebbi reply when Avidan asked him what they needed to do?\n(c) What is now the problem with the previous answer?\n(d) How do we resolve it?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q16",
        "label": "16)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rebbi Chiya bar Avin add after citing Rav who Davened Kabalas Shabbos on Erev Shabbos with regard to Rebbi Yashiyah? What did the latter do on Shabbos afternoon?\n(b) What She'eilah do we ask concerning Kidush according to Rav?\n(c) In answer to the She'eilah we cite Rav Nachman Amar Shmuel.   What did he say?\n(d) What is the Halachah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q17",
        "label": "17)",
        "text": "(a) What similar She'eilah do we ask concerning Havdalah according to Rebbi Yashiyah?\n(b) And we answer with a statement of Rav Nachman Amar Shmuel.   What did he say about reciting Havdalah before nightfall?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q18",
        "label": "18)",
        "text": "(a) In a strange conclusion to the Sugya, Rebbi Zeira ... Amar Rav recalls how Rebbi Yishmael b'Rebbi Yossi stood by a certain pillar one Erev Shabbos.   What did he do there?\n(b) According to Ula, it was neither a pillar next to which he stood, not was it Rebbi Yishmael b'Rebbi Yossi, nor was it Kabalas Shabbos that he Davened on Erev Shabbos.  In which location did he stand?\n(c) Who was it?\n(d) What did he Daven?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q19",
        "label": "19)",
        "text": "(a) What objection do we raise to the interpretation of our Mishnah 'Tefilas Arvis Ein lo K'va' - that one may Daven Ma'ariv all night?\n(b) Then what does it mean?\n(c) Rav Yehudah Amar Rav cites Raban Gamliel who holds Tefilas Arvis Chovah'.   Who says that it is R'shus?\n(d) Abaye rules like Raban Gamliel.   What does Rava say?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q20",
        "label": "20)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rebbi Yehoshua reply to a Talmid who asked him whether Tefilas Arvis is R'shus or Chovah?\n(b) What did the Talmid tell Raban Gamliel when he subsequently replied 'Chovah' to the same question?\n(c) The latter said he would wait until all the 'Ba'alei-T'risin' (people who wield shields) gathered in the Beis-ha'Medrash.   To whom was he referring?\n(d) Why did he call them 'Ba'alei-T'risin'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q21",
        "label": "21)",
        "text": "(a) When the questioner repeated his She'eilah and Raban Gamliel repeated his answer, what did Rebbi Yehoshua reply when Raban Gamliel whether there was anyone present who held that Arvis R'shus?\n(b) And what did he reply when Raban Gamliel pointed out that he had been informed that Rebbi Yehoshua himself maintained that it was  and ordered him to stand?\n(c) What happened next that raised the ire of the entire gathering?\n(d) They then ordered Chutzpis to stop.   Who was Chutzpis? What was he doing?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q22",
        "label": "22)",
        "text": "(a) This was the third time that Raban Gamliel had abused Rebbi Yehoshua in this way.   On which other occasion, besides that of the B'chor of Rebbi Tzadok, did he do so?\n(b) What did they therefore decide to do?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q23",
        "label": "23)",
        "text": "(a) Why did they not replace Raban Gamliel with...\n1. ... Rebbi Yehoshua?\n2. ... Rebbi Akiva?\n(b) Whom did they subsequently appoint?\n(c) Besides being both wise and wealthy, what great Yichus did he possess?\n(d) The advantage of being wise is obvious.   What is the advantage of being wealthy?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q24",
        "label": "24)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rebbi Elazar ben Azaryah initially reply when they offered him the illustrious post of Rosh Yeshivah?\n(b) What did he reply when his wife pointed out that perhaps they will depose him too?\n(c) How old was Rebbi Elazar ben Azaryah at the time?\n(d) What other objection did she therefore raise against accepting the appointment?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q25",
        "label": "25)",
        "text": "(a) What happened to override her objection?\n(b) What did Rebbi Elazar ben Azaryah subsequently declare as a result of that miracle in the Mishnah in the first Perek?"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "daf": 28,
    "questions": [
      {
        "id": "q1",
        "label": "1)",
        "text": "(a) Rebbi Yochanan cites a Machlokes between Aba Yosef ben Dustai and the Rabbanan as to how many benches were added in the Beis-ha'Medrash when Rebbi Elazar ben Azaryah became the Rosh Yeshivah.   One of them says four hundred.  What does the other one say?\n(b) What caused this sudden influx of Talmidim?\n(c) Why did Raban Gamliel place the guard at the entrance to the Beis Hamedrash?\n(d) What did Rebbi Elazar ben Azaryah say?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q2",
        "label": "2)",
        "text": "(a) How did they console Rabban Gamliel in a dream?\n(b) How meaningful was the consolation?\n(c) Which Maseches did they learn (initiate) that day in the Beis-ha'Medrash?\n(d) Why is that significant?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q3",
        "label": "3)",
        "text": "(a) What did Raban Gamliel do that was most praiseworthy?\n(b) We know that from what he replied when Yehudah the Ger asked whether he was permitted to marry a bas Yisrael.   What was Yehudah the Ger's She'eilah? Why did he think that it may be forbidden?\n(c) Raban Gamliel maintained that it was Asur.   What did Rebbi Yehoshua say?\n(d) If Raban Gamliel source was the Pasuk \"Lo Yavo Amoni u'Mo'avi bi'Kehal Hash-m\", on what grounds did Rebbi Yehoshua permit it?\n(e) On which principle was his ruling based?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q4",
        "label": "4)",
        "text": "(a) How did Rebbi Yehoshua (based on a similar Pasuk in Amos) counter Raban Gamliel's argument that (based on the Pasuk in Yirmiyahu), the Galus of Amon had already come to an end?\n(b) What did the Beis-Din rule?\n(c) What did this episode prompt Raban Gamliel to do?\n(d) What did he comment when he saw that the walls of Rebbi Yehoshua's house were black?\n(e) What did Rebbi Yehoshua retort?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q5",
        "label": "5)",
        "text": "(a) What did Raban Gamliel mean when he asked Rebbi Yehoshua for forgiveness because 'Ne'eneisi lach'?\n(b) What was Rebbi Yehoshua's initial response?\n(c) What did Raban Gamliel add to his request that elicited forgiveness on the part of Rebbi Yehoshua?\n(d) Who volunteered to inform the Chachamim in the Beis-ha'Medrash that the two Chachamim had made up?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q6",
        "label": "6)",
        "text": "(a) To whom was the laundry-man referring, when, citing Rebbi Yehoshua, he told the Talmidei-Chachamim in the Beis-ha'Medrash ...\n1. ... 'Let the one who is used to wearing the garment wear it!'\n2. ... 'And should the one who is not used to wearing it say to the one who is \"Take off the garment and let me wear it?'\n(b) How did Rebbi Akiva, on behalf of the other Talmidei-Chachamim,  respond?\n(c) Why did he say that?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q7",
        "label": "7)",
        "text": "(a) To whom was Rebbi Akiva referring when he talked about 'a sprinkler the son of a sprinkler'?\n(b) What was the gist of his Mashal?\n(c) What did he mean by that?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q8",
        "label": "8)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rebbi Akiva say to Rebbi Yehoshua when he realized that he had made up with Raban Gamliel?\n(b) Why did they decide not to simply ...\n1. ... depose Rebbi Elazar ben Azaryah and reinstate Raban Gamliel as Nasi?\n2. ... allow them to take it in turns?\n(c) So what did they decide to do?\n(d) This explains the question in Chagigah 'Whose Shabbos was it?'   What does the Gemara there answer?\n(e) And what was the name of the Talmid who posed the She'eilah (concerning Tefilas Arvis) in the first place?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q9",
        "label": "9)",
        "text": "(a) We learned in our Mishnah that one may Daven Musaf all day.   What does Rebbi Yochanan nevertheless comment about somebody who Davens Musaf after seven hours?\n(b) Why does the Tana Kama of the Beraisa rule that somebody who has to Daven Musaf and Minchah should Daven Minchah first?\n(c) On what grounds does Rebbi Yehudah give Musaf precedence?\n(d) Like whom does Rebbi Yochanan Pasken?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q10",
        "label": "10)",
        "text": "(a) Why would one sometimes find Rebbi Zeira sitting outside the Beis-ha'Medrash of Rebbi Nasan bar Tuvi?\n(b) Why did he sit there?\n(c) On one occasion, when Rebbi Nasan bar Tuvi left the Beis-ha'Medrash, Rebbi Zeira asked him who had given the Shi'ur that day.   What did the latter reply?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q11",
        "label": "11)",
        "text": "(a) How did Rebbi Zeira react when Rebbi Nasan bar Tuvi told him that Rebbi Yochanan had taught that the Halachah was not like Rebbi Yehudah (with regard to Davening Musaf before Minchah)?\n(b) What did Rebbi Nasan bar Tuvi mean when he asked Rebbi Zeira ...\n1. ... 'Chada hi Lach?'\n2. ... 'O Chadas hi Lach?'\n(c) To which Rebbi Zeira replied 'Chadas hi Li'.   What had he not been sure about until then?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q12",
        "label": "12)",
        "text": "(a) Based on a Pasuk in Tzefanyah (\"Nugi mi'Mo'ed Asafti mi'Mecha\") what did Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi say about someone who Davens Musaf after seven hours according to Rebbi Yehudah?\n(b) We know that \"Nugi\" in that Pasuk means 'broken' on account of Rav Yosef's translation.   How did Rav Yosef translate it?\n(c) Based on the same Pasuk, what does Rebbi Elazar say about someone who Davens Shachris after four hours according to Rebbi Yehudah?\n(d) Some learn this from the Pasuk in Tehilim \"Dalfah Nafshi mi'Tugah\". Rav Nachman bar Yitzchak learns it from the Pasuk in Eichah \"Besulosehah Nugos ve'Hi Mar lah\".   What does this Pasuk mean?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q13",
        "label": "13)",
        "text": "(a) Where was Rav Yosef the Rosh Yeshivah?\n(b) When did he tend to give his Shabbos Shiur?\n(c) Why did Abaye confront Rav Ivya when he failed to attend one Shabbos?\n(d) What did Rav Ivya reply ...\n1. ... initially?\n2. ... quoting Rav Huna when Abaye asked him why he didn't eat something and then come to the Shi'ur?\n3. ...  quoting Rebbi Yochanan when Abaye asked him why he did not Daven Musaf and come?\n(e) How did Abaye refute Rav Ivya's last argument?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q14",
        "label": "14)",
        "text": "(a) We just cited Rav Huna who forbids eating before Musaf.   What similar ruling does Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi issue regarding Minchah?\n(b) What is the Halachah with regard to eating before ...\n1. ... Musaf?\n2. ... Minchah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q15",
        "label": "15)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rebbi Nechunyah ben Hakanah do when he entered the Beis-ha'Medrash and when he left?\n(b) What was the gist of ...\n1. ... the former?\n2. ... the latter?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q16",
        "label": "16)",
        "text": "(a) Elaborating on the Mishnah, the Beraisa cites the full text of Rebbi Nechunyah's Tefilos.    When entering the Beis-ha'Medrash, what does one ask for after requesting Divine Assistance not to err or stumble over a D'var Halachah (not to declare Tahor something that is Tamei, so that one's colleagues should not rejoice over one's errors)?\n(b) And before leaving, what distinction does one draw between oneself who ...\n1. ... gets up early and others who get up early?\n2. ... toils and others who toil?\n3. ... runs and others who run?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q17",
        "label": "17)",
        "text": "(a) What did Eliezer's Talmidim ask him to teach them when they went to visit him on his death-bed?\n(b) After advising them to be careful to treat their colleagues with respect. he instructed them to keep their children from 'Hegyon', which might mean learning too much Chumash, which is extremely attractive.    What else might it mean?\n(c) Where did he advise them to place them?\n(d) Of what did he tell them to be aware when Davening?\n(e) What did he assure them all this would earn them?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q18",
        "label": "18)",
        "text": "(a) What was Raban Yochanan ben Zakai's reaction when his Talmidim came to visit him on his deathbed?\n(b) When they asked him why he was crying, they addressed him as 'Ner Yisrael and Amud ha'Yemini'.   What third title did they call him by?\n(c) In reply, he began by listing four things, that, as opposed to a king of flesh and blood, are everlasting with regard to Hakadosh-Baruch-Hu, who is the King of Kings: Two of them are that He exists forever and that His anger has permanent effect.  What are the other two?\n(d) Then he mentioned that, as opposed to a king of flesh and blood, there were two things that he could not do. One of them was to appease Him with words.   What was the other?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q19",
        "label": "19)",
        "text": "(a) Finally, he referred to one of two journeys that he was about to make.   Which two journeys?\n(b) So why was he crying?\n(c) Why did he make the contrast between Hash-m and a human king?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q20",
        "label": "20)",
        "text": "(a) How did he respond when his Talmidim asked him for a B'rachah?\n(b) What was their reaction to that unusual B'rachah?\n(c) How did he justify it?\n(d) Why did he then instruct them to remove the vessels from the room?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q21",
        "label": "21)",
        "text": "(a) For whom did he finally instruct them to place a chair?\n(b) What was he coming for?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q22",
        "label": "22)",
        "text": "(a) Our Mishnah cites Raban Gamliel, who maintains that one is obligated to Daven the full Amidah each and every day.   What does Rebbi Yehoshua say?\n(b) What compromise does Rebbi Akiva make?\n(c) What does Rebbi Eliezer say about someone whose Tefilah is fixed (he Davens without expression [See Tiferes Yisrael])?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q23",
        "label": "23)",
        "text": "(a) Rebbi Yehoshua refers to a short Tefilah where one asks Hash-m to redeem the remnant of Yisrael, and that He should always tend to their needs 'be'Chol Parashas ha'Ibur' (which will explained in the Sugya.   How does the Tefilah end?\n(b) On what occasion does one recite it?\n(c) What does the Tana say one should do if one is riding a donkey and wants to Daven the Amidah?\n(d) If this is not possible, one should turn one's face towards Yerushalayim.   What if one cannot do that either?\n(e) What must one do if one wishes to recite the Amidah whilst sailing on a raft?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q24",
        "label": "24)",
        "text": "(a) What is the connection between the Amidah ...\n1. ... and the Mizmor in Tehilim \"Havu le'Hashem b'nei Eilim ... \", according to Rebbi Hillel the son of Rebbi Shmuel bar Nachmeni?\n2. ... and the Sh'ma, according to Rav Yosef?\n3. ... and the vertebrae in one's spinal cord, according to Rebbi Tanchum Amar Rebbi Shmuel bar Nachmeni?\n(b) According to Rebbi Hillel, why did Chazal choose particularly \"Mizmor le'David\"?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q25",
        "label": "25)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rebbi Tanchum Amar Rebbi Shmuel bar Nachmeni say about bowing down during the Amidah?\n(b) What did Ula mean when he added to that 'until an Isar (a small coin) appears'?\n(c) What did Rebbi Chanina say about bowing during the Amidah?\n(d) How did Rava qualify Rebbi Chanina's lenient ruling?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q26",
        "label": "26)",
        "text": "(a) What is the problem with referring to the eighteen B'rachos of the Amidah?\n(b) How does Rebbi Levi solve the problem?\n(c) To what does it correspond according to ...\n1. ... Rebbi Hillel b'rei de'Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi (the Names of Hash-m in 'Mizmor le'David')?\n2. ... Rav Yosef (the Names o Hash-m in the Sh'ma)?\n3. ... Rebbi Tanchum Amar Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi (the vertebrae on the spinal cord)?"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "daf": 29,
    "questions": [
      {
        "id": "q1",
        "label": "1)",
        "text": "(a) What did Shimon ha'Pekuli do in front of Raban Gamliel in Yavneh? Why was he called 'ha'Pekuli'?\n(b) Who responded when Raban Gamliel asked whether there was anyone present who was able to establish a B'rachah against the Tzedokim (who were prominent at that time)?\n(c) What happened the following year when Shmuel ha'Katan himself went to the Amud to Daven?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q2",
        "label": "2)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rav Yehudah Amar Rav say about a Chazan who errs over ...\n1. ... any of the other B'rachos of the Amidah?\n2. ... Birchas ha'Minim?\n(b) Why is that?\n(c) Then why did they not remove Shmuel ha'Katan?\n(d) What did Abaye answer when someone asked why they did not suspect that he had retracted?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q3",
        "label": "3)",
        "text": "(a) How do we answer the Kashya from the Pasuk in Yechezkel \"u've'Shuv Tzadik mi'Tzidkaso ve'Asah Avel\", which suggests that a Tzadik can become a Rasha?\n(b) Citing the Mishnah 'Al Ta'amin be'Atzm'cha ad Yom Moscha', how do we query this answer from Yochanan Kohen Gadol?\n(c) What is the significance of Abaye's answer 'Hu Yanai, Hu Yochanan'."
      },
      {
        "id": "q4",
        "label": "4)",
        "text": "(a) Rava maintains that Yochanan was not alias Yanai ha'Melech.   How does Rava then explain why they did not depose Shmuel ha'Katan as Chazan when he got stuck in the middle of Birchas ha'Minim?\n(b) He bases this ruling on a statement of Rav Yehudah Amar Rav (or Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi).   What did Rav Yehudah Amar Rav say?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q5",
        "label": "5)",
        "text": "(a) The Gemara now discusses the sources of the number of B'rachos in the various Amidos.   Rebbi Chalafta ben Shaul attributes the seven B'rachos in the Shabbos Amidah to the seen 'Kolos'.   Which seven 'Kolos?'\n(b) And to which aspect of Chanah's Tefilah (in Seifer Shoftim) does Rebbi Yitzchak from Carthage attribute the nine B'rachos of the Rosh ha'Shanah (Musaf) Amidah?\n(c) What did Mar say that connects Chanah to Rosh ha'Shanah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q6",
        "label": "6)",
        "text": "(a) We attribute the twenty-four B'rachos that one says on a Ta'anis to the twenty-four expressions of Renanah that Shllomoh ha'Melech recited.   On what occasion did he recite them?\n(b) What problem do we have with that?\n(c) How do we resolve it?\n(d) Why did that day require special mercy?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q7",
        "label": "7)",
        "text": "(a) Rebbi Yehoshua in our Mishnah permits Davening an abridged version of the Amidah ('Me'ein Shemonah-Esrei').   According to Rav, that abridged version is know as 'Havineinu'. How many B'rachos does 'Havineinu' comprise?\n(b) What is the gist of the B'rachah?\n(c) How does it end?\n(d) How does Rav explain 'Me'ein Shemonah-Esrei'?\n(e) What did Abaye say about anybody who Davens 'Havineinu'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q8",
        "label": "8)",
        "text": "(a) On which two occasions does Rav Nachman Amar Shmuel object to Davening it?\n(b) Why is that?\n(c) Rabah bar Shmuel queries Rav Nachman from a Beraisa. According to Rebbi Eliezer there, one inserts 'Havdalah' on Motza'ei Shabbos .... in 'Modim'.   What does Rebbi Akiva say?\n(d) What did Rav Nachman reply to Rabah bar Shmuel's suggestion to insert Havdalah as a fourth independent B'rachah, like Rebbi Akiva?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q9",
        "label": "9)",
        "text": "(a) Why do we not Pasken like Rebbi Akiva all the year round?\n(b) How do we initially use the same logic to explain Rav Nachman Amar Shmuel's ruling?\n(c) On what grounds do we reject this proof? What obvious alternative does one have?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q10",
        "label": "10)",
        "text": "(a) On what grounds does Rav Bibi bar Abaye maintain that one cannot recite 'Havineinu' during the winter months?\n(b) On what grounds do we refute Mar Zutra's suggestion that we insert it in 'Havineinu' ('ve'Dashneinu bi'Ne'os Artz'cha ve'Sein Tal u'Matar ... ')?\n(c) How do we reconcile this with the fact that the Chachamim instituted Havdalah in 'Chonein ha'Da'as' and were not worried that one may err?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q11",
        "label": "11)",
        "text": "(a) Based on a statement of Rebbi Tanchum Amar Rav Asi, Rav Ashi suggests that one inserts 've'Sein Tal u'Matar ... ' in Shome'a Tefilah.  What did Rebbi Tanchum Amar Rav Asi say about someone who forgets ...\n1. ... Gevuros Geshamim in Techi'as ha'Meisim?\n2. ... She'eilah in Birchas ha'Shanim?\n(b) How do we answer the Kashya?\n(c) What did Rebbi Tanchum Amar Rav Asi also say about someone who forgot Havdalah in 'Chonein ha'Da'as'?\n(d) Why is that?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q12",
        "label": "12)",
        "text": "(a) How do we initially reconcile the ruling of Rebbi Tanchum concerning 'Gevuros Geshamim' with the Beraisa which says 'Ein Machzirin oso'?\n(b) Why be'Tzibur, do we think that one does not need to go back?\n(c) What problem do we have with this based on the reason given by Rebbi Tanchum?\n(d) So we conclude that both Rebbi Tanchum and the Beraisa are speaking about be'Yachid.    Then why does the Tana say 'Machzirin oso'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q13",
        "label": "13)",
        "text": "(a) According to Rebbi Tanchum Amar ... Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi, what does someone who forgot to insert 'Ya'aleh ve'Yavo' on Rosh Chodesh if he remembers only ...\n1. ... during 'Modim'?\n2. ... during 'Sim Sholom'?\n3. ... after he has concluded the Amidah?\n(b) How did Rav Papa b'rei de'Rav Ada bar Acha define 'concluded the Amidah' in this case?\n(c) If Rav Papa b'rei de'Rav Ada bar Acha learned this from his father, from whom did his father learn it?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q14",
        "label": "14)",
        "text": "(a) Rav Nachman bar Yitzchak qualifies Rav Papa's ruling.    On what condition does one only need to go back to 'Retzei' even if he has already gone back three steps?\n(b) According to the second Lashon he is more stringent.   On what condition must one begin the Amidah again even if one has not yet gone back three steps?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q15",
        "label": "15)",
        "text": "(a) There are four interpretations of Rebbi Eliezer's statement with reference to the importance of not making one's Tefilah fixed.   What does Rebbi Ya'akov bar Idi Amar Rebbi Oshaya mean when he defines it as 'Someone whose Tefilah is a burden to him'?\n(b) The Rabbanan explain that it pertains to someone who reads it mechanically, without feeling.   How do Rabah and Rav Yosef explain it?\n(c) Rebbi Zeira claimed that he was able to insert something different in his Tefilos.   Then why didn't he?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q16",
        "label": "16)",
        "text": "(a) According to Abaye and Rebbi Chanina sons of Avin, Rebbi Eliezer is referring to anybody who does not Daven with 'the redness of the sun'.   What did they mean by that?\n(b) This is based on a statement of Rebbi Chiya bar Aba Amar Rebbi Yochanan.   What did Rebbi Chiya bar Aba say about Davening with the redness of the sun?\n(c) What does Rebbi Zeira subsequently learn from the Pasuk in Tehilim ...\n1. ... \"Yira'ucha Im Shemesh\"?\n2. ... \"ve'Lifnei Yare'ach Dor Dorim\"?\n(d) What did they say in Eretz Yisrael about anybody who waits for 'the redness of the sun to Daven? Which Tefilah were they referring to?\n(e) What was their reason?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q17",
        "label": "17)",
        "text": "(a) Part of the Tefilah composed by Rebbi Yehoshua to recite in a place of danger reads 'be'Chol Parashas ha'Ibur Yih'yu Tzorcheihem Lefanecha'.   How does Rav Chisda Amar Mar Ukva translate it?\n(b) Rebbi Eliezer, Rebbi Yehoshua and Rebbi Elazar b'Rebbi Tzadok argue over the text of the Tefilah that one recites when traveling in a location where there are bands of wild animals and robbers.    Rav Huna Paskens like the fourth version of the B'rachah: 'Tzorchei Am'cha Merubim ve'Da'atam Ketzarah'.   Who is its author?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q18",
        "label": "18)",
        "text": "(a) Who gave Rav Yehudah the brother of Rav Sala Chasida some good pieces of advice?\n(b) What did he tell him what happen if he did not get ...\n1. ... angry?\n2. ... drunk?\n(c) And what did he advise him to do before setting out on a journey?\n(d) How did Rebbi Ya'akov Amar Rav Chisda define that Tefilah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q19",
        "label": "19)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rebbi Ya'akov Amar Rav Chisda say about anybody who sets out on a journey?\n(b) What is the gist of ...\n1. ... the first half of Tefilas ha'Derech?\n2. ... the second half?\n(c) How does it end?\n(d) On what grounds did Abaye object to Rebbi Ya'akov's text 'Y'hi Ratzon mi'Lefanecha Hash-m Elokai ... she'Tolicheini le'Shalom ... '?\n(e) How did he therefore amend it?"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "daf": 30,
    "questions": [
      {
        "id": "q1",
        "label": "1)",
        "text": "(a) We already cited Rebbi Ya'akov Amar Rav Chisda who obligates someone setting out on a journey to recite Tefilas ha'Derech.   What deadline does he give for reciting it?\n(b) How does the B'hag interpret 'ad Kamah ... ad Parsah'?\n(c) According to Rav Chisda, one must stand when reciting Tefilas ha'Derech.   What does Rav Sheishes say?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q2",
        "label": "2)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rav Chisda do, when, on one occasion, he was traveling together with Rav Sheishes and the time came to recite Tefilas ha'Derech?\n(b) Why did Rav Sheishes need to ask his Shamash what Ra Chisda was doing?\n(c) How did he react when the Shamash replied that he was reciting Tefilas ha'Derech?\n(d) Why did he do that?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q3",
        "label": "3)",
        "text": "(a) Besides the actual text, what is the basic difference between 'Havineinu' and the short Tefilah that one Davens in a location of danger?\n(b) How about repeating them when one arrives home?\n(c) What third distinction do we draw between the way that they need to be recited?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q4",
        "label": "4)",
        "text": "(a) On what condition does the Tana Kama of the Beraisa require somebody riding a donkey to dismount and Daven?\n(b) What does Rebbi say?\n(c) Why is that?\n(d) Like whom does Rava (or Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi) Pasken?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q5",
        "label": "5)",
        "text": "(a) Based on the Pasuk in Melachim \"Vehispal'lu el Hash-m\", what does the Tana in another Beraisa say a blind person or someone who does not know the directions should do when Davening the Amidah?\n(b) And what should a person who is Davening ...\n1. ... in Chutz la'Aretz do, based on the Pasuk there \"Vehispal'lu Eilecha Derech Artzam\"?\n2. ... somewhere in Eretz Yisrael, based on the Pasuk there \"Vehispal'lu Eilecha Derech ha'Ir asher Bacharta\"?\n(c) And what does the Tana finally say about a person who is standing ...\n1. ... in Yerushalayim, based on the Pasuk in Divrei ha'Yamim \"Vehispal'lu el ha'Bayis ha'Zeh\"?\n2. ... in the Beis-ha'Mikdash, based on the Pasuk in Melachim \"Vehispal'lu el ha'Makom ha'Zeh\"?\n3. ... in the Kodesh Kodshim?\n4. ... behind the Beis ha'Kapores (behind the Kodesh Kodshim on the west)?\n(d) What is the outcome of all these rulings?\n(e) Rebbi Avin (or Rebbi Avina) supports this with the Pasuk in Shir ha'Shirim \"ke'Migdal David Tzavrech, Banuy le'Talpi'os\".   How does he Darshen the word \"(le')Talpi'os\"?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q6",
        "label": "6)",
        "text": "(a) What would the father of Shmuel and Levi (regarding reciting the Sh'ma and the Amidah) do when they set out on a journey early in the morning?\n(b) This conforms to the Tana Kama of the Beraisa.   What does the Tana say regarding someone who travels on Rosh ha'Shanah, on Succos or on Purim?\n(c) And what does the Tana Kama then say regarding someone who travels by carriage or by boat?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q7",
        "label": "7)",
        "text": "(a) Rebbi Shimon ben Elazar maintains in the latter case that one should recite the Sh'ma and Daven the Amidah in the carriage in order to juxtapose Ge'ulah to Tefilah.   On what grounds does the Tana Kama disagree with that?\n(b) What is then the basis of their Machlokes?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q8",
        "label": "8)",
        "text": "(a) On what occasion did Mereimar and Mar Zutra gather a Minyan in their houses on Shabbos?\n(b) When did the people who attended the D'rashos, who would recite the Sh'ma before the D'rashah, Daven the Amidah?\n(c) When would Rav Ashi recite the Sh'ma and Daven the Amidah when he Darshened?\n(d) Where was Rav Ashi Rosh Yeshivah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q9",
        "label": "9)",
        "text": "(a) Why did Rav Ashi repeat the Amidah when he arrived home after the D'rashah?\n(b) Why did he take his cue from ...\n1. ... Mereimar and Mar Zutra?\n2. ... the father of Shmuel and Levi?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q10",
        "label": "10)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rebbi Elazar ben Azaryah in the Mishnah mean when he says that Tefilas ha'Musafin only applies be'Chaver Ir?\n(b) What do the Chachamim say?\n(c) How does Rebbi Yehudah amend Rebbi Elazar ben Azaryah's ruling?\n(d) How do we explain the Machlokes between the Tana Kama and Rebbi Yehudah in Rebbi Elazar ben Azaryah? What are its ramifications?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q11",
        "label": "11)",
        "text": "(a) Like whom did Rav Huna bar Chiya Amar Rebbi Chiya bar Rav Pasken?\n(b) Rav Chiya bar Avin supported this ruling from a statement of Shmuel.   What did Shmuel declare that he never did in Neherda'a except for one occasion?\n(c) What happened on that occasion that caused Shmuel to Daven Musaf on his own?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q12",
        "label": "12)",
        "text": "(a) What was Rebbi Yanai's response when Rebbi Chanina the T'nach expert Paskened in front of him like Rebbi Yehudah Amar Rebbi Elazar ben Azaryah regarding Davening Musaf on one's own?\n(b) When Rebbi Yochanan claimed that he saw Rebbi Yanai Daven two consecutive Amidos, what did he mean?\n(c) What was he out to prove?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q13",
        "label": "13)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rebbi Yirmiyah suggest to Rebbi Zeira that refuted Rebbi Yochanan's proof?\n(b) On what grounds did Rebbi Zeira reject Rebbi Yirmiyah's suggestion?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q14",
        "label": "14)",
        "text": "(a) Where was Rebbi Ami and Rebbi Asi's Beis-ha'Medrash situated?\n(b) What is the fact that they used to Daven 'between the pillars' of their Beis-ha'Medrash coming to teach us?\n(c) Rav Yitzchak bar Avdimi in the name of Rabeinu Paskened like Rebbi Yehudah in the name of Rebbi Elazar ben Azaryah.   Who is 'Rabeinu'?\n(d) What did Rebbi Chiya bar Aba subsequently do that raised Rebbi Zeira's eyebrows (See 12c)?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q15",
        "label": "15)",
        "text": "(a) Rebbi Zeira refuted the suggestion that maybe Rebbi Chiya bar Aba repeated Shachris because he had Davened the first one without Kavanah based on a statement by Elazar.   What did Rebbi Elazar say about someone who reckons that he is unable to Daven with Kavanah?\n(b) What other reason did he initially suggest as to why Rebbi Chiya bar Aba may have repeated Shachris?\n(c) This reason too, he refuted based on a Beraisa.   What does the Beraisa say about someone who forgets to ...\n1. ... insert 'Ya'aleh ve'Yavo' at Shachris?\n2. ... Daven the Musaf Amidah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q16",
        "label": "16)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rebbi Chiya bar Aba retort citing Rebbi Yochanan?\n(b) This might mean that one does then not need to repeat the Amidah since one subsequently hears it from the Chazen.   How did the B'hag explain it?\n(c) So why did Rebbi Chiya bar Aba in fact retract\n(d) What have we now proved?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q17",
        "label": "17)",
        "text": "(a) What are we referring to when we ask how long one must wait between one Tefilah and another?\n(b) Rav Huna and Rav Chisda argue over the answer. One of them says 'K'dei she'Tischonen Da'ato alav'.   What does he mean?\n(c) What does the other one say?\n(d) What does he mean?\n(e) The one source is the Pasuk \"Va'eschanan el Hash-m\".   From which Pasuk in Ki Sissa does the other one derive his opinion?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q18",
        "label": "18)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rav Anav Amar Rav say about someone who omits 'Ya'aleh ve'Yavo' at Ma'ariv'?\n(b) Why is that?\n(c) How does Ameimar attempt to qualify Rav's ruling?\n(d) What is the reason behind his suggestion?\n(e) On what grounds did Rav Ashi refute it?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q19",
        "label": "19)",
        "text": "(a) What does the Tana mean when he says that one is obligated to Daven the Amidah with 'Koved Rosh'?\n(b) What did the early Chasidim used to do before Davening the Amidah?\n(c) Why did they do that?\n(d) What does the Mishnah say a person should do if, whilst he is Davening the Amidah ...\n1. ... a king greets him?\n2. ... a snake 'winds itself round his heel'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q20",
        "label": "20)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rebbi Elazar learn from the Pasuk in Shmuel (in connection with Chanah) \"ve'Hi Maras Nefesh\"?\n(b) On what grounds do we refute this proof?\n(c) From which Pasuk in Tehilim (that we recite every day at the beginning of Davening) does Rebbi Yossi b'Rebbi Chanina then learn it?\n(d) We refute that proof too, because David was different.   In what way was he different?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q21",
        "label": "21)",
        "text": "(a) So Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi learns 'Koven Rosh' from the Pasuk (also in Tehilim) \"Hishtachavu la'Hashem be'Hadras Kodesh\".   How does he interpret the words \"be'Hadras Kodesh\"?\n(b) On what grounds do we refute this proof too?\n(c) In practical terms, this means emulating Rav Yehudah.   What did Rav Yehudah used to do before he Davened?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q22",
        "label": "22)",
        "text": "(a) How does Rav Nachman bar Yitzchak finally learn the Din of Davening the Amidah with Koved Rosh from the Pasuk in Tehilim \"Ivdu es Hash-m be'Yir'ah ... \"? What is the connection with this Pasuk and Tefilah?\n(b) And what does Rav Ada bar Masna Amar Rav learn from the end of the Pasuk \"ve'Gilu bi'Re'adah\"?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q23",
        "label": "23)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rabah once comment when he noticed that Abaye was in a particularly jovial mood?\n(b) What did Abaye reply?\n(c) in similar vein, Rebbi Zeira once made a similar comment to that of Rabah when he once saw Rebbi Yirmiyah more exuberant than usual. Only he quoted the Pasuk in Mishlei \"be'Chol Etzev Yih'yeh Mosar\".   What does the Pasuk mean?\n(d) What did Rebbi Yirmiyah reply?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q24",
        "label": "24)",
        "text": "(a) On what occasion did Mar b'rei de'Ravina once smash a valuable cup when the people were rejoicing excessively?\n(b) What was the value of the cup?\n(c) Rav Ashi once did the same thing at his son's wedding.   What did he smash?\n(d) What did both sages achieve by doing that?"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "daf": 31,
    "questions": [
      {
        "id": "q1",
        "label": "1)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rav Hamnuna the younger sing at the wedding of Mar b'rei de'Ravina's son following the request of the Rabbanan?\n(b) What did he answer when they asked him how they should respond?\n(c) What does Rebbi Yochanan quoting Rebbi Shimon bar Yochai, learn from the Pasuk in Tehilim \"Az Yimalei S'chok Pinu\"?\n(d) Based on the same Pasuk, when will our mouths be full of laughter?\n(e) What was Resh Lakish's reaction, when he heard this from Rebbi Yochanan?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q2",
        "label": "2)",
        "text": "(a) The Beraisa maintains that the criterion for beginning the Amidah is neither Koved Rosh, Din nor a D'var Halachah.   What then, is it?\n(b) Why can the latter two not be criteria for beginning the Amidah?\n(c) Abaye gives an example of Halachah Pesukah as the ruling of Rebbi Zeira in connection with Jewish women who see a drop of blood.   What did Rebbi Zeira say in that regard?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q3",
        "label": "3)",
        "text": "(a) Rava gives an example of Halachah Pesukah as a ruling of Rav Hoshaya, who permits 'cheating' by bringing one's produce into the house with its chaff.     What does 'with its chaff' mean?\n(b) What does Rav Hoshaya now allow one to do?\n(c) Then why is the owner not allowed to eat a fixed meal from it?\n(d) The source for the Heter min ha'Torah is the Pasuk in Re'ei (in connection with T'rumah) \"Reishis Degancha\".   What do we learn from there?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q4",
        "label": "4)",
        "text": "(a) Alternatively, Rava cites the Halachah Pesukah of Rav Huna.    What did Rav Huna saWh about the blood of a Kodshim animal on which one performed Hakazas ha'Dam (blood-letting)?\n(b) What do we learn from the Pasuk in Acharei-Mos (in connection with blood) \"Nesativ lachem al ha'Mizbe'ach\"?\n(c) How do we then reconcile Rav Huna's ruling with this D'rashah?\n(d) What do we mean when we conclude that ...\n1. ... the Rabbanan did like our Mishnah?\n2. ... Rav Ashi did like the Beraisa?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q5",
        "label": "5)",
        "text": "(a) Another Beraisa states that prior to Davening one should be neither sad nor in a lazy or a jovial mood. Besides not talking, what two other items does the Tana add to this list?\n(b) In what mood does he say one should be when one rises to Daven the Amidah?\n(c) With regard to the Amidah, this translates into 'Divrei Tanchumin shel Torah'.   What does this mean in practical terms?\n(d) What else should one do specifically when in the mood of Simchah shel Mitzvah.\n(e) And we support this with the early Nevi'im.   How do they all conclude their respective Sefarim?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q6",
        "label": "6)",
        "text": "(a) How should one take leave of one's friend according to the Beraisa quoted by Mari the great-grandson of Rebbi Yirmiyah bar Aba)?\n(b) What is the advantage of doing this?\n(c) And we illustrate this with a story where Eav Kahana once accompanied Rav Shimi bar Ashi from Pum Nahara to Tzenisa de'Bavel.   What does Tzenisa de'Bavel mean?\n(d) What did Rav Kahana ask Rav Shimi bar Ashi in connection with them?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q7",
        "label": "7)",
        "text": "(a) Rav Kahana's question reminded Rav Shimi bar Ashi of a statement by Rebbi Yossi b'Rebbi Chanina.   What problem did the latter have with the Pasuk in Yirmiyahu \"ba'Aretz asher Lo Avar bah Ish ve'Lo Yashav Adam Sham\"?\n(b) How did he therefore explain the Pasuk (by first of all interpreting Adam as Adam ha'Rishon)?\n(c) What has that to do with Tzenisa de'Bavel?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q8",
        "label": "8)",
        "text": "(a) When Rav Shimi bar Ashi went from Pum Nahara to bei Tzenisa, what did Rav Kahana do?\n(b) Why was the latter location called by that name?\n(c) What did the latter ask the former about the date-palms there?\n(d) This reminded Rav Shimi bar Ashi about a statement of Rebbi Yossi b'Rebbi Chanina.   What problem did the latter have with the Pasuk in Yirmiyahu \"be'Eretz Lo Avar bah Ish ve'Lo Yashav sham Adam\"?\n(e) How did he therefore explains the Pasuk?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q9",
        "label": "9)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rav Mordechai do when Rav Ashi went from Hagrunya to bei Kipi or even as far as bei Dura?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q10",
        "label": "10)",
        "text": "(a) Aba Shaul in a Beraisa cites the Pasuk in Tehilim \"Tachin Libam Takshiv Oznecha\" in support of the Tana Kama.   What did the Tana Kama say?\n(b) In another Beraisa, Rebbi Yehudah describes how Rebbi Akiva used to Daven the Amidah.   When did he used to cut his Amidah short?\n(c) Why did he do that?\n(d) In stark contrast, when he Davened on his own, he would begin Davening in one corner and they would find him in another corner.   How did he get there?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q11",
        "label": "11)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rebbi Chiya bar Aba learn from the Pasuk in Daniel ...\n1. ... \"ve'Chavin Pesichan leih\"?\n2. ... \"ve'Zimnin T'lasa be'Yoma ... \"?\n(b) From where does he learn that ...\n1. ... this was not a new Minhag initiated by Daniel after he arrived in Bavel?\n2. ... one cannot Daven facing any direction that one fancies?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q12",
        "label": "12)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rebbi Chiya bar Aba learn from ...\n1. ... the Pasuk in Tehilim \"Erev va'Voker ve'Tzahorayim Asichah ve'Ehemeh ... \"?\n2. ... Chanah regarding how to Daven?\n(b) Whereas the order of Tefilah he learns from the Pasuk in Melachim \"li'Shemo'a el ha'Rinah ve'el ha'Tefilah\".   If \"Rinah\" refers to Tefilah (praise), what does \"Tefilah\" refer to?\n(c) What do he now learn from there?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q13",
        "label": "13)",
        "text": "(a) What distinction does Rebbi Chiya bar Aba draw between after 'Emes ve'Yatziv' (i.e. before the Amidah) and after the Amidah?\n(b) What does he specifically allow one to add after the Amidah?\n(c) We support this with a statement by Rebbi bar Ashi in the name of Rav.   What did he permit one to say in 'Shome'a Tefilah'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q14",
        "label": "14)",
        "text": "(a) Rav Hamnuna cites many major Halachos that we can learn from Chanah (one of which we cited a little earlier).   What does he learn from the Pasuk in Shmuel ..\n1. ... \"ve'Chanah hi Medaberes al Libah\"?\n2. ... \"Vayachsh'vehah Eli le'Shikorah\"?\n(b) And what does Rebbi Elazar learn from the Pasuk there \"Vayomer eilehah Eli 'ad Masai Tistakarin' \"?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q15",
        "label": "15)",
        "text": "(a) How does Ula (or Rebbi Yossi b'Rebbi Chanina) interpret the opening words of Chanah's retort \"Lo Adoni!\"? What did she claim Eli ha'Kohen was lacking?\n(b) According to the first Lashon, she accused him of suspecting her falsely.   What did she accuse him of, according to the second Lashon?\n(c) What ought she claim he ought to have realized?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q16",
        "label": "16)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rebbi Elazar learn from ...\n1. ... Chanah's retort?\n2. ... the fact that Chanah asked Eli not to accus her of being a 'bas Beliya'al'?\n(b) From where does he learn with a Gezeirah-Shavah \"Beliya'al\" \"Beliya'al\" that 'Beliya'al' refers to Avodah-Zarah?\n(c) Besides the fact that someone who suspects a fellow-Jew of something that he did not do is obligated to appease him, what does Rebbi Elazar learn from Eli's response \"L'chi le'Shalom\"?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q17",
        "label": "17)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rebbi Elazar comment on the Pasuk \"And Chanah made a Neder and she said 'Lord of Hosts (Hash-m Tzeva'kos)' \"?\n(b) Why did Chanah in fact, refer to Hash-m by that Name?\n(c) What Mashal did she apply to her request regarding a poor man who stood at the entrance of the banqueting hall as a royal banquet was in progress and asked for a morsel of food but nobody took any notice? What did he subsequently say to the king?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q18",
        "label": "18)",
        "text": "(a) When Chanah in her Tefilah said \"Im Ra'oh Tir'eh ba'Oni Amosecha (If you will surely see the suffering of Your maindservant)\", what was she threatening to do when she used the double expression \"Im Ra'oh Tir'eh\"?\n(b) What would she achieve by doing that (based on the Pasuk in Naso \"ve'Nisah ve'Nizre'ah Zara\")?\n(c) On what basis would Hash-m be forced to comply?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q19",
        "label": "19)",
        "text": "(a) This is the opinion of Rebbi Yishmael in a Beraisa.   How does Rebbi Akiva interpret the Pasuk in Naso?\n(b) What is now the problem?\n(c) On what grounds does he disagree with Rebbi Yishmael?\n(d) How will he then explain \"Im Ra'oh Tir'eh ... \"?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q20",
        "label": "20)",
        "text": "(a) What are the connotations of the word \"Amasecha\", which Chanah mentioned three times in her Tefilah?\n(b) Which three things was she referring to?\n(c) What do they have to do with death?\n(d) According to one opinion, Chanah referred to them as 'Bidkei Misah' (examiners of death).   How did she refer to them, according to another opinion?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q21",
        "label": "21)",
        "text": "(a) According to Rav, when Chanah prayed for 'Zera Anashim', she meant that Hash-m should grant her a son who would be a 'Gavra be'Guvrin'.   What did she mean by that?\n(b) Based on the plural term (\"Anashim\"), Shmuel explains that it refers to the two men that Shmuel would crown.   What does Shmuel have to do with Chanah?\n(c) Which two men did he crown?\n(d) Due to the same grammatical inference, how does Rebbi Yochanan interpret it, based on the Pasuk in Tehilim \"Moshe ve'Aharon be'Chohanav u'Shemuel be'Kor'ei Hash-m?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q22",
        "label": "22)",
        "text": "(a) The Rabbanan explain that she Davened for a man who would be absorbed among men.   How did Rav Dimi explain this when he arrived from Eretz Yisrael?\n(b) This means not be too lanky, too short or too stout.   What else, besides 'not too ruddy and not too pale' does it incorporate?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q23",
        "label": "23)",
        "text": "(a) To explain why Chanah said \"I Davened for this boy\", Rebbi Elazar relates that they brought little Shmuel to Eli for having issued a ruling. What did he see them looking for? What ruling did he therefore issue?\n(b) How did he extrapolate it from the Pasuk in Vayikra \"Vehikrivo ha'Kohen\"?\n(c) What was wrong with what he did?\n(d) What was Chanah's response when Eli initially wanted Shmuel killed?\n(e) What did Eli therefore suggest that elicited the above response from Chanah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q24",
        "label": "24)",
        "text": "(a) In an earlier Tefilah of Chanah, where she Davened for a child, the Pasuk relates \"ve'Hinei hi Medaberes al Libah\".   What does Rebbi Elazar in the name of Rebbi Yossi ben Zimra extrapolate from the words \"al Libah\"?\n(b) What did Rebbi Elazar quoting the same Tana also say about someone who fasts on Shabbos (See Tos. DH 'Kol ha'Yoshev')?\n(c) Why is that?\n(d) Why will he nevertheless get punished?\n(e) What does Rav Nachman bar Yitzchak advise him to do escape punishment?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q25",
        "label": "25)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rebbi Elazar mean when he said 'Chanah Hitisah Devarim K'lapei Ma'lah'?\n(b) He said the same about Eliyahu.   What did he accuse Hash-m of?\n(c) What did Rebbi Shmuel bar Rebbi Yitzchak add to this, based on the Pasuk in Michah \"va'Asher Hari'osi\"?"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "daf": 32,
    "questions": [
      {
        "id": "q1",
        "label": "1)",
        "text": "(a) In addition to the Pasuk in Michah that we just cited (\"va'Asher Hari'osi\"), Rebbi Chama b'Rebbi Chanina cites the Pesukim in Yirmiyah \"Hinei ka'Chomer be'Yad ha'Yotzer, kein Atem be'Yadi Beis Yisrael\", and in Yechezkel \"va'Hasirosi es Leiv ha'Even mi'Besarchem, ve'Nasati l'cha Leiv Basar\". What do they all have in common?\n(b) What does Rebbi Chama b'Rebbi Chanina therefore comment on them?\n(c) In what connection does Rav Papa quote the Pasuk in Yechezkel \"Ve'es Ruchi Etein be'Kirbechem ve'Asisi es asher be'Chukai Teileichu\"?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q2",
        "label": "2)",
        "text": "(a) What is Rebbi Elazar pointing out when he 'amends' the word \"el\" (in the Pasuk in Beha'aloscha \"Vayispalel Moshe el Hash-m\") to \"al\"?\n(b) He bases the mandate to do this on Rebbi Eliezer ben Ya'akov.   What did Rebbi Eliezer ben Ya'akov used to do?\n(c) How does de'Bei Rebbi Yanai learn the same lesson from Moshe's words in the first Pasuk in Devarim \"ve'Di Zahav\"? What was Moshe intimating when he said that?\n(d) What Mashal do they give in connection with a lion roaring to illustrate it?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q3",
        "label": "3)",
        "text": "(a) Rebbi Oshaya compares it to someone who possesses a hefty but weak cow, and Rebbi Chiya bar Aba Amar Rebbi Yochanan to a man who took his son, bathed him, gave him food and drink and hung a purse-full of money round his neck.   What is the conclusion of ...\n1. ... the first Mashal?\n2. ... the second Mashal?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q4",
        "label": "4)",
        "text": "(a) What comment does Rav Acha b'rei de'Rav Huna add, based on the Pasuk in Hoshe'a \"ke'Mar'isam va'Yisba'u, Save'u, Vayaram Libam, al-Kein Shechechuni!\"?\n(b) Rav Nachman learns the same thing from the Pasuk in Eikev \"ve'Ram Levavecha ... \".   How does the Pasuk continue?\n(c) The Rabbanan learn it from the Pasuk in Ha'azinu \"Vayishman Yeshurun Vayiv'at\", or from the Pasuk in Vayeilech \"Ve'achal Ve'sava ve'Dashein ... \".   How does the latter Pasuk continue?\n(d) What does Rebbi Shmuel bar Nachmeni Amar Rebbi Yonasan extrapolate from the Pasuk in Hoshe'a \"ve'Chesef Hirbeisi lahem, ve'Zahav Asu le'Ba'al\"?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q5",
        "label": "5)",
        "text": "(a) How does Rebbi Elazar explain the words \"Lech Reid\" (in the Pasuk in Ki Sisa, following the sin of the Golden Calf, \"Lech Reid ki Shicheis Amcha\")?\n(b) Why did Hash-m order him to do so?\n(c) What was Moshe's reaction to that?\n(d) How did Hash-m's words \"Heref mimeni ve'Ashmidem\" galvanize him into action?\n(e) What Mashal do we give (to a king who becomes angry with his son and begins beating hm in front of his close friend) to illustrate this?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q6",
        "label": "6)",
        "text": "(a) What did Hash-m say He would do if Moshe would let him?\n(b) What does Rebbi Avahu extrapolate from the words \"ve'Atah Hanichah Li ... ve'E'esah oscha le'Goy Gadol\"? What makes these words awesome?\n(c) What did Moshe threaten Hash-m at that point?\n(d) To what does Rebbi Elazar attribute Moshe refusal of Hash-m's offer?\n(e) What did mean when he added that in addition, Moshe would be embarrassed if that happened?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q7",
        "label": "7)",
        "text": "(a) Rebbi Elazar translates the Pasuk there \"Vayechal Moshe\" as 'Moshe implored (Hash-m)\".   How does Rav translates it based on the Gezeirah-Shavah \"Vayechal\" \"Lo Yachel Devaro\" (in Matos).\n(b) What do the Chachamim learn from LLo Yachel Devaro\"?\n(c) How does ...\n1. ... Rav therefore translate \"Vayechal Moshe\"?\n2. ... Shmuel translate it, based on the Pasuk there \"And if not (if You don't accept my Tefilah) erase me from your book!\""
      },
      {
        "id": "q8",
        "label": "8)",
        "text": "(a) Rav Yitzchak translates \"Vayechal Moshe\" as 'Moshe caused the Midas ha'Rachamim to take effect (on K'lal Yisrael).   How do the Rabbanan translate it?\n(b) According to Rebbi Eliezer in a Beraisa, it means 'until he was gripped by Achilu.   How do Rebbi Elazar and Abaye between them translate 'Achilu'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q9",
        "label": "9)",
        "text": "(a) The Pasuk continues Z'chor le'Avraham ... Asher Nishba'ta lahem Bach\".  How does Rebbi Elazar interpret the word \"Bach\"?\n(b) What does Moshe's statement therefore mean?\n(c) What is strange about the word \"Amarti\" (in the Pasuk there \"Va'tedaber aleihem Arbeh es Zar'achem ... ve'Chol ha'aretz ha'Zos asher Amarti Etein le'Zar'achem ... \"?\n(d) How does Rebbi Elazar explain it?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q10",
        "label": "10)",
        "text": "(a) Rebbi Elazar also queries the word \"Yecholes\" in the Pasuk (there, quoting the nations of the world, \"mi'Bilti Yecholes Hash-m Lehavi es ha'Am ha'Zeh el ha'Aretz ... \").   What ought Moshe to have said?\n(b) How does he explain it?\n(c) What did Moshe reply when Hash-m reminded him of the incredible miracles that He performed at the Yam-Suf?\n(d) And what does Rebbi Yochanan learn from Hash-m's reply \"Salachti ki'Devarecha!\"?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q11",
        "label": "11)",
        "text": "(a) Based on the word \"ki'Devarecha\", what does Tana de'bei Rebbi Yishmael add?\n(b) How does this Pasuk render Moshe praiseworthy?\n(c) And how does Rava Amar Rav Yitzchak explain the words of Hash-m \"ve'Ulam Chai Ani\"?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q12",
        "label": "12)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rebbi Simlai say about the way should Daven before Hash-m?\n(b) How does he learn it from Moshe Rabeinu's Tefilah in the opening Pesukim of Va'eschanan?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q13",
        "label": "13)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rebbi Elazar say about Tefilah and good deeds?\n(b) How does he learn it from Moshe Rabeinu?\n(c) What did his Tefilah achieve that his good deeds could not?\n(d) On what basis did Rebbi Elazar also say that fasting is greater than Tzedakah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q14",
        "label": "14)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rebbi Elazar learn from the Pasuk in Yeshayah \"Lamah Li Rov Zivcheichem\", on the one hand, and the Pasuk in Eichah \"u've'Parishchem Kapeichem\" on the other?\n(b) How does he prove it from there?\n(c) And what does Rebbi Yochanan learn from the same Pasuk in Yeshayah \"Yadeichem Damim Mile'u\"?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q15",
        "label": "15)",
        "text": "(a) What does the Pasuk in Eichah say that prompted Rebbi Elazar to say that from the day the Beis-ha'Mikdash was destroyed the gates of Tefilah are closed?\n(b) What does he learn from the Pasuk which ends \"e' Dim'asi Al Techrash\"?\n(c) Based on the Pasuk in Eichah \"Sakosah be'Anan Lach me'Avor Tefilah\", what did Rava refrain from doing on a cloudy day?\n(d) In a prophecy that required Yechezkel to take a copper pan, where did Hash-m instruct him to place it ('as an iron wall')?\n(e) Based on that prophecy, what did Rebbi Elazar say about the relationship between Yisrael and their Father in Heaven from the day the Beis-ha'Mikdash was destroyed?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q16",
        "label": "16)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rebbi Chanin Amar Rebbi Chanina say about someone who Davens a long Tefilah?\n(b) He learns it from Moshe, who Davened for forty days (after the sin of the Golden Calf)..   How do we know that he was answered?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q17",
        "label": "17)",
        "text": "(a) We query Rebbi Chanin however, from a statement of Rebbi Chiya bar Aba.   Based on a Pasuk in Mishlei (\"Tocheles Memushachah ... \") what did Rebbi Chiya bar Aba Amar Rebbi Yochanan say about someone who Davens a long Tefilah?\n(b) What does he give as the antidote, based on the continuation of the same Pasuk)?\n(c) How do we reconcile the two statements?\n(d) What does Rebbi Chama b'Rebbi Chanina learn from the repetition of the phrase \"Kaveh el Hash-m\" (in the Pasuk in Tehilim \"Kaveh el Hash-m, Chazak ve'Ya'metz Libechah ve'\"Kaveh el Hash-m\")?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q18",
        "label": "18)",
        "text": "(a) The Beraisa lists four things that require constant Chizuk.   The last two are Tefilah and Derech Eretz.   What is 'Derech Eretz'?\n(b) What are the first two things on his list?\n(c) How does the Tana learn the first two from the Pasuk in Yehoshua \"Rak Chazak ve'Ematz Me'od Lishmor ve'La'asos ke'Chol ha'Torah ... \"?\n(d) From which Pasuk in Tehilim (that we just discussed) does he learn Tefilah?\n(e) What does he then learn from the Pasuk in Yehoshua \"Chazak ve'Vischazek be'ad Ameinu\"?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q19",
        "label": "19)",
        "text": "(a) What problem do we have with the Pasuk in Yeshayah \"Vatomer Tzi'on Azavani Hash-m va'Hashem Shecheichani\"?\n(b) How does Resh Lakish resolve it (with a Mashal of a man who marries a second wife)?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q20",
        "label": "20)",
        "text": "(a) In the list of creations that He created on behalf of Yisrael, how many Mazalos (constellations) did He create?\n(b) After the thirty Chayil (heads of the troops [for each Mazal]), times thirty Ligyon, times thirty Rahaton, times thirty Karton, times thirty Gist'ra, how many stars did He create for each Gist'ra?\n(c) To what does the number of stars per Gist'ra correspond?\n(d) How did this dispose of Yisrael's claim that Hash-m had forsaken them?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q21",
        "label": "21)",
        "text": "(a) What did Hash-m mean when, in the very next Pasuk in Yeshayah, He replied \"ha'Sishkach Ishah Ulah\"? What could He not possibly forget?\n(b) What did He replied (in the same Pasuk) when Yisrael asked Him whether He could also not forget the episode of the Golden Calf?\n(c) In answer to which query does the Pasuk conclude \"ve'Anochi Lo Eshkachech\"?\n(d) This bears out a statement of Rebbi Elazar Amar Rebbi Oshaya.   What did he comment on ...\n1. ... \"Gam Eileh Tishkachnah\"?\n2. ... \"ve'Anochi Lo Eshkachech\"?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q22",
        "label": "22)",
        "text": "(a) We learned in our Mishnah that the early Chasidim used to wait one hour before the Amidah.   Which Pasuk in Tehilim does Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi cite as the source for this?\n(b) What does he learn from the Pasuk there \"Ach Tzadikim Yodu li'Shemecha, Yeishvu Yesharim es Panecha\"?\n(c) What does the Beraisa learn from the same two Pesukim?\n(d) What problem do we have with the long hours that the Chasidim spent immersed in Tefilah?\n(e) How do we resolve the problem?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q23",
        "label": "23)",
        "text": "(a) We learned in our Mishnah that, whilst one is Davening the Amidah, even if one is greeted by a king, one should not respond.   According to Rav Yosef, which kind of king is the Tana referring to?\n(b) Why is one permitted to respond to a Nochri king?\n(c) We query Rav Yosef from a Beraisa.   What does the Beraisa say one should if during the Amidah, one sees an Anas (who will kill a man for his money) or a wagon approaching at speed?\n(d) How do we reconcile Rav Yosef with the Beraisa?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q24",
        "label": "24)",
        "text": "(a) The Beraisa cites an episode with a certain Chasid who was greeted by a Sar (a prince or a captain) after he broke his journey to Daven.   What did the Sar initially do when the Chasid failed to respond to his greeting?\n(b) When he did, the Sar quoted two Pesukim in Va'eschanan; one of them was \"Rak Hishamer l'cha u'Shemor Naf'sh'cha Me'od\",   What was the other?\n(c) Before continuing, how did he refer to the Chasid?\n(d) And what did he add after asking him why he did not respond to his greeting?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q25",
        "label": "25)",
        "text": "(a) What did the Chasid request of the Sar before responding?\n(b) What did he ask the Sar in response to his question?\n(c) And what did the Sar reply when, after he answered the Chasid's first question in the negative, the Chasid asked him what they would do to him if he did?\n(d) How did the Chasid conclude?\n(e) How does the story end?"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "daf": 33,
    "questions": [
      {
        "id": "q1",
        "label": "1)",
        "text": "(a) Commenting on our Mishnah, which forbids one to interrupt the Amidah if a snake is close by, Rav Sheishes permits removing a scorpion.   Why is that?\n(b) We query this however, from a Beraisa.   What distinction does the Tana draw between someone who falls into a pit of snakes or scorpions and someone who falls into a lion's den?\n(c) Why is that?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q2",
        "label": "2)",
        "text": "(a) Rebbi Yitzchak permits a person to interrupt the Amidah if he sees oxen, due to a statement of Rav Oshaya.   What distinction did Rav Oshaya draw between someone who sees a Shor Tam (which has not yet gored three times) and a Shor Mu'ad (which has)?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q3",
        "label": "3)",
        "text": "(a) What does a Beraisa in the name of Rebbi Meir say one should do if one sees an ox feeding from a basket?\n(b) And what should one then do with the ladder?\n(c) Shmuel qualifies Rebbi Meir's advice.   To which sort of ox does it apply and when?\n(d) What does he mean when he says that the 'Satan then dances between its horns'?\n(e) Why specifically then?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q4",
        "label": "4)",
        "text": "(a) The Beraisa tells of an Arod that was causing havoc in the vicinity of Rebbi Chanina ben Dosa.   What is an Arod?\n(b) What did Rebbi Chanina ben Dosa ask them to do when they told him about it?\n(c) What happened after he covered the mouth of the tunnel where it lived with his heel?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q5",
        "label": "5)",
        "text": "(a) After the Arod bit him and died, what did he ...\n1. ... do with it?\n2. ... announce in the Beis-ha'Medrash?\n(b) What was the people's response?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q6",
        "label": "6)",
        "text": "(a) The Mishnah now discusses various aspects of the Amidah.   Whereabouts does insert ...\n1. ... Gevuros Geshamim? What is 'Gevoros Geshamim'?\n2. ... the request for rain?\n(b) Why do we also mention Gevuros Geshamim there?\n(c) According to the Tana Kama, whereabouts do we insert Havdalah?\n(d) Rebbi Akiva says as a fourth B'rachah on its own.   What does Rebbi Eliezer say?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q7",
        "label": "7)",
        "text": "(a) According to Rav Yosef, why did they fix ...\n1. ... Gevuros Geshamim in 'Techi'as ha'Meisim'?\n2. ... She'eilah in Birchas ha'Shanim?\n(b) What did he mean when he also said that they fixed Havdalah in 'Chonein ha'Da'as' because it is Chochmah?\n(c) What reason did the Chachamim give to explain it?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q8",
        "label": "8)",
        "text": "(a) Rebbi Ami praised De'ah (knowledge) because it appears in the first of the weekday B'rachos.   Why else did he praise it, based on the Pasuk in Shmuel \"Ki Keil De'os Hash-m\"?\n(b) What else did he say about De'ah, based on the Pasuk in Yeshayah \"Ki Lo Am Binos Hu, al-Kein Lo Yerachamenu Oseihu\"?\n(c) What did Rebbi Elazar say about ...\n1. ... the Beis-ha'Mikdash, based on the Pasuk in Beshalach \"   ... Pa'alta Hash-m, Mikdash Hash-m ... \"?\n2. ... someone who possesses De'ah, based on a combination of theis Pasuk and the Pasuk Yeshayah?\n(d) How does Rav Acha Karchina'ah query this from the Pasuk in Tehilim \"Keil Nekamos Hash-m ... \"?\n(e) What did Rebbi Elazar reply?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q9",
        "label": "9)",
        "text": "(a) In the same vein as Rebbi Elazar's reply, how did Ula describe the two 'Nekamos' that we are about to quote?\n(b) What is the Pasuk in ve'Zos ha'B'rachah \"Hofi'a me'Har Paran\" referring to?\n(c) Why is it good?\n(d) Which Pasuk does he then quote that refers to something bad?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q10",
        "label": "10)",
        "text": "(a) What problem does Rav Sh'man bar Aba have with the Machlokes in our Mishnah over where to insert Havdalah?\n(b) Rebbi Yochanan conceded to Rav Sh'man bar Aba's statement concerning the Anshei Keneses ha'Gedolah.   What did he then say about Havdalah?\n(c) How does that answer Rav Sh'man bar Aba's Kashya?\n(d) The same statement is quoted in the name of Rebbi Chiya bar Aba Amar Rebbi Yochanan.   What ruling do both statements end with?\n(e) What did Rabah and Rav Yosef say?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q11",
        "label": "11)",
        "text": "(a) Rabah queries the last ruling from a Beraisa.   What does the Tana there say about someone who erred by omitting ...\n1. ... 'Mashiv ha'Ru'ach' in 'Techi'as ha'Meisim' or ve'Sein Tala u'Matar' in Birchas ha'Shanim?\n2. ... Havdalah in 'Chonein ha'Da'as'?\n(b) What is the reason for the latter ruling?\n(c) What is the problem with the reason the way the Tana presents it?\n(d) How do we therefore amend it?\n(e) And we support this from a statement of Rebbi Yochanan.   What did Rebbi Yochanan reply in the presence of Rebbi Binyamin bar Yefes, when Rebbi Yossi (or R. Shimon ben Ya'akov from Tzur) asked him in Tzidon whether someone who forgot Havdalah in 'Chonein ha'Da'as needs to repeat the Amidah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q12",
        "label": "12)",
        "text": "(a) What She'eilah did they ask regarding someone who Davens on Motza'ei Shabbos after heaving already recited Havdalah?\n(b) What did Rav Nachman bar Yitzchak reply?\n(c) How did he learn it from a 'Kal va'Chomer'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q13",
        "label": "13)",
        "text": "(a) What does the Beraisa quoted by Rav Acha Aricha say about someone who recites Havdalah ...\n1. ... in the Tefilah?\n2. ... on both occasions?\n(b) Based on the former ruling, what problem do we have with the latter ruling?\n(c) This problem is based on a statement by Rav (or Rebbi Yochanan and Resh Lakish).   Which La'v does one transgress upon reciting a B'rachah she'Einah Tzerichah according to Rav (or Rebbi Yochanan and Resh Lakish)?\n(d) How do we therefore amend Rav's second statement?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q14",
        "label": "14)",
        "text": "(a) Rav Sheishes asked Rav Chisda what happens if someone forgot Havdalah both in the Amidah and over a cup of wine.  What exactly is the She'eilah?\n(b) What did Rav Sheishes answer?\n(c) When Ravina asked Rava what the Din is regarding whether someone who recited Havdalah in the Amidah repeating it over a cup of wine, he replied 'Like Kidush'.   What did he mean by that?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q15",
        "label": "15)",
        "text": "(a) Rebbi Chiya bar Avin, who was once riding a donkey behind Rebbi Zeira, asked him whether, under certain circumstances, he had in fact ruled in the name Rebbi Yochanan like Rebbi Eliezer in our Mishnah with regard to inserting Havdalah in Hoda'ah.   Under which circumstances?\n(b) What problem do we have with the question?\n(c) On what grounds do we reject the suggestion that ...\n1. ... the Rabbanan )'Atah Chonein') argue with him?\n2. ... Rebbi Akiva ('B'rachah bi'Fenei Atzmah') argues with him?\n(d) Why do we not hold like Rebbi Akiva the whole year round?\n(e) How do we then explain the latter rejection, bearing in mind that on Yom-Tov that falls on Motza'ei Shabbos there are only seven B'rachos?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q16",
        "label": "16)",
        "text": "(a) To answer the question, we amend the wording to 'Matin (ke'Rebbi Eliezer' [instead of 'Halachah ... ').   What does 'Matin' mean?\n(b) In an independent Machlokes, Rav Yitzchak bar Avdimi citing Rav says 'Halachah', and some say 'Matin'.   What is the difference between the two opinions?\n(c) Rebbi Yochanan says 'Modim'.   How does Rebbi Chiya bar Aba quote Rebbi Yochanan?\n(d) On what grounds does Rebbi Zeira accept Rebbi Chiya bar Aba's version of Rebbi Yochanan?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q17",
        "label": "17)",
        "text": "(a) Why did Rebbi Zeira mention Rachbah in his previous statement? Whose Talmid was he?\n(b) What did he quote Rav Yehudah as having said about the seating arrangement on Har ha'Bayis?\n(c) Rebbi Zeira's point was based on the fact that Rachbah used the expression 'Satav li'Feni m mi'Satav'.   What is the significance of his choice of words?\n(d) We reject the explanation that Rachba was careful to quote even the S'feikos of his Rebbe, Rebbi Yehudah.   Why would this have  been physically impossible?\n(e) A second reason is because it was common for Amora'im to quote the opinions of Tana'im accurately.  What third objection do we have against that explanation?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q18",
        "label": "18)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rav Yosef mean when he said (with regard to the previous Sugya, regarding Havdalah in the Amidah on Motza'ei Shabbos that falls on Yom-Tov) 'Lo Hai Yada'na ve'Lo Hai Yada'na'?\n(b) Instead he quoted Rav and Shmuel.   Which 'pearl' did Rav and Shmuel institute in Bavel?\n(c) 'va'Todi'enu' resembles the regular Havdalah.   What did they insert in place of 'bein Yom ha'Shevi'i le'sheishes Yemei ha'Ma'aseh'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q19",
        "label": "19)",
        "text": "(a) The Mishnah rules that if someone says 'Your mercy has reached a bird's nest', we silence him (See Mesores ha'Shas on this Mishnah).   Who is that someone?\n(b) What exactly is he saying?\n(c) The Tana says the same about somebody who says that 'Hashem's Name should be mentioned on the good' or 'Modim Modim'. What is wrong with saying ...\n1. ... the former?\n2. ... the latter?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q20",
        "label": "20)",
        "text": "(a) Two Amora'im dispute what is wrong in saying 'Your mercy has reached a bird's nest', Rebbi Yossi bar Avin and Rebbi Yossi bar Z'vida.   Where did they both live?\n(b) One of them ascribes the prohibition to the fact that this creates jealousy among the world's creatures.   What does the other one say?\n(c) A Chazan once went 'down to the Amud' in Rabah's Shul and declared 'Just as You have mercy on a bird's nest, so too shall You take pity and have mercy on us.   What strange reaction did this elicit from Rabah?\n(d) Who queried Rabah from our Mishnah?\n(e) How do we explain it?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q21",
        "label": "21)",
        "text": "(a) What was Rebbi Chanina's reaction when the Chazan in his Shul began the Amidah with a string of praises 'ha'Keil ha'Gadol ... ve'ha'Nora, ve'ha'Adir ve'ha'Izuz ... '?\n(b) When did he rebuke him?\n(c) Then why do we say the three that we do 'ha'Gadol, ha'Gibor ve'ha'Nora'?\n(d) On what occasion did Ezra insert them?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q22",
        "label": "22)",
        "text": "(a) Rebbi Chanina compared adding more praises to a king who possessed a million golden Dinrim.   What did the people say about him?\n(b) What does that have to do with the current case?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q23",
        "label": "23)",
        "text": "(a) What is Rebbi Chanina referring to when he says that ...\n1. ... 'everything is in the Hands of Hash-m?\n2. ... 'Yir'as Shamayim is the only thing that is not'?\n(b) From which Pasuk in Eikev does he learn it?\n(c) We query the inference from the Pasuk (that Yir'as Shamayim is not significant) from another statement of Rebbi Chanina.   What did Rebbi Chanina, quoting Rebbi Shimon ben Yochai, say based on the Pasuk in Yeshayah \"Yir'as Hash-m hi Otzaro!\"?\n(d) So how do we answer the Kashya?\n(e) How does Rebbi Canina himself compare it to someone from whom one asks to borrow a large (expensive) vessel or a small (cheap) one?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q24",
        "label": "24)",
        "text": "(a) To what does Rebbi Zeira compare someone who says \"Sh'ma Sh'ma\"?\n(b) How do we query this from the Beraisa which states that it is despicable to repeat 'Sh'ma'?\n(c) What do we answer? When is it despicable and when do we silence him?\n(d) Why is that?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q25",
        "label": "25)",
        "text": "(a) On what grounds did Abaye reject Rav Papa's suggestion that perhaps the Chazan is only repeating 'Sh'ma' because he did not have Kavanah the first time?\n(b) What do we do to him ...\n1. ... in the event that this is indeed why he repeated the Pasuk?\n2. ... if he continues to do this habitually?"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "daf": 34,
    "questions": [
      {
        "id": "q1",
        "label": "1)",
        "text": "(a) What does the Tana say about declaring that good people should bless Hash-m (See Mesores ha'Shas)?\n(b) Why is that?\n(c) And what does he say about where a Chazan errs in the (as yet unwritten) text of the Amidah?\n(d) Why should a person not decline to replace him?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q2",
        "label": "2)",
        "text": "(a) From where does the replacement resume?\n(b) What if he skipped an entire B'rachah?\n(c) And what does the Mishnah say about the Chazan answering 'Amen' to Birchas Kohanim?\n(d) What is the reason for this ruling?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q3",
        "label": "3)",
        "text": "(a) What does the Mishnah say about a Chazan who is a Kohen?\n(b) Why is that?\n(c) On what condition does he therefore permit him to Duchen"
      },
      {
        "id": "q4",
        "label": "4)",
        "text": "(a) Given that a person who is asked to act as Chazan should initially refuse, to what does the Beraisa compare someone who ...\n1. ... does not do so?\n2. ... refuses excessively?\n(b) What is therefore the correct procedure?\n(c) Another lists two other things, besides Sarvanus (refusing to act as Chazan) that are bad in excess, but good, when applied modestly. One of them is yeast.   What is the other?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q5",
        "label": "5)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rav Huna say about someone who erred whilst Davening the Amidah and omitted something in ...\n1. ... the first three B'rachos of the Amidah?\n2. ... the middle B'rachos?\n3. ... the last three B'rachos?\n(b) What does Rav Asi mean when he says that the middle B'rachos have no specific order?\n(c) Rav Sheishes cites our Mishnah which obligates the replacement Chazan to resume from the beginning of the B'rachah where the first Chazan erred.   On whom does this pose a Kashya?\n(d) Why is it not a Kashya on Rav Huna, who obligates the person who errs to go back to 'Atah Chonein'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q6",
        "label": "6)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rav Yehudah say about adding one's own personal request during the Amidah.   Where is it not appropriate?\n(b) Where should one then do so?\n(c) Rav Yehudah's ruling is based on a statement of Rebbi Chanina.   To what did Rebbi Chanina compare ...\n1. ... the first three B'rachos of the Amidah?\n2. ... the middle B'achos?\n3. ... the last three B'rachos?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q7",
        "label": "7)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rebbi Eliezer reply when the people complained about a ceefirtain Chazan who Davened ...\n1. ... a long Tefilah?\n2. ... a short Tefilah?\n(b) How ...\n1. ... long was the Tefilah that Moshe Davened after the sin of the Golden Calf?\n2. ... short was the Tefilah that he Davened for his sister Miriam?\n(c) What does Rebbi Ya'akov Amar Rav Chisda learn from the wording of the latter Tefilah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q8",
        "label": "8)",
        "text": "(a) On which four occasions in the Amidah does the Beraisa require one to bow down?\n(b) When should one desist from doing so?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q9",
        "label": "9)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rebbi Shimon ben Pazi Amar Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi in the name of bar Kapara say about ...\n1. ... a Hedyot?\n2. ... a Kohen Gadol?\n3. ... a king?\n(b) Rebbi Yitzchak bar Nachmeni quotes Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi differently.   What he say about ...\n1. ... a Kohen Gadol?\n2. ... a king?\n(c) What is the reason for these distinctions?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q10",
        "label": "10)",
        "text": "(a) What does the Beraisa learn (regarding the definition of the various words denoting bowing down) from the Pasuk ...\n1. ... in Melachim \"Vatikod Bas Sheva Apayim Eretz\"?\n2. ... in Melachim (in connection with the Tefilah of Shlomoh ha'Melech) \"Kam mi'lifnei Mizbach Hash-m mi'Kero'a al Birchav\"?\n3. ... in Vayeishev (in connection with Yosef and his brothers) \"Ha'vo Navo ... Lehishtachavos lefanecha Artzah?\"?\n(b) Whom did Rav Chiya b'rei de'Rav Huna see Matzli Atzlu'yi?\n(c) What did he mean by that? In what connection did he say it?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q11",
        "label": "11)",
        "text": "(a) How do we resolve the contradiction between the Beraisa that considers bending one's knees in 'Hoda'ah' praiseworthy and the Beraisa which considers it despicable?\n(b) When the Rabbanan asked Rava why, despite the second Beraisa, he bent his knees both at the beginning and at the end of Hoda'ah, from whom, besides Rav Nachman, did he claim to have taken his cue?\n(c) How do all these Chachamim reconcile what they did with the Beraisa ...\n1. ... that forbids it?\n2. ... that states 'ha'Kore'a be'Hoda'ah u'be'Hoda'ah shel Hallel, Harei Zeh Meguneh'? How do they establish 'be'Hoda'ah'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q12",
        "label": "12)",
        "text": "(a) The Mishnah considers it a bad sign if someone errs in the Amidah.    What does the Tana say about a Shali'ach Tzibur who errs?\n(b) On which principle is this based?\n(c) What did they say about Rebbi Chanina ben Dosa, when he Davened on behalf of the sick?\n(d) What did he reply when they asked him how he knew?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q13",
        "label": "13)",
        "text": "(a) When the Gemara asked with regard to which B'rachah the Mishnah considers an error a bad sign, what did Rebbi Chiya ... quoting Chad de'bei Rebbi answer?\n(b) Others quote him in connection which a Beraisa which initially requires a person to try and muster Kavanah for the entire Amidah.   What does the Tana add to that?\n(c) What did Rebbi Chiya ... quoting Chad de'bei Rebbi comment on that?\n(d) Regarding which statement in our Mishnah did Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi quote the Pasuk in Yeshayah \"Borei Niv Sefasayim Shalom Shalom la'Rachok, ve'la'Karov Amar Hash-m u'Refasiv\"?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q14",
        "label": "14)",
        "text": "(a) Rebbi Chiya bar Aba Amar Rebbi Yochanan states that all the positive prophesies of the prophets were directed at three groups of people, two of them those who marry off their daughters to Talmidei-Chachamim and those who do business with Talmidei-Chachamim.   What is the third?\n(b) To whom does the Pasuk there \"Ayin Lo Ra'asah Elokim Zulasecha Ya'aseh li'Mechakeh Lo\" refer?\n(c) What does Rebbi Chiya bar Aba mean by that?\n(d) By the same token, about which era did he claim that ...\n1. ... the prophets prophesied?\n2. ... Yeshayah ha'Navi said \"Ayin Lo Ra'asah Elokim Zulasecha\"?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q15",
        "label": "15)",
        "text": "(a) In this point however, Shmuel disagrees with Rebbi Yochanan.  How did Shmuel describe the era of Mashi'ach?\n(b) From which Pasuk in Re'ei did he extrapolate it?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q16",
        "label": "16)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rebbi Chiya bar Aba Amar Rebbi Yochanan also say about the all the prophecies of the Nevi'im regarding ...\n1. ... the Ba'alei Teshuvah?\n2. ... the Tzadikim?\n(b) In this point, Rebbi Avahu disagrees with him.   What did Rebbi Avahu say about Ba'alei Teshuvah and Tzadikim?\n(c) How did he learn this from the Pasuk in Yeshayah \"Shalom Shalom la'Rachok, ve'la'Karov ... \"?\n(d) How does Rebbi Yochanan interpret \"la'Rachok, ve'la'Karov\"?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q17",
        "label": "17)",
        "text": "(a) According to Rebbi Yehoshua ben Levi, \"Ayin Lo Ra'asah Elokim Zulasecha\" refers to wine that has been fermenting in its grapes since the six days of the Creation.  How does Rebbi Shmuel bar Nachmeni interpret it?\n(b) If nobody ever saw Eden, where was Adam ha'Rishon?\n(c) How do we know that Gan and Eden are not one and the same?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q18",
        "label": "18)",
        "text": "(a) The Beraisa cites an incident where the son of Raban Gamliel fell ill.   Whom did he send to Rebbi Chanina ben Dosa to Daven for their recovery?\n(b) Where did the latter go to fulfil Raban Gamliel's request?\n(c) What did he tell the two emissaries upon his return?\n(d) And what did he reply when they asked him whether he was a Navi?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q19",
        "label": "19)",
        "text": "(a) What did Raban Gamliel's emissaries do before leaving Rebbi Chanina ben Dosa's house?\n(b) What did they discover when they reported to Raban Gamliel?\n(c) What did Raban Gamliel's son ask for the moment he recovered?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q20",
        "label": "20)",
        "text": "(a) Who fell ill on another occasion, when Rebbi Chanina ben Dosa went to learn Torah by Raban Yochanan ben Zakai?\n(b) What did he do when the latter asked him to Daven on behalf of his son?\n(c) What did Raban Yochanan ben Zakai exclaim when his son recovered immediately?\n(d) What did he reply when his wife asked him whether this meant that Rebbi Chanina ben Dosa was greater than him?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q21",
        "label": "21)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rebbi Chiya bar Aba Amar Rebbi Yochanan say a room in which one Davens must have?\n(b) What is the reason for this ruling?\n(c) He learned this from the Pasuk \"Ve'chavin Pesichan leih be'Aliseih ... '.   With reference to whom is the Pasuk speaking?\n(d) Where was the room in which he Davened situated?\n(e) In which direction did it face?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q22",
        "label": "22)",
        "text": "(a) Why did Rav Kahana consider it a Chutzpah to Daven in a valley?\n(b) Based on the Pasuk in Tehilim \"Ashrei N'suy Pesha K'suy Chata'ah\", what else did he consider i a Chutzpauh to do?"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "daf": 35,
    "questions": [
      {
        "id": "q1",
        "label": "1)",
        "text": "(a) The Mishnah now discusses Birchos ha'Nehenin (the Brachah Rishonah over food).   What B'rachah does one recite over the fruit of...\n1. ... a tree?\n2. ... the ground?\n(b) What is the sole exception to ...\n1. ... the former?\n2. ... the latter?\n(c) What common reason applies to both of them?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q2",
        "label": "2)",
        "text": "(a) According to the Tana Kama, one recites 'Borei P'ri ha'Adamah' over Yerakos (greens).   What does Rebbi Yehudah say?\n(b) Over what, according to him, does one recite 'Borei P'ri ha'Adamah'?\n(c) Why does he differentiate between them?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q3",
        "label": "3)",
        "text": "(a) What does the Beraisa learn from the double plural form of the word \"Hillulim\" in the Pasuk in Kedoshim (in connection with Neta R'vai (fruit of the fourth year) \"Kodesh Hillulim la'Hashem\"?\n(b) What does Rebbi Akiva extrapolate from there?\n(c) We query the Beraisa however, on the grounds that \"Hilulim\" is needed to each us two other things; one of them is 'Achleih ve'Hadar Achleih'.   What does that mean?\n(d) How do we learn the first 'Achleih' from \"Hilulim\"?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q4",
        "label": "4)",
        "text": "(a) The second Limud teaches us that the Din of R'vai is confined to something over which one sings Shirah.   What is that?\n(b) How do we learn it from there?\n(c) What does Rebbi Shmuel bar Nachmeni Amar Rebbi Yonasan learn from the Pasuk in Shoftim \"Vatomar lahem ha'Gefen 'he'Chadalti es Tiroshi ha'Mesamei'ach Elokim va'Anahim' \"?\n(d) How does he learn it from there?\n(e) We conclude that the Kashya on the Beraisa only applies to the text which refers to the Isur as 'Kerem R'vai'.    Why will it fall away according to the text that refers to it as 'Neta R'vai'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q5",
        "label": "5)",
        "text": "(a) The two texts constitute a Machlokes between Rebbi Chiya and Rebbi Shimon b'Rebbi.   What might we learn from the Gezeirah-Shavah \"Lehosif lachem Tevu'aso \" (written in Kedoshim in connection with Kerem R'vai) from the Pasuk in Ki Seitzei (in connection with Kil'ayim) \" u'Tevu'as ha'Kerem\"?\n(b) How will this too, answer the Kashya on the Beraisa?\n(c) Assuming that text reads 'Kerem R'vai', what still remains difficult if we ...\n1. ... learn the Gezeirah-Shavah?\n2. ... don't learn it?\n(d) According to the latter Kashya, from where can we learn the B'rachah before eating?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q6",
        "label": "6)",
        "text": "(a) How do we initially suggest that we learn the obligation to recite a B'rachah by other foods via a Mah Matzinu from the fruit of a vineyard?\n(b) On what grounds do we refute this suggestion?\n(c) Why can we then not learn it from produce (bread), by which the Torah writes \"ve'Achalta ve'Sava'ta u'Verachta\"?\n(d) So we learn it from a Tzad ha'Shaveh.    Which 'Tzad ha'Shaveh'?\n(e) How do we refute the Tzad ha'Shaveh too? Why can we not learn all foods from it?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q7",
        "label": "7)",
        "text": "(a) What is the one tree whose food we can learn from the 'Tzad ha'Shaveh' of wine and bread?\n(b) How do we query the need to learn olives from the Tzad ha'Shaveh, based on the Pasuk in Shoftim (in connection with Shimshon) \"Vayav'er mi'Gadish ve'ad Kamah ve'ad Kerem Zayis\"?\n(c) How does Rav Papa answer this Kashya?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q8",
        "label": "8)",
        "text": "(a) Left with the Kashya of 'Tzad Mizbe'ach', we try to learn a B'rachah by other food from the (Shiv'as ha'Minim) seven species with which Eretz Yisrael is praised.   From where do we know that the Shiv'as ha'Minim require a B'rachah Achronah?\n(b) What is the problem with learning other foods from them?\n(c) We reiterate the fact that can learn the B'rachah Rishonah from the B'rachah Acharonah with a Kal va'Chomer.   What else do we ask even according to the opinion that holds 'Neta R'vai'? What problem do we have with learning all other foods (such as meat, eggs and fish) from grapes?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q9",
        "label": "9)",
        "text": "(a) What do we mean when we conclude that reciting a B'rachah is a S'vara?\n(b) What does the Beraisa say about someone who benefits from this world without a B'rachah?\n(c) What problem do we have with the suggestion that one can rectify this by going to a Chacham?\n(d) How does Rava therefore amend the Tana's statement 'Yeilech Eitzel Chacham'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q10",
        "label": "10)",
        "text": "(a) In similar vein to the Beraisa that we just learned, what does Rav Yehudah Amar Shmuel learn from the Pasuk in Tehilim \"la'Hashem ha'Aretz u'Melo'ah\"?\n(b) How does Rebbi Levi deal with the apparent contradiction between the aforementioned Pasuk and the Pasuk there \"ha'Shamayim Shamayim la'Hashem ve'Aretz Nasan li'V'nei Adam\"?\n(c) Rav Chanina bar Papa cites the Pasuk in Mishlei \"Gozel Aviv ve'Imo ve'Omar Ein Pesha, Chaver He le'Ish Mashchis\".   To whom do \"Aviv\" and \"Imo\" respectfully, refer?\n(d) Based on this Pasuk, what does Rebbi Chanina bar Papa say about someone who benefits from this world without a B'rachah?\n(e) If he has stolen the B'rachah from Hash-m, what has he stolen from Yisrael?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q11",
        "label": "11)",
        "text": "(a) In connection with the previous question, what does Rebbi Chanina bar Papa learn from the Pasuk ...\n1. ... in Ha'azinu \"ha'Lo Hu Avichah Kanecha\"?\n2. ... in Mishlei \"Sh'ma B'ni Musar Avicha ve'Al Titosh Toras Imecha\"?\n(b) In the earlier Pasuk in Mishlei, to whom does \"Ish Mashchis\" refer?\n(c) How does Rebbi Chanina bar Papa then explain the Pasuk?\n(d) What is the connection between him and Yerav'am?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q12",
        "label": "12)",
        "text": "(a) What problem does Rebbi Chanina bar Papa have with the Pasuk in Hoshe'a \"ve'Lakachti Degani be'Ito ... \"? What does another Pasuk say in Parshas Eikev?\n(b) How does he resolve the 'discrepancy'?\n(c) Bearing in mind the Pasuk in Eikev that we just quoted, what does Rebbi Yishmael in a Beraisa, comment on the Pasuk in Yehoshua \"Lo Yamush Seifer ha'Torah ha'Zeh mi'Picha\"?\n(d) Why is that?\n(e) What objection does Rebbi Shimon bar Yochai raise to that, with regard to someone who plows, plants, reaps, threshes and winnows, each in its time?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q13",
        "label": "13)",
        "text": "(a) How does Rebbi Shimon therefore interpret the Pasuk in Yeshayah \"ve'Amdu Zarim ve'Ra'u Tzonchem ... \" (in keeping with the Pasuk \"Lo Yamush ... \")?\n(b) How does he establish the Pasuk in Eikev?\n(c) And what does he then learn from the Pasuk in Ki Savo \"ve'Avadta es Oyvecha\"?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q14",
        "label": "14)",
        "text": "(a) What did Abaye comment about many who did like Rebbi Yishmael and many who did like Rebbi Shimon bar Yochai?\n(b) Why did Rava instruct the Rabbanan (his Talmidim) to do during the months of Nisan and Tishri?\n(c) Why specifically ...\n1. ... Nisan?\n2. ... Tishri?\n(d) Why did he insist on that?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q15",
        "label": "15)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rabah bar bar Chanah Amar Rebbi Yochanan comment with regard to the corollary of the learning and the work of ...\n1. ... the earlier generations?\n2. ... the latter generations?\n(b) How did he contrast the results?\n(c) And what distinction did he draw between the earlier and the later generations regarding T'rumos and Ma'asros?\n(d) Which Tana did Rebbi Yochanan quote in both cases?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q16",
        "label": "16)",
        "text": "(a) The above statement is connected to the Machlokes regarding when Tevel becomes Chayav Ma'asros min ha'Torah.   According to Rebbi Yanai (after being winnowed and the pile being flattened), produce becomes subject to Ma'asros after entering the house via the door.   From which Pasuk in Ki Savo (in connection with Biy'ur Ma'asros) does he learn it?\n(b) Based on the Pasuk \"ve'Achlu bi'She'arecha ve'Save'u\", what does Rebbi Yochanan say?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q17",
        "label": "17)",
        "text": "(a) What do we initially suggest is the reason for the fact that wine requires a special B'rachah?\n(b) According to Rav Yehudah Amar Shmuel and Rebbi Yitzchak Amar Rebbi Yochanan, what B'rachah does one recite over olive-oil?\n(c) Why does that create a problem with the previous statement?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q18",
        "label": "18)",
        "text": "(a) We try to answer that there is no other option by olive-oil.   Why could one not recite 'Borei P'ri ha'Zayis?\n(b) Why would that create a problem?\n(c) How do we overcome that problem? What B'rachah could one recite over olive-oil?\n(d) What S'vara does Mar Zutra therefore present to explain why one recites a special B'rachah over wine but not over olive-oil?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q19",
        "label": "19)",
        "text": "(a) We query this too, from the Mishnah in Nedarim.   What does the Mishnah say about somebody who makes a Neder not to eat Mazon, what are he only two foods that are allowed to him?\n(b) And we ask that if everything else falls under the category of Mazon, we have a problem with a statement of Rav and Shmuel.   What did Rav and Shmuel about 'Borei Miynei Mezonos'? Over how many species of food does one recite it?\n(c) What is now the problem with that?\n(d) Rav Huna answers that the Mishnah in Nedarim is referring, not to Mazon, but to someone who declares 'Kol ha'Zan alai'.   What Kashya does this now pose on Mar Zutra's statement regarding oil?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q20",
        "label": "20)",
        "text": "(a) How do we finally differentiate between wine (which has a special B'rachah) and oil (which doesn't)?\n(b) We initially query this too, from Rava.   What did Rava used to do on Erev Pesach?\n(c) Why did he used to do that?\n(d) How do we reconcile this with what we just said (that wine satisfies)?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q21",
        "label": "21)",
        "text": "(a) We query this distinction too, from the Pasuk in Tehilim \"ve'Yayin Yesamach L'vav Enosh ve'Lechem L'vav Enosh Yis'ad\".   What is the problem from there?\n(b) How do we reinterpret the Pasuk to answer it?\n(c) Then why do we not recite Birchas ha'Mazon over it?\n(d) When Rav Nachman bar Yitzchak asked Rava what the Din will be if one did fix a Se'udah over wine, the latter rfeplied that when Eliyahu comes and informs us that one fixes a meal over wine then one will be able to Bensch over it.   What in the meantime?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q22",
        "label": "22)",
        "text": "(a) What problem do we have with Rav Yehudah Amar Shmuel and Rebbi Yitzchak Amar Rebbi Yochanan, quoted earlier, who rule that one recites 'Borei P'ri ha'Eitz' over olive-oil?\n(b) We learn this from the Beraisa which rules that someone who anoints himself with T'rumah oil must pay the Kohen the principle plus a fifth.   What if he drinks it?\n(c) Why is that?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q23",
        "label": "23)",
        "text": "(a) We reject the suggestion that they are speaking where one ate the olive-oil together with bread from a Mishnah later in the Perek.   What does the Tana say there about someone who eats a 'secondary' (Tafeil) food together with a 'major' one (Ikar)?\n(b) How does that disprove the previous suggestion?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q24",
        "label": "24)",
        "text": "(a) We conclude that, based on a statement of Rabah bar Shmuel,  Rav Yehudah Amar Shmuel ... is speaking where he 'ate' the olive-oil via Anigron.   What basically, is 'Anigron'?\n(b) Rabah bar Shmuel defines 'Anigron' as Maya de'Silka and Achsigron as Maya de'Kulhu Shalki.   What is ...\n1. ... 'Maya de'Silka'?\n2. ... 'Maya de'Kulhu Shalki'?\n(c) What problem do we have with this answer? What B'rachah ought one to recite over this mixture?\n(d) How do we answer this Kashya?"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "daf": 36,
    "questions": [
      {
        "id": "q1",
        "label": "1)",
        "text": "(a) What does the Beraisa say about someone whose throat hurts him drinking olive-oil on Shabbos (See Tos.fos DH 'Lo Ye'ar'enu')?\n(b) Why is that?\n(c) What does the Tana allow him to do to alleviate the pain?\n(d) What have we proved from here B'rachah-wise?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q2",
        "label": "2)",
        "text": "(a) Bearing in mind that the olive-oil is the major ingredient, why is it then not obvious that one recites 'Borei P'ri ha'Eitz'?\n(b) So why does one?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q3",
        "label": "3)",
        "text": "(a) Over wheat-flour, Rav Yehudah requires the B'rachah 'Borei P'ri ha'Adamah'.   What does Rav Nachman say?\n(b) How did Rava query Rav Nachman ('Don't argue with Rav Yehudah!') from the previous ruling of Shmuel and Rebbi Yochanan?\n(c) On what grounds do we reject the proof from there? In what way is wheat flour worse than olive-oil?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q4",
        "label": "4)",
        "text": "(a) We query this theory too however, based on a statement of Rebbi Zeira  ... Amar Shmuel.   According to Shmuel, what B'rachah does one recite over a raw gourd and barley-flour?\n(b) What do we initially extrapolate with regard to wheat-flour?\n(c) How do we refute the proof? Why did Shmuel see fit to mention specifically barley-flour?\n(d) Why would we have thought that barley-flour is worse than salt and salt-water, which requires 'Shehakol'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q5",
        "label": "5)",
        "text": "(a) Why do we in fact, recite a B'rachah over it?\n(b) What B'rachah does one recite over salt and salt-water?\n(c) From where do we know this?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q6",
        "label": "6)",
        "text": "(a) Shmuel and Rav Yehudah argue over the B'rachah one makes over Korei.   What is 'Korei'?\n(b) According to Rav Yehudah, one recites 'Borei P'ri ha'Adamah'.   What does Shmuel say?\n(c) Rav Yehudah argues that technically it is a Peira.   What does Shmuel say?\n(d) What does Shmuel prove from a radish?\n(e) How do we refute Shmuel's proof?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q7",
        "label": "7)",
        "text": "(a) We query the current refutation from a Tz'laf.   What is a 'Tz'laf'?\n(b) What exactly is the 'Parcha' of the Tz'laf?\n(c) The Mishnah discusses 'kinds of Nitzpeh'.   What is 'Nitzpeh'?\n(d) Why does the Tana refer to 'kinds' of Nitzpeh'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q8",
        "label": "8)",
        "text": "(a) What B'rachah does the Mishnah in require for ...\n1. ... the leaves and the berries of the Tz'laf?\n2. ... the Evyonos (the capers [synonymous with the Parcha]) and the Kafrisin? What is 'Kafrisin'?\n(b) What is now the problem?\n(c) What distinction does Rav Nachman bar Yitzchak draw between a soft Lulav-branch and a caper-bush?\n(d) What is the reason for the former?\n(e) Bearing in mind Shmuel's support of Rav Yehudah, like whom is the Halachah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q9",
        "label": "9)",
        "text": "(a) What distinction does Rav Yehudah Amar Rav draw between the Evyonos of a Tz'laf of Orlah and the Kafrisin in Chutz la'Aretz?\n(b) What problem do we have with this from the Mishnah regarding Tz'laf that we just quoted?\n(c) We answer by establishing Rav Yehudah like Rebbi Akiva in Ma'asros. Rebbi Eliezer there rules that the berries, the capers and peels are subject to Ma'asros.   What does Rebbi Akiva say?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q10",
        "label": "10)",
        "text": "(a) Why did Rav Yehudah then not simply say 'Halachah ke'Rebbi Akiva'?\n(b) On what principle is this based?\n(c) Then why did he not say 'Halachah ke'Rebbi Akiva be'Chutzah la'Aretz'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q11",
        "label": "11)",
        "text": "(a) Which part of the Tz'laf of Orlah did Ravina find Mar bar Rav Ashi throwing away, and which part was he eating?\n(b) Considering that he lived in Bavel, like which Tana did he hold?\n(c) Ravina queried Mar bar Rav Ashi from a Beraisa, where Beis Shamai considers Tz'laf Kil'ayim be'Kerem.   According to that, how does Beis Shamai classify Tz'laf?\n(d) What do Beis Hillel say?\n(e) Why is that?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q12",
        "label": "12)",
        "text": "(a) What do both Beis Shamai and Beis Hillel say about Tz'laf regarding the Chiyuv Orlah?\n(b) What is not the problem with Beis Shamai?\n(c) How do we resolve it?\n(d) What does the Mishnah in Orlah say about Safek Orlah in ...\n1. ... Eretz Yisrael?\n2. ... Syria?\n3. ... Chutz la'Aretz?\n(e) On what condition is the latter permitted?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q13",
        "label": "13)",
        "text": "(a) What Ravina now ask on Mar bar Rav Ashi?\n(b) How do we answer the Kashya?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q14",
        "label": "14)",
        "text": "(a) We ask further that, based on the word \"Es\" (in the Pasuk in Kedoshim \"va'Afraltem Orlaso Es Piryo\"), even according to Rebbi Akiva, the Kafrisin ought to be considered Orlah.  What does \"es\" imply?\n(b) What do we learn from it?\n(c) How does Rava resolve the problem? Why, despite \"Es\", do Kafrisin not have the Din of a Shomer?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q15",
        "label": "15)",
        "text": "(a) Abaye queries Rava's answer from a Mishnah in Uktzin that discusses what does and what doesn't, combine with a pomegranate to make up a Shi'ur k'Beitzah.   Which area of Halachah does this ruling affect?\n(b) What does the Tana there say about ...\n1. ... the Pitma (the flower) at one end of a pomegranate?\n2. ... the Netz (the fluff) at the other end?\n(c) How does this affect the status of the fluff?\n(d) What does the Mishnah say in Orlah about ...\n1. ... the peel and the Netz of a pomegranate?\n2. ... the peels of nuts and their pits?\n(e) What is not the Kashya on Rava?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q16",
        "label": "16)",
        "text": "(a) Seeing as the criterion of the Shomer of a fruit is not connected to whether it is a Shomer after it has become detached, how does Rava redefine the criterion of what makes a Shomer a Shomer?\n(b) Why is the Kafrisin of Tz'laf then not considered a Shomer?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q17",
        "label": "17)",
        "text": "(a) We query this answer of Rava too, from a statement of Rav Nachman regarding Masch'li (of dates).   What are 'Mas'chli'?\n(b) On what grounds did Rav Nachman Amar Rabah bar Avuhah say that Masch'li are suibject to Orlah?\n(c) Why does this pose a Kashya on Rava? When is Masch'li a Shomer?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q18",
        "label": "18)",
        "text": "(a) We answer that Rav Nachman holds like Rebbi Yossi in connection with S'mader.   What is 'S'mader'?\n(b) What does Rebbi Yossi say about it?\n(c) Like whom does Rava then hold?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q19",
        "label": "19)",
        "text": "(a) Rav Shimi from Neherda'a queries Rava from a Mishnah in Shevi'is, which discusses from which stage one is prohibited from cutting down fruit-trees in the Sh'mitah. Beis Chamai say 'mi'she'Yotzi'u'.   What does that mean?\n(b) Beis Hillel agree with Beis Shamai regarding most fruit, but gives different stages for carob-trees, vines, and olive-trees.   The stage for carob-trees is from the time that the fruit develops the shape of a chain (mi'she'Yashrishu'), for vines, mi'she'Yigre'u' and for olive-trees mi'she'Yanitz'u.   What is the meaning of 'mi'she'Yanitz'u'?\n(c) Rav Asi equates 'mi'she'Yigre'u' with Boser and Pul ha'Lavan (a white bean). It is obvious that grapes are not beans.   What does he then mean?\n(d) What is the difference between Boser and S'mader?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q20",
        "label": "20)",
        "text": "(a) Bearing in mind that the Tana gives the Tana considers Boser a fruit and not S'mader, who must be the author of the Mishnah?\n(b) What do we now extrapolate from the Mishnah that poses a Kashya on Rava?\n(c) How does Rava finally resolve the problem? Why are Kafrisin of Tz'laf not considered fruit in that they do protect the Evyonos?\n(d) What happened once when they removed the peel of ...\n1. ... a pomegranate?\n2. ... a Tzlaf?\n(e) Based on the Gemara's conclusion with regard to the Kafrisin (the peel of the Tz'laf), what B'rachah does one recite over it?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q21",
        "label": "21)",
        "text": "(a) According to Rav Sheishes, over peppers one recites 'Borei P'ri ha'Adamah'.   What does Rava say?\n(b) Rava follows his reasoning elsewhere.   What did he say about someone who eats peppers or ginger on Yom Kipur?\n(c) Why does he refer to it as 'Kas Pilp'li ... ')?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q22",
        "label": "22)",
        "text": "(a) We query Rava however, from a Beraisa.   What does Rebbi Meir there query the words \"Kol Eitz Ma'achal\" in the Pasuk in Kedoshim (in connection with Orlah) \" ... u'Neta'tem Kol Eitz Ma'achal va'Araltem Orlaso es Piryo\"?\n(b) How does he therefore interpret \"Kol Eitz Ma'achal\"? Why specifically a pepper-tree?\n(c) What is it coming to teach us?\n(d) And how does he connect this with the Pasuk in Eikev \"Eretz asher Lo be'Miskeinus Tochal bah Lechem, Lo Sechsar Kol bah\"?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q23",
        "label": "23)",
        "text": "(a) What is now the Kashya on Rava?\n(b) How do we reconcile Rava with the Beraisa?\n(c) What did Rava say about someone who eats ginger on Yom Kipur?\n(d) When the Rabbanan (or Ravina) cited this ruling to Mereimar, what did the latter ask from the case of crushed ginger with honey that came from India? What did Rava rule there regarding ...\n1. ... eating it?\n2. ... the B'rachah?\n(e) What did they answer?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q24",
        "label": "24)",
        "text": "(a) We now discuss the B'rachah that one recites over Chavitz Kidra and Daysa (a dish of pounded grain).   What is 'Chavitz Kidra'?\n(b) According to Rav Yehudah, one recites 'Shehakol'.   What does Rav Kahana say?\n(c) Rav Yehudah concedes that the B'rachah for plain Daysa is 'Borei Miynei Mezonos', and they argue over Daysa that resembles Chavitz Kidra.   What sort of Daysa is that?\n(d) What is then the basis of their Machlokes?\n(e) Rav Yosef accepts the opinion of Rav Kahana, based on a ruling of Rav and Shmuel.   What did Rav and Shmuel say about any food that contains one of the five species of grain?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q25",
        "label": "25)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rav and Shmuel also say about any food that comprises the five species of grain?\n(b) Having issued ...\n1. ... the latter ruling (regarding any food that comprises the five species ... ), why did they see fit to issue the former one (regarding any food that contains ... )?\n2. ... the former ruling, why did they see fit to issue the latter one? What would we have thought requires 'Borei Miynei Mezonos', had they not issued it?"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "daf": 37,
    "questions": [
      {
        "id": "q1",
        "label": "1)",
        "text": "(a) We query the previous ruling of Rav and Shmuel (regarding rice and millet) from a Beraisa.   To what does the Tana there compare the B'rachah before and after eating bread made of rice or millet?\n(b) What is Ma'aseh Kedeirah?\n(c) How does this pose a Kashya on Rav and Shmuel?\n(d) What do we answer? In which regard do we compare rice and millet bread to Ma'aseh Kedeirah?\n(e) What B'rachah does one in fact recite ...\n1. ... before rice and millet bread?\n2. ... after rice and millet bread?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q2",
        "label": "2)",
        "text": "(a) We query Rav and Shmuel again from a Beraisa, which begins by defining 'Ma'aseh Kedeirah' as Chilka, Targis, Zariz and Arsan.   If 'Chilka' is grain that has been divided into two, what are 'Targis', 'Zariz' and 'Arsan', respectively?\n(b) What does the Tana say about rice?\n(c) We answer by establishing the Beraisa like Rebbi Yochanan ben Nuri.   How does he define rice?\n(d) And what does he say about ...\n1. ... eating rice on Pesach\n2. ... being Yotzei one's obligation with Matzos made of rice?\n(e) What do the Rabbanan then hold?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q3",
        "label": "3)",
        "text": "(a) We query this from another Beraisa, which discusses the B'rachos that one recites over grain.   What does the Tana say about the B'rachah that one recites when chewing wheat?\n(b) And what B'rachah does one recite over wheat (before and after), if it has been ground, baked and cooked, assuming the pieces ...\n1. ... are still intact?\n2. ... are no longer intact?\n(c) The Tana then equates the B'rachah when chewing rice with that of chewing wheat.   What does he say with regard to the B'rachah over rice (before and after), if it has been ground, baked and cooked, even if the pieces are intact?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q4",
        "label": "4)",
        "text": "(a) On what grounds do we reject the suggestion that the author of the Beraisa is Rebbi Yochanan ben Nuri?\n(b) What is therefore the Kashya on Rav and Shmuel?\n(c) What is the conclusion?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q5",
        "label": "5)",
        "text": "(a) Like which Tana in the Mishnah (on Daf 35.) do we establish the Beraisa which maintains that the B'rachah over wheat kernels is 'Borei Miynei Zera'im', to reconcile it with the Beraisa who requires 'Borei Miynei Mezonos'?\n(b) What does Rebbi Yehudah say?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q6",
        "label": "6)",
        "text": "(a) In the same Beraisa, we learned that the B'rachah after cooked rice is 'al ha'Michyah'. A second Beraisa says 've'Lo K'lum'.   What does 've'Lo K'lum' mean?\n(b) Rav Sheishes establishes the author of the second Beraisa as Raban Gamliel, who initially gives the B'rachah after the five species of grain as 'three B'rachos'.   Which three B'rachos?\n(c) What do the Chachamim say?\n(d) In an incident that once occurred involving Rebbi Akiva and the elders, where was the loft in which they were sitting situated?\n(e) Which of the seven species of fruit (for which Eretz Yisrael is praised) did they bring before them?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q7",
        "label": "7)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rebbi Akiva do when Raban Gamliel asked him to recite the B'rachah Achronah After the meal?\n(b) How did Raban Gamliel react to that?\n(c) The latter replied - by quoting Raban Gamliel himself.   What did Raban Gamliel say?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q8",
        "label": "8)",
        "text": "(a) Rebbi Yehudah quotes Raban Gamliel differently.   What does he say about whatever is of the seven species even if it is not grain, or grain even if it has not been baked as bread?\n(b) What do the Chachamim say?\n(c) And what B'rachah do Raban Gamliel and the Chachamim respectively require over bread made of rice or millet?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q9",
        "label": "9)",
        "text": "(a) Like which Tana has Rav Sheishes now established the Beraisa which requires a B'rachah of 'al ha'Michyah' after cooked rice?\n(b) We have a problem with this however, from the second ruling (the Seifa de'Reisha) there.   What B'rachah Achronah did the Tana there require if the pieces of wheat-bread that were cooked after being baked are no longer intact?\n(c) What is the problem?\n(d) To resolve the discrepancy, we establish that Beraisa like the Chachamim.   How do we amend the Seifa regarding rice ' ... Mevarech alav B'rachah Achas me'ein Shalosh'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q10",
        "label": "10)",
        "text": "(a) Rava discusses Rihata de'Chakla'i and Rihata di'Mechuza.   What is another name for 'Rihata'?\n(b) What is the difference between ...\n1. ... the words 'Chakla'i' and 'Mechuza'?\n2. ... the two types of Chavitza?\n(c) What B'rachah did Rava initially require over the former?\n(d) Why is that?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q11",
        "label": "11)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rava finally rule with regard to Rihata de'Chakla'i?\n(b) He bases this on a statement of Rav and Shmuel.   Which statement?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q12",
        "label": "12)",
        "text": "(a) On what condition does Rav Yosef require 'ha'Motzi' before eating a Chavitza and Birchas ha'Mazon afterwards?\n(b) What equivalent B'rachos will one recite if the pieces are less than a k'Zayis?\n(c) Rav Yosef bases his ruling on a Beraisa which discusses a Kohen who is in Yerushalayim, bringing a Minchah for the first time.   What B'rachah does he recite first?\n(d) What B'rachah does he then recite over the Minchah?\n(e) What is Rav Yosef's proof from there? How does he know that the piece of Minchah that the Kohen is eating consists of a k'Zayis?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q13",
        "label": "13)",
        "text": "(a) Tana de'Bei Rebbi Yishmael disagrees with the previous Beraisa.   How does the Kohen break up the Minchah according to him?\n(b) What B'rachah ought the Kohen to recite according to him?\n(c) We query this however, from yet another Beraisa, which discusses someone who collects the ground flour of Menachos and eats it on Pesach.   What does the Tana say about the equivalent, if it is ...\n1. ... Chametz?\n2. ... Matzah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q14",
        "label": "14)",
        "text": "(a) How do we therefore establish the case?\n(b) What is then the problem with the Seifa 've'Hu she'Achlan bi'Chedei Achilas P'ras'?\n(c) How do we therefore re-establish the Beraisa to solve it?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q15",
        "label": "15)",
        "text": "(a) We finally cite Rav Sheishes who disagrees with Rav Yosef's distinction regarding between pieces that are a k'Zayis and pieces that are less than a k'Zayis.  What does he rule by Chavitza even if the pieces are less than a k'Zayis?\n(b) What condition does Rava add to that?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q16",
        "label": "16)",
        "text": "(a) What did Ravin Amar Rebbi Yochanan say about T'ruknin (regarding Chalah) when he arrived from Eretz Yisrael?\n(b) Abaye defines T'ruknin as Kuba de'Ar'a.   What is 'Kuba de'Ar'a'?\n(c) What does Abaye say about T'risa?\n(d) Some define T'risa as G'vil Marsach, others as Nahama de'Hind'ki (dough that one bakes on a spit-rod, constantly anointing it with oil, or with eggs and oil).   What is 'G'vil Marsach'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q17",
        "label": "17)",
        "text": "(a) Yet a third opinion defines T'risa as Lechem he'Asuy le'Kutach.   What is 'Lechem he'Asuy le'Kutach'?\n(b) Rebbi Chiya cited a Beraisa which exempts it from Chalah.   What problem do we have with that?\n(c) How do we reconcile the two Beraisos? What is 'As'an ke'Avin (or ke'Achin)'?\n(d) On what condition is it then Patur?"
      }
    ]
