  {
    "daf": 38,
    "questions": [
      {
        "id": "q1",
        "label": "1)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rav Yosef reply, when Abaye asked him what B'rachah to recite over Kuva de'Ar'a (which we just discussed with regard to Chalah)?\n(b) On what grounds did Mar Zutra then recite over it 'ha'Motzi' and Birchas ha'Mazon?\n(c) On what grounds did Mar bar Rav Ashi rule that someone who eats it on Pesach has fulfilled his obligation?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q2",
        "label": "2)",
        "text": "(a) What did Mar bar Rav Ashi also say regarding someone who drinks date-honey?\n(b) Why is that?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q3",
        "label": "3)",
        "text": "(a) We support Mar bar Rav Ashi with a Beraisa in T'rumos. Rebbi Eliezer there renders Chayav someone who drinks date-honey, apple-cider, vinegar of Sefuniyos (what are Sefuniyos?) or other fruit-juice.   What is he Chayav?\n(b) What does Rebbi Yehoshua say?\n(c) Why is that?\n(d) Like whom does Mar bar Ra Ashi now hold?\n(e) What in fact, are the only beverages that are considered fruit?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q4",
        "label": "4)",
        "text": "(a) A certain Tamid-Chacham asked Rava what the Din is with regard to T'rima.   What is 'T'rima'?\n(b) What was Rava's initial reaction to the She'eilah?\n(c) In an effort to clarify matters, Ravina asked the questioner whether he was referring to Shumsh'mi (sesame-seeds), Kurt'mi or Purtz'ni.   Why does one press Shumsh'mi?\n(d) If 'Kurt'mi' is saffron (a spice), to which one adds wine and drinks, what is 'Purtz'ni'? Why does one press it?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q5",
        "label": "5)",
        "text": "(a) Ravina's question reminded Rava what T'rima is, and he equated it with Chashilta.   What is 'Chashilta'?\n(b) And he promptly cited Rav Asi.   What did Rav Asi say about using T'rumah dates to manufacture ...\n1. ... T'rima?\n2. ... beer?\n(c) Why the difference?\n(d) What B'rachah does one therefore recite over T'rima of dates?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q6",
        "label": "6)",
        "text": "(a) We now discuss Shesisa.   What is 'Shesisa'?\n(b) According to Rav, the B'rachah over Shesisa is 'Shehakol'.   What does Shmuel say?\n(c) Rav Chisda explains that there is no dispute, but that one is speaking about a thick mixture and the other about one that is thin.   Which is which?\n(d) How will this explain each of the two opinions?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q7",
        "label": "7)",
        "text": "(a) Rav Yosef queries this explanation from a Beraisa.   What does the Tana say about ...\n1. ... mixing the ingredients of a liquid Shesisa on Shabbos?\n2. ... drinking Zeisum ha'Mitzri (made with barley and other ingredients) on Shabbos?\n(b) What is now the problem?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q8",
        "label": "8)",
        "text": "(a) Abaye answers the Kashya with a Mishnah (in Shabbos).   What does the Tana there say about eating and drinking food and beverages that cure on Shabbos?\n(b) On what grounds is it permitted?\n(c) How does this answer Rav Yosef's Kashya?\n(d) What does Abaye add in an alternative answer (which is basically the same as the first)?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q9",
        "label": "9)",
        "text": "(a) Now that the Mishnah in Shabbos teaches us that a liquid Shesisa is permitted on Shabbos (because it is not a cure), what is Rav coming to teach us?\n(b) Why is that?\n(c) On what grounds do we erase 've'Hilch'sa ... ' from the text? Who is its author?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q10",
        "label": "10)",
        "text": "(a) According to the Tana Kama of a Beraisa, one recites over bread the B'rachah of 'ha'Motzi' (like our Mishnah).   What does Rebbi Nechemyah say?\n(b) Based on the Pasuk (in Balak) \"Keil Motzi'am mi'Mitzrayim\", what does even the Tana Kama concede?\n(c) What does ...\n1. ... the Tana Kama say (based on the Pasuk in Eikev \"ha'Motzi l'cha Mayim mi'Tur ha'Chalamamish\")?\n2. ... Rebbi Nechemyah say (based on the Pasuk in Va'eira ha'Motzi eschem mi'Tachas Sivlos Mitzrayim\")\n(d) How do the Chachamim explain the latter Pasuk (based on the beginning of the Pasuk \"vi'Yeda'tem ki Ani Hash-m Elokeichem ... \")?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q11",
        "label": "11)",
        "text": "(a) What did the Rabbanan tell Rav Zeira about bar Rav Z'vid, the brother of Rav Shimon bar Rav Z'vid?\n(b) What was Rebbi Zeira's response? What did he instruct them to do?\n(c) When he eventually came to his house, what B'rachah did he recite over bread?\n(d) What did Rebbi Zeira comment on that?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q12",
        "label": "12)",
        "text": "(a) What two things would bar Rav Z'vid have taught had he recited 'ha'Motzi ... '?\n(b) What did he teach by reciting 'Motzi ... '?\n(c) Then why did he say 'Motzi ...'?\n(d) What is the Halachah?\n(e) What is the reason for this ruling?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q13",
        "label": "13)",
        "text": "(a) We learned in our Mishnah that over vegetables one recites 'Borei P'ri ha'Adamah'.   What do we learn from the fact that the Tana links vegetables with bread?\n(b) What does Ravna'i quoting Abaye extrapolate from this about 'Sh'lakos' (cooked vegetables)?\n(c) Rav Chisda before him said the same thing quoting Rabeinu.   Who is 'Rabeinu'?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q14",
        "label": "14)",
        "text": "(a) Raboseinu who 'came down' from Eretz Yisrael quoting Rebbi Yochanan disagreed however.   Who is 'Raboseinu ... '? What did he say?\n(b) What compromise did Rav Chisda himself make between the two opinions? Over which cooked vegetables does one recite ...\n1. ... 'Shehakol'?\n2. ... 'Borei P'ri ha'Adamah'?\n(c) Why do we cite cabbage, beets and pumpkin?\n(d) Which two vegetables does Rav Nachman bar Yitzchak cite as vegetables that one generally eats raw?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q15",
        "label": "15)",
        "text": "(a) Rav Nachman too, quoting Rabeinu ruled that over Sh'lakos one recites 'Borei P'ri ha'Adamah'.   Who is 'Rabeinu'?\n(b) What did Chavereinu who 'came down' from Eretz Yisrael quoting Rebbi Yochanan say? To whom did he refer to as 'Chavereinu'?\n(c) What did Rav Nachman comment on the two opinions?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q16",
        "label": "16)",
        "text": "(a) Rebbi Meir in a Beraisa rules that if one eats a soaked or a cooked Rakik (Matah), one is Yotzei on Pesach.   What does Rebbi Yehudah say?\n(b) How did Rav Nachman interpret the Machlokes?\n(c) How does this tie up with the Machlokes between Shmuel and Rebbi Yochanan (regarding Sh'lakos)?\n(d) We refute his interpretation however, inasmuch as both opinions hold that over Sh'lakos one recites 'Borei P'ri ha'Adamah'. On what grounds does Rebbi Yossi then say that one is not Yotzei the Chiyuv Matzah with cooked Matzah?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q17",
        "label": "17)",
        "text": "(a) We then quote Rebbi Chiya bar Aba Amar Rebbi Yochanan who requires 'Borei P'ri ha'Adamah' over cooked vegetables.   What does Rebbi Binyamin bar Yefes say?\n(b) From whom did Ula learn his error. when he cited earlier Rebbi Yochanan regarding the same issue?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q18",
        "label": "18)",
        "text": "(a) Why was Rebbi Zeira surprised when he heard that Rebbi Chiya bar Aba and Rebbi Binyamin bar Yefes disputed Rebbi Yochanan?\n(b) What made Rebbi Chiya bar Aba more reliable than Rebbi Binyamin bar Yefes?\n(c) What did he also used to do that the latter did not?\n(d) Above all, we bring two proofs for Rebbi Chiya bar Aba from Rebbi Yochanan himself, the first from a Turmus bean.   What is a 'Turmus bean'?\n(e) What B'rachah did Rebbi Yochanan rule one recites over it?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q19",
        "label": "19)",
        "text": "(a) What did Rebbi Chiya bar Aba attest that he saw Rebbi Yochanan do after eating a salted olive?\n(b) What do we initially think he meant?\n(c) What has a salted olive got to do with cooked food?\n(d) What do we initially think Rebbi Yochanan would have done (B'rachah-wise) had cooking changed the status of the food?\n(e) How do we refute the proof from here that Rebbi Yochanan requires the same B'rachah over cooked food?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q20",
        "label": "20)",
        "text": "(a) Rav Yitzchak bar Shmuel queries Rebbi Chiya bar Aba from a Mishnah in Pesachim.   What does the Tana there say about being Yotzei on Pesach with ...\n1. ... the stalks of the various species of Maror?\n2. ... Maror that has been pickled?\n3. ... Shelukin or cooked? What is Shelukin?\n(b) What is the Kashya on Rebbi Chiya bar Aba (Amar Rebbi Yochanan)?\n(c) How do we refute it?"
      }
    ]
