      },
      {
        "id": "q20",
        "label": "20)",
        "text": "(a) When does the Tana in a Beraisa permit throwing pop-corn and nuts before a Chasan and Kalah?\n(b) Why does he forbid it in the winter?\n(c) What does he say about loaves of bread or cakes?\n(d) Why is that?"
      },
      {
        "id": "q21",
        "label": "21)",
        "text": "(a) What does Rav Yehudah say about someone who forgot and placed food in his mouth without reciting a B'rachah?\n(b) One Beraisa supports Rav Yehudah's ruling and a second Beraisa says that one should swallow it.   What does a third Beraisa say?\n(c) How do we establish ...\n1. ... the second Beraisa?\n2. ... the third Beraisa?\n(d) Why does the second Beraisa require one to spit out the food? Why not move it to the side of the mouth (like the first Beraisa)?\n(e) This is based on a statement of Rav Yitzchak Kaskesa'ah in the name of Rebbi Yochanan.   On which Pasuk in Tehilim is the statement based?"
      }
    ]
